title: swedish rye bread
directions: Soak yeast in warm water.
Combine brown sugar, salt, shortening and add hot water and stir.
Cool.
Stir in rye flour; beat.
Add yeast and caraway seed.
Mix well.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn on floured surface.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Knead.
Place dough in bowl, let rise to double in size.
Divide into 2 portions.
Round each piece.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.
Place on greased sheet.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
For a soft crust, butter tops while hot.

title: magnolia deep south pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour milk in last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook for 10 minutes at 350°, then 30 minutes at 325°.

title: bob hope's lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in pan.
Gradually add water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 1 minute until mixture is clear and thickened.
Stir small amount into beaten egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Stir in lemon juice, butter and rind.
Pour into shell.

title: nana gracia's chilaquales
directions: Tear the tortillas into small bite size pieces and fry in light oil until crisp.
Drain the chips and set aside on a paper towel.
If you use the chorizo sausage, brown this now together with the onions.
If you choose to leave the chorizo out, then just brown the onions lightly and add olives.
Put the ingredients into a casserole. Pour sauce over all and the grated cheese on top. Add a few dollops of sour cream. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin dream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except Dream Whip mixture only until all blended.
Fold in the prepared Dream Whip.
Spoon into 3 baked pie shells.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: pecan sweet roll rings
directions: Unroll crescent dough and separate in to eight rectangles; seal perforations.
Brush with 2 tablespoons butter.
Combine the pecans, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon over each rectangle; gently press into dough.
Roll up jelly roll style, starting at a ling side.
Pinch seams to seal. Twist 2-3 times.

title: molasses candy
directions: Make in a Teflon pan.
Stir with a wooden spoon.
Cook the first 4 ingredients over medium heat until a little dropped in cold water is brittle.
Add the nuts.
Remove at once from stove. Add the baking soda; beat hard.
Turn into two 8 x 8-inch buttered pans, then cut and wrap in waxed paper.

title: easy cherry torte
directions: Combine marshmallows and milk in top of double boiler.
Melt over low heat; cool.
Fold in whipped cream and pour onto graham cracker crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate or freeze.
Serve as is or top with a dab of whipped cream.

title: chocolate banana drop cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together.
Thoroughly mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla together until light and fluffy.
At low speed, blend in chocolate, then flour alternately with bananas.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 1 1/2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and powdered sugar. Stir in vanilla and a tablespoon of water.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Mix together.
Fill loaf pan and refrigerate.

title: split pea soup
directions: Soak peas overnight; drain and add cold water, pork, ham bone or water in which ham has been boiled and onion.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours, or until peas are soft.
Rub through sieve.
Add the flour, mixed with fat, to soup.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add seasonings.
Thin with milk if necessary.

title: biscotti(anise cookies)
directions: Beat eggs with salt; add sugar; blend thoroughly.
Sift flour and baking powder; add to eggs and sugar.
Add anise oil and butter; mix well.
Knead until smooth.
Roll small pieces into 3-inch oblong and other shapes.
Bake in moderate oven 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: aunt irene's slaw
directions: Chop vegetables.
Bring all other ingredients to a boil and pour over cabbage mixture.
Cool and refrigerate overnight.

title: sizzled salmon with chopped tomatoes and mint
directions: Place salmon in an ovenproof glass baking dish and pour orange juice over fish.
Marinate for about 10 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine tomatoes and orange rind.
Set aside.

title: mom's brown sugar sauce
directions: With brown sugar and flour in saucepan, add enough water until thick.
Heat on medium until sugar has melted.
Add butter and stir until thick.
This is delicious on strawberries and cake. Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Dip chicken in melted butter.
Roll in cracker crumbs, parsley, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Last 15 minutes, pour lemon juice over chicken.

title: flying saucers - cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs, molasses and milk.
In another bowl, mix flour, salt, soda, spices, raisins and oats. Mix this with the butter mixture.
Drop in spoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Make sure to leave a lot of space between each cookie.
They spread.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice and fruits.
Stir in Cool Whip and mix well.
Freeze in covered container.
Serves 16.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk in bowl and set aside.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and whipped topping together in bowl.
Add pudding mixture to cheese mixture and blend.
Starting with crushed cookies, alternate layers of cookies and pudding, ending with crushed cookies.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Shake a few potatoes at a time in bag to coat well.
Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place potatoes in single layer in pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Turn once during baking.
Can sprinkle with parsley when done.

title: meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine egg, 1/3 cup pizza sauce and bread crumbs.
Mix in meat.
On foil, pat out beef mixture to a rectangle.
In a small bowl, combine 1/2 c. Mozzarella cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Spoon cheese mixture down the center of loaf.
Use the foil to bring sides of beef together. Pinch and seal sides and edges of beef roll.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool macaroni.
Combine first 6 ingredients. Mix together Western dressing and Miracle Whip.
The color should become a pale pink when enough Miracle Whip has been added.
Stir into first 6 ingredients.

title: disgustingly rich brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease inside of 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Melt the margarine.
Stir together cocoa and sugar.
Stir in melted margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla and stir again.
Add the flour and salt and mix until smooth.
Add nuts.
Scrape the mixture into greased pan and spread into an even layer.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick pulls out clean.
Let cool before cutting.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, water, and syrup to the soft ball stage; then pour 1/2 of the syrup mixture slowly over the beaten egg whites. Add vanilla.
Return remainder of syrup mixture to heat and cook to hard ball stage or until syrup crackles when dropped into cold water.
Continue beating candy while the remaining syrup cooks, and then pour over candy and beat until mixture forms soft peaks and begins to lose its gloss.
Add nuts.
Drop from teaspoon, pushing off with a second spoon onto wax paper.
If Divinity becomes too hard, beat in a few drops of hot water.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onions, bell pepper, salt and pepper. Drain off excess fat.
Add soup, water, corn and chili powder. Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Put this mixture in a casserole dish and spoon cornbread mixture on top.
Bake until cornbread is done.

title: choco-coconut cake roll
directions: Line jelly roll pan with aluminum foil; grease.
Beat egg whites in large bowl until foamy.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar. Beat until stiff peaks.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks; gradually add 1/3 cup sugar and vanilla; keep beating.
Combine flour, cocoa and all remaining ingredients.
Add to liquids.
Blend well.
Spread batter into pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Place on a towel that's sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Roll up and place on a towel to cool.

title: potato and onion casserole
directions: Place alternate layers of potatoes, onion and margarine in a buttered casserole.
Cover with the mushroom soup.
Bake at 350° until the potatoes and onions are tender.

title: crumb cake
directions: Add baking soda to buttermilk and let foam while mixing other ingredients.
Mix
together
flour,
brown
sugar
and shortening until
crumbly.
Set
aside
1 cup for the topping. To the remaining
flour
mixture,
add
the cinnamon, egg and buttermilk. Pour
into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle topping over
the
batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cornmeal waffles
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture. Combine eggs, milk and butter; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Bake in a preheated, oiled waffle iron. Serve hot with desired topping.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Mix and blend all ingredients, except chicken wings.
Place chicken in a glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Form in baking dish; put bell pepper slivers on top of meat loaf, alternating green and red. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: spiced grape jelly
directions: Put enough water with grapes to get them to start boiling (about 1 pint). Boil until grapes are soft. Put in cheese cloth bag and let drip. Bring juice to a boil. Add sugar (2 cups sugar to 3 cups juice). Add rest and boil over low heat until jelly flakes from spoon. Seal in jars.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and butter (or can use all oleo).
Add brown sugar and salt.
Add egg yolks, vanilla and flour.
Beat well.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Scoop cookie dough using a teaspoon.
Roll into balls.
Dip in egg white; roll in ground walnuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Make thumbprint.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Take out and press in thumbprint.
Bake until brown.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and salt and pepper to taste.
Combine 1 package of Ritz crackers, crumbled fine with 1 stick of melted butter.
Top chicken mixture with crackers and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: damson pudding(heritage)
directions: Mix sugar and flour together; add to Damsons.
Add egg yolks and margarine.
Cook in a double boiler until thick; then add vanilla flavoring.
Pour into a baking dish.
Add miniature marshmallows on top.
Heat for 10 minutes in a 350° oven or until marshmallows brown.

title: oat pancakes
directions: Heat griddle over medium-high heat (or preheat electric griddle or skillet to 375°).
Oil lightly. Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and oil. Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cup batter on hot griddle.
Turn when tops are covered with bubbles and edges look cooked.
Turn only once.
Top with fresh or frozen berries or add blueberries or raspberries to batter.
Makes 12 pancakes.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Generously grease four 6 x 3 x 2-inch foil loaf pans.

title: screwball cake
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juices from fruits to measure 4 cups.
Add jello, pudding and tapioca and cook until thick.
Cool and mix with fruit.
Will keep a week in refrigerator.

title: mashed potato soup
directions: Place all in saucepan. Add enough water to cover. Bring to a boil, then simmer until all veggies are tender. Mash all together, then add 1 stick butter and enough warm milk to make soup consistency. If becomes too thin, add Potato Buds to thicken.

title: rhubarb cherry pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Add filling. Top with a lattice crust.
Flute the edges.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes or until crust is golden and filling is bubbling. Yields 8 servings.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Boil lasagne noodles; rinse.
Brown beef with onion and green pepper.
Add tomato sauce to meat mixture; also, add garlic salt and oregano.
Rinse cottage cheese; mix with Mozzarella cheese.

title: cinnamon crisp
directions: Mix well
and pat in greased pan.
Bake at 350°.
Cut in squares.
Makes about 25.

title: veal marsala
directions: Saute veal in oil. Add vegetables and seasonings. Cook over low heat until tender. Add wine and simmer 3 to 4 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix thoroughly pineapple with its juice and dry pudding. Blend in cool whip. Add nuts. Refrigerate for at least two hours.

title: mustard brisket
directions: Trim fat from brisket.
Heat oil in a 6-quart pressure cooker over medium-high heat until hot.
Add brisket and brown all sides.
Add water and next five ingredients.
Close lid securely. Bring to high pressure over high heat, about 4 minutes.
Adjust heat to medium-low or level needed to maintain high pressure. Cook 45 minutes.

title: thumper's tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Strain tuna fish; put in small dish.
Break into little pieces.
Drain peas and set aside. Empty can of soup into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add milk and stir in.
Add the tuna, peas and noodles to the casserole and stir everything together.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place hamburger in a greased casserole.
Cover with the frozen vegetables and pour undiluted soup over all.
Arrange the Tater Tots on top and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cut them into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Put them in a baking dish and fan them slightly. Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs. Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more.
Nice for a special dinner or company.

title: crispy low-fat chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix lemon juice, garlic powder and egg whites, then dip chicken breasts in mixture.
Roll chicken breasts in corn flakes and place on baking sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Recipe makes 4 servings.
Grams of fat per serving: 1.

title: tropical cheese log
directions: Combine cream cheese and pineapple.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Shape into log.
Slice and serve.

title: sudden sauce
directions: Stir together onion, Worcestershire sauce, catsup, brown sugar and water. Simmer 1/2 hour or spread over roast pork or beef for the last hour of baking at 350°. Pour simmered sauce over any meat, when ready to be served.

title: fantastic strawberry pie
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles crumbs.
Add water, one tablespoon at a time, and mix lightly with a fork.
Shape into ball and roll flat (the size of a 9-inch pie plate).
Bake at 450° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Let cool.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Layer pickles and seasoning mix in jar.
Leave out at room temperature overnight.
Shake well, then refrigerate.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Cover or place in Mason jar in refrigerator overnight.

title: kiss cookies
directions: In bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat the first 6 ingredients until fluffy.
At low speed, beat in the next 4 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until browned.
Immediately press kisses on top.

title: lemon fluff salad
directions: Mix sugar and pineapple juice.
Boil 15 minutes and cool.
Mix gelatin with boiling water.
Add cream cheese; mix well, then add pineapple and nuts.
Put in refrigerator and cool.
Whip the cream.
Fold in cooled mixture.
Place in dish and refrigerate. Cut in squares and serve on lettuce.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter (or Crisco), sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, then add bananas.
Add dry ingredients along with buttermilk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: lemon cake(no frosting)
directions: Mix eggs, water and jello for 2 minutes.
Add alternately cake mix and salad oil.
Beat 1 minute.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned candied yams
directions: Peel and cut yams in quarters.
Sprinkle granulated sugar and brown sugar over yams in a medium saucepan.
Add nutmeg, cinnamon, butter, vanilla, salt and water.
Cover and simmer over medium heat until yams are cooked and liquid forms a syrup.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter until consistency of pie crust. Add nuts, vanilla and mix well. Take small pieces and roll out in hand.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until lightly brown.
Cool and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: curried cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower until tender-crisp and put in large casserole dish.
Combine milk, chicken soup, mayonnaise, cheese and curry powder and pour over cauliflower.
Mix together melted butter and crumbs and sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa and 1/2 cup sugar 5 times.
Put egg whites in large bowl of mixer.
Add salt.
Beat on high No. 10 until foamy 1/2 minute.
Add cream of tartar.
Beat on high until whites are stiff and stand in points, 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Sprinkle in rapidly 1 1/3 cups sugar.
Beat on No. 8 about 1 minute.
Turn to No. 2 speed and add vanilla.
Fold in flour mixture, folding in by hand with whip in 4 additions turning bowl often.
Up and over motion about 15 times.
Put in pan; carefully cut through batter with a knife or spatula, going around in circular motion 6 times to release large air bubbles.
Bake in ungreased 10-inch tube pan at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool upside down.

title: mushroom turnovers
directions: Work until all dough is smooth.

title: baked rotini
directions: Boil noodles until tender; drain.
In large skillet, cook beef, onion and green pepper; drain excess fat.
Add tomatoes, paste, mushrooms and seasonings.
Simmer on low heat 20 minutes. Combine cooked noodles and sauce; layer 1/2 into
3 quart baking dish.
Top with 1 cup cheese.
Layer remaining rotini mixture and top with remaining mozzarella.

title: the colonel's original recipe
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan passies
directions: In small mixing bowl, stir together eggs, brown sugar, butter or margarine, vanilla and salt just until smooth.
Mix in pecans or spoon about 1 teaspoon of the chopped pecans into each pastry-lined muffin cup.
Fill each with egg mixture.
Bake in 325° oven about 25 minutes, or until filling is set.
Cool; remove from pans. Cover and chill to store.
Makes 24.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Beat eggs well.
Add to sugar and butter mixture.
Add vanilla and mashed bananas.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk.
Beat well. Add nuts.
Pour into 2 buttered loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: orange juice delight
directions: Combine in blender.
Process until frothy.
Serve immediately. Makes 2 servings.

title: good pilaw
directions: Boil water and add all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and cut heat off.
Let set 20 minutes.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Put roast and water or beef broth in bottom of crock-pot and add seasonings. Add potatoes, carrots, onion, cabbage and green pepper.

title: lemon fluff bars
directions: Mix 1/3 cup butter with confectioners sugar.
Mix in flour and press mixture into bottom of an ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Put cocoa and hot milk together.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, mix the ingredients and place the mixture in a pudding pan.
Put the pudding pan in a pan of warm water.
Bake pudding for 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: marinated morsels
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except turkey and shrimp.
Pour the mixture over the turkey and shrimp.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Drain.
Serve with wild rice.
Garnish with almonds and artichoke hearts.

title: peg's potato salad
directions: Cook, cool and peel potatoes.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Place in large bowl.
Combine vinegar, sugar, water and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Set aside.
Mix flour and 1/4 cup water.
Stir into vinegar mixture and simmer until thick.
Toss sauteed onion and fried bacon (crumbled) with potatoes.
Toss with cooked dressing.
Serve hot or cold.

title: wassail
directions: Mix all together in large crock-pot (5-quart), starting with juices.
You can add slices of orange to float on top.
Heat to simmer at low for an hour or two.
Keep warm to drink.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Mix beef, applesauce, Minute rice, onion, salt and pepper; shape into balls.
Place 1 layer deep in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix catsup and water; pour over meatballs.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: chili
directions: Heat oil and brown beef and set aside.
Puree onion soup in blender and pour over beef.
Stir in spices.
Add beans, tomato paste and sauce. Stir until well combined. Heat over low heat at least 20 minutes until piping hot and flavors have blended. Serves 4 to 6.

title: quick chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk, cocoa and shortening to boil.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal. Drop by tablespoon on wax paper.
Ready to serve in 15 to 30 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen cookies.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Place each breast between 2 pieces of clear plastic wrap. Working from the center to the edges, pound with flat side of meat mallet to 1/4-inch thickness.
Remove plastic wrap.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Mix all together and cook until the desired thickness.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in casserole and brown in oven at 375°. For the first hour, cover with lid or tinfoil; the last 1/2 hour, remove cover. Serves 6.

title: crispy crust chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken; remove skin and bones.
Cut up and place in 13 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix broth and celery soup and pour over chicken.
Stir in frozen vegetables (thaw).
Combine margarine, pepper, flour, baking powder and milk and pour over all.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown at 375°.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: *Optional:
Add any color of peppers (yellow banana peppers, overripe ones are orange).
Just chop up a few and add.

title: 24-hour fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding with juice until thick and add pudding dressing to fruit after cooling.
Make sure fruit is well drained and add bananas just before serving.

title: leeks with french gravy
directions: Remove outer parts of leeks. Wash well and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Cover with water, add salt and simmer 20 to 30 minutes until tender.
Make French gravy by combining butter and flour, mixing well but do not cook.
Add some of the leek broth to this mixture, stirring until smooth.
Add this to the leeks and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve with boiled potatoes.

title: goop melange
directions: Dice onion and fry with ground chuck.
Drain.
Cook the macaroni until tender; drain.
Combine package of cheese from box of macaroni and cheese, tomato sauce, one can of water and sugar. Simmer 15 minutes.

title: beef and cabbage scallops
directions: Brown beef in large skillet.
When meat begins to change color, add celery and onion.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Alternate layers of meat mixture, cabbage and potatoes in a 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and butter. Cover with foil; bake for 1 hour, or until vegetables are tender.

title: italian vegetables in beer batter
directions: Let beer stand at room temperature for 45 minutes until flat. In bowl, combine flour, Parmesan, parsley,	salt, and garlic powder.
Stir in olive oil, egg yolks and flat beer.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in stiff beaten egg whites.
Dip vegetables into batter.
Fry in hot oil (about 375°) a few at a time until golden, 2 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels and serve immediately with lemon wedges.
Can be used for cocktails.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add to milk and vanilla.
Put on stove and let come to a bol, but do not boil.
Take off and add margarine.
Store in an airtight container in refrigerator and reheat as needed.
Serve over ice cream or yellow cake.

title: creamy chicken noodle soup
directions: In a 6-quart saucepot, stir together broth, 1 cup milk, carrot, celery, green pepper, onion, marjoram, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inches.
Beat all ingredients until smooth, 30 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with fresh fruit if desired.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: green salad or cole slaw dressing
directions: Put in jar and shake well.
Add 1 teaspoon poppy seed.

title: oil pastry
directions: In a mixing bowl stir together flour and salt.
Pour oil and milk into a measuring cup (do not stir); add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir lightly with a fork.
Form into 2 balls; flatten slightly with hands.
Cut waxed paper into four 12-inch squares. Place each ball of dough between 2 squares of paper.
Roll each ball of dough into a circle to edges of paper.
(Dampen work surface with a little water to prevent paper from slipping.)
Peel off top papers and fit dough, paper side up, into 9-inch pie plates.
(Or reserve one portion for use as a top crust.) Remove paper.
Continue as directed for pastry of single-crust pie.
This recipe makes 2 single crust or one double-crust 9-in. pie crust.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water for 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain and cool.
Peel potatoes and cut into cubes. Combine potatoes, pickles, onion, salt and pepper. Pour over potato mixture.
Combine mayo and mustard stir in well. Chill well before serving.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, milk, parsley, onion, horseradish sauce and pecans.
Spread on ham and roll up.
Chill.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: peter's chicken and rice
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Pour off fat.
Add sausage, tomatoes, water, onions, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat 40 minutes. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook 30 minutes more or until chicken is done.
Yields 8 servings.

title: adirondack sweet rolls(method:  skillet)
directions: Mix Bisquick, 1/4 cup sugar and water to make a firm dough. Pat out an inch or less thick.
Cover dough with remaining 1/4 cup sugar, cinnamon, fruit and some melted butter.
Roll into slab and slice into cylinders 3/4-inch thick.
Fry in pan greased with butter.
Mix the powdered sugar with some melted butter to make an icing; drop onto cooked sweet rolls.

title: louis' poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 5 minutes in a large bowl.
Pour into well greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake for one hour in a preheated 350° oven.
Cool for 15 minutes on cake rack; then turn onto cake plate and dust with powdered sugar.
Yummm!

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Cook cauliflower 10 minutes in boiling salted water; drain well.
Combine cauliflower with 2 tablespoons butter, onion, cheese, sour cream and salt.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole; melt remaining butter and toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: special punch
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and cinnamon in a blender container and process at a high speed for 1 minute.
Pour chilled juices and ginger ale into a 4-quart punch bowl.
Add egg spice mixture, stirring slowly. If desired, place scoops of sherbet on top of punch. Makes 12 (1 cup) servings.

title: nanny's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with jackets on in salted water.
Peel and dice potatoes, warm.
Add mayonnaise to warm potatoes; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix again.
Add more mayonnaise if needed.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together and pour into prepared pan. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: toll house cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Line with waxed paper; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, brown sugar and sugar; beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla extract and salt; mix well.
Gradually add flour.
Stir in 1 cup chocolate.
Spread batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Combine first four ingredients and cocoa (if using).
Beat egg yolks into milk.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Cook over slow fire until thick.
If using chocolate squares, break into pieces and add to cooked mixture, stirring until melted.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: lemon butter cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 3 cups flour, baking powder and extract.
Cover fruit and nuts with 1 cup flour.
Add to mix.
Line pan with greased brown paper.
Pour batter into pan and let set overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Raise heat to 350° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: blanche's chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and butter together until smooth.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Mix together baking powder, salt and flour.
Add a little milk and flour alternately to the egg mixture until all is used up.
Stir well.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix beef, egg, salt and black pepper together; add bread crumbs. Place in bottom of baking dish. Chop onion. Spread over meat. Spread mushroom soup over this. Spread sliced cheese over this. Top cheese with Tater Tots. Cook 1 hour at 300°.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Cream together oleo, oil, sugar, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, cocoa and baking soda.
Add the sifted mixture to the first mixture, blending well with a wooden spoon.
Add the zucchini and mix well.
Grease, but do not flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread coconut on bottom of pan.
Pour batter over coconut.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: italian zucchini
directions: Chop zucchini in moderately large chunks; chop onions.
Saute in olive oil.
Add tomatoes and simmer until done.

title: grandma shelton's fried pies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut
in shortening.
Add ice water and knead
well.
Break
off
small
pieces of dough about the size of an
egg and roll on well floured board.
Place filling in middle of
pastry.
Dampen
edge of pastry.
Fold over and seal edges. Trim
to
shape.
Fry
in shortening until brown. These can also be
baked
in
oven
at
375° for about 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Mama was "famous" for her fried apple pies for many years!

title: tomatoes(how to can)
directions: You will need sterilized jars.

title: mexican tortilla casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
While browning hamburger, mix soups and sauce.
Add hamburger and mix.
Grate cheese.
Place tortillas, torn in fourths, in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add a layer of hamburger mixture, then a layer of cheese.
Repeat tortillas, hamburger and cheese.
Bake about 30 minutes at 375°.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Cut in oleo.
Add egg, orange peel and juice, all at once.
Stir until mixture is evenly moist.
Fold in raisins and cranberries.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: walnut cheese sticks
directions: Blend cottage cheese and 1/2 pound butter with a fork.
Add flour and blend until dough holds together.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Spread dough with melted butter, then sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Cut into triangles 3-inches wide at base.
Beginning at base, roll dough into sticks. Place point side down onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Mix ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour.
After chilling, make 2 dozen 1-inch balls and put 1 in each muffin.
Press around to form shell.

title: flavored rice
directions: Place water in 3-quart Tupperware casserole and microwave to boiling.
Add rice and cover.
Microwave on High 10 to 12 minutes. This is a great side dish with many entrees cooked in the bottom of the stack cooker.

title: cheese cake bars
directions: Mix cake mix, oleo, 1 egg and nuts together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs; mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: mincemeat
directions: Boil and grind the beef.
Peel, core and grind apples. Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 1 hour.
Ladle into hot, clean jars.
Seal.
Process 1/2 hour in boiling water bath.
Let stand 6 to 8 weeks before using.

title: fudge cookies(made on top of stove.)
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients 2 minutes in saucepan.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Spoon onto waxed paper and let harden.

title: chicken and pastry
directions: Cover skinned fryer with water.
Add chicken broth.
Cook or boil for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove chicken, bone and cut into serving pieces.
Strain broth.

title: great red potatoes
directions: Boil potato chunks (don't peel); drain.
Place 1/2 potatoes in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with 1/2 of Italian dressing packet.
Repeat with another layer of potatoes, butter and mix.
Marinate 1 hour to overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Good warmed up!

title: tea cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients; roll into balls.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken in the water until tender (20 to 25 minutes). Remove meat and cut into strips; sprinkle with lemon juice, salt and pepper and toss, then set aside.
Add soup mix and rice to 2 cups of broth in which the chicken was cooked.
Cover and bring to a boil; remove from heat and let stand until all the broth is absorbed (15 to 20 minutes).
Stir to fluff.
Chop celery, onion and drained pineapple.
Blend curry and mustard into mayonnaise and sour cream.
Put all ingredients together; blend thoroughly. Cover and chill thoroughly.
Better if made the day before.

title: taco salad
directions: Crumble ground beef in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Add onions. Microwave at High for 4 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes, or until meat loses its pink color, stirring to break up meat after half the cooking time. Drain.
Stir in beans, water and taco seasoning.
Microwave, uncovered, at Medium for 10 to 13 minutes, or until thick and bubbly (stir once).
Combine lettuce, tomatoes and green peppers in salad bowl with meat and beans.
Spoon mixture over lettuce. Top with cheese, then corn chips.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Stir together flour,
baking
powder,
baking
soda and salt in a medium bowl.
Stir
together buttermilk and oil then pour over flour mixture and mix well.
Knead dough gently on a lightly floured surface 10 to
12 times.
Roll or pat dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter, dipping cutter in flour between cuts,
and
put on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for
to
minutes or until golden. Serve warm. Makes 8 biscuits.

title: corn pudding(from 1975 edition)
directions: In a bowl, beat egg and milk until well blended.
Add broken saltines and mix well.
Add sugar and corn and stir until blended. Pour into greased baking dish.
Dot top with butter.
Bake in heated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: second night steak
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Add mushrooms and chipped meat. Sprinkle gravy mix over your meat and add water.
Stir well.
(You can make your own gravy, if you prefer.)
Bring to a boil and reduce to lowest heat.
Simmer about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: old fashion chestnut dressing
directions: Melt butter in a skillet and saute sausage meat and onion. Add water or broth, seasonings and bread crumbs.
Stir in chestnuts.

title: grandpa's barbecue sauce
directions: Cook over low heat, stir occasionally.

title: coriander cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Sift together flour, coriander, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Blend into creamed mixture and add water; beat well. Drop from spoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
These are real good!

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Cook pineapple, sugar and flour until thick; cool.
Slice bananas and place in bottom of crusts.
Sprinkle nuts over bananas and pour pineapple mixture over nuts.
Whip the cream and stir in coconut.
Spread over pies and chill at least 2 hours.

title: beef and tortellini soup
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven over high heat cook ground beef, stirring frequently until all pan juices evaporated and beef is well browned, about 10 minutes.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add tomatoes with puree, undiluted French onion soup, frozen green beans, tortellini, basil and 3 1/2 cups water.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add zucchini and cook uncovered 10 minutes until tender.

title: apple crisp
directions: Fill 9 x 13-inch pan full of fresh, sliced apples.
Mix remainder of ingredients into crumbles.
Sprinkle over top of apples. Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Serve hot or cold. Whipped cream can also be added.

title: round-up taco dip
directions: Combine sour cream with taco seasoning.
Layer with shredded lettuce, tomatoes, green onions and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cream cheese pastry
directions: Roll out one package crescent rolls to make rectangle in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cheese, sugar, egg yolk, vanilla and lemon juice.
Spread this mixture over rolls.
Top with next package of crescent rolls.
Using fork, mix egg white with 1 tablespoon water.
Spread this over top of rolls.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: shrimp and cheese spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese.
Add tomatoes and drained sausage.
Serve with chips.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Add
spices
to
water.
Heat to boil.
Add tea.
Steam for
5 minutes; strain.
Heat juices and sugar just to boiling point. Stir and add to hot tea.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: overnight caramel pecan cinnamon rolls
directions: Cut each thawed bread loaf into 8 slices.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts in small bowl.
Dip each slice of dough into melted butter; coat with cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Stand each slice upright in greased 12-cup Bundt pan.
Sprinkle any remaining cinnamon mixture over rolls; sprinkle with dry pudding mix.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops and season with salt and pepper. When brown on both sides, place in baking dish.
Pour soup over chops.
Bake in 375° preheated oven for about 45 minutes.

title: milky way cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine candy bars and 1 cup oleo in top of double boiler.
Melt over hot (not boiling) water.
Set aside to cool.
Cream sugar and 1 cup oleo until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add to mixture alternately with flour beginning and ending with flour.
Add candy mixture and nuts.
Mix it until well blended.
Pour into 4 (8 or 9-inch) cake pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: wealthy chocolate
directions: Crust:
Combine cookie crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and melted butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat firmly and bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Let cool.

title: crab and avocado salad
directions: Halve the avocados.
Discard the seed; scoop out the flesh, leaving 1/2 inch of flesh as a shell in the avocado skin.
Slice the scooped out flesh.
Combine the mayonnaise with the catsup; add the crabmeat, tossing to coat it.
Add the eggs and sliced avocado; mix well.
Heap into the scooped out shells.

title: strawberry german pie
directions: Mix together all but
last two ingredients and put in a pie pan.
Bake at 350°	until
light
brown.
Let
cool 4 to 5 hours. Mix Cool Whip and drained strawberries and spread over pie.
Store in refrigerator.

title: bon-bons
directions: Put nuts in large mixing bowl. Melt butter and pour over nuts. Add coconut, milk and sugar, mix well. Roll into balls, refrigerate. Melt paraffin and chocolate chips together in top of double boiler. Using toothpick in each chilled ball, dip into chocolate mixture. Place on wax paper to harden.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well all of the ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
(Or place foil on the cookie sheet and bake cookies on foil.)
Bake at 325° until brown.
Slide off cookie sheet very gently as cookies are tender.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder. Into standard measuring cup, break the egg.
Beat lightly and fill the cup with milk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Beat a little.
Let stand to rise 5 minutes.
Drop batter by tablespoons on top of boiling stew meat or chicken. Cover and boil for 20 minutes.

title: cheese shrimp puffs
directions: Microwave Directions:
Arrange crackers on 2 napkin-lined plates.
In medium microwave-safe bowl, microwave butter on High for 10 seconds to soften.
Add cheese; blend well.
Stir in egg yolk and shrimp.
Beat egg white until stiff peaks form.
Fold into cheese-shrimp mixture.
Top each cracker with spoonful of mixture. Microwave 1 plate at a time on High for 1 minute.
Makes 32 snacks.

title: wild rice and mushroom dish
directions: Cook the rice and drain.
Brown sausage, add butter, mushrooms, onions, celery, bell pepper and parsley.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir the rice into the sausage mixture. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Excellent with charbroiled steaks and a crisp green salad.

title: south texas style quail
directions: Dust quail with combined salt, pepper and flour.
Place in skillet of hot deep fat; cover and brown on both sides, turning only once.
Pour off grease and add cream and cook over low heat until tender.
Thicken gravy.
Serve with hot biscuits.

title: walnut-cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over hot water; set aside to cool.
Cream the butter; slowly add sugar.
Beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir chocolate into mixture.
Add flour, salt, walnuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla, stirring well.
Pour batter into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured baking pan; set aside.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal. Let stand 20 minutes.
Cream the butter and sugars.
Add remaining ingredients plus oatmeal. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in 1 cup boiling salted water in saucepan for 3 minutes, stirring to break apart; drain.
Combine egg, cheese, mayonnaise and soup in bowl; mix well.
Mix in broccoli.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lucky to have any left
directions: Combine flour, butter and pecans in bowl; mix well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cream sugar and cream cheese in bowl with mixer until light and fluffy.
Fold in 16 ounce Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled layer.
Combine pudding mix and milk in mixer bowl until thickened.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Chill several hours.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish and top with 1 package Ritz crackers (crumbled). Dot with 1 stick margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: justine's scallop-shrimp dish
directions: Line a 13 x 9-inch dish with the crackers (save enough for topping).
Boil shrimp 3 minutes until just pink.
Cut scallops into quarters.
Mix soup with mayonnaise.
Mix all together.
Pour into dish lined with crushed crackers. Sprinkle top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ma king's tea cakes
directions: Mix all together, then	take small portion of dough and roll thin,
and cut
in	little	circles.
A
little
coconut sprinkled on top before baking
is
good
if desired.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Don't overcook.

title: easy barbecue chicken
directions: *You can use other parts of chicken if you want to.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Saute
pork
chops,
carrots,
broccoli, peas and green onion in margarine
in a large skillet 3 to 4 minutes or until pork is cooked.
Remove
from
skillet,
and set aside.
Cook rice in skillet
until thoroughly heated.
Push rice to sides of skillet, forming
a
well in center.
Pour eggs into well, and cook
until set,
stirring
occasionally.
Stir rice into eggs;
add
the vegetables and remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit salad or pie
directions: Mix the fruit cocktail, juice and all, with pudding.
When well blended, add Cool Whip.
Either refrigerate as is or spoon into a prepared graham cracker crust for a quick and easy pie.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add bananas and flour thoroughly.
Add nuts. Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in the water.
Add fruit juices and the lemon juice to sugar water.
When ready to serve, add the 7-Up slowly.

title: chicken curry
directions: Remove the skin from the chicken and clean very well.
Slice onion and saute in 1/4 cup vegetable oil to a golden brown.
Add ginger and garlic paste and chicken pieces.
Stir a while and then add chili powder, salt and water.
Cook in low-medium heat with cover on it.
Let it cook for a few minutes (10 to 15 minutes). Add chopped tomatoes.
Now, cook in low heat for 10 minutes more.

title: carrot salad (diabetic)
directions: Cook carrots in salted water until tender.
Combine soup, vinegar, oil and sweetener; heat to boiling and simmer until oil blends.
Add pineapple, green pepper and onion to soup mixture. Pour over carrots; mix.
Serve hot or cold.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin honey wheat bread
directions: Combine flour, wheat germ, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and baking soda in large bowl.
Combine eggs, pumpkin, honey, vegetable oil and milk in medium bowl.
Add to flour mixture. Stir just until blended.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Put rhubarb in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle jello and sugar over it.
Put marshmallows on top.
Mix cake mix as directed on package and spread on top.
Bake at 375° until brown and firm in center.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Saute chicken breasts in Crisco until lightly browned.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Saute onion in oleo over medium heat until clear, but not brown.
Mix soup, wine, water, rosemary, salt and pepper with onion until well blended.

title: valentine punch
directions: Mix water and sugar with Kool-Aid according to package directions.
Then add orange drink, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Mix together well.
Chill overnight in refrigerator, if possible.
Serve in punch bowl with fresh strawberries for garnish.

title: brandied fruit
directions: Drain 1 can of pitted tart cherries well.
Put in a clean large jar and add 1 cup sugar.
Stir well.
Cover and let stand at room temperature 2 weeks.
Stir every other night.
Add 1 cup drained pineapple and 1 cup sugar.
Stir every other night for 2 weeks.
Add 1 can drained peaches and 1 cup sugar.
Stir every other night for 2 weeks.
Ready to eat.
Keep adding drained fruit with 1 cup sugar about every 2 weeks.
Use maraschino cherries the second time around to keep fruit a pretty color.
Stir with wooden spoon.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together except for 1/2 cup pecans.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: rhubarb custard
directions: Cream the eggs, sugar, butter, flour and milk; pour over rhubarb.
Bake in a 400° oven for 50 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Grease a 2 quart round baking dish. Set the pie crust out. Heat the butter in a large saute pan over medium high heat. Add onions and celery, season with salt and pepper and cook, stirring for 2 minutes. Stir in flour and cook, stirring, for 3 to 4 minutes to make a blond roux. Stir in the chicken broth and bring the liquid to a boil. Reduce the heat to medium low and simmer until the sauce begins to thicken, 4 to 6 minutes. Stir in potatoes, carrots, peas, chicken and parsley. Season with salt and pepper and mix well.

title: artichoke spinach dip(similar to darryl's)
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cheddar cheese.
Heat to bubbling. Sprinkle with Cheddar.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mock hollandaise sauce(low-fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl, stirring until well blended.

title: *yogurt cake
directions: Mix ingredients until blended. Grease lightly a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool and cut into diamond shape.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar and cornstarch and add to water.
Cook until clear.
Add jello and cool.
Add strawberries.
Put filling in a baked pie crust.
Chill.
May be topped with whipped cream.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift flour and baking powder into bowl. Cut in butter and cheese as for pie crust using pastry cutter. Add water and mix well. Use pastry press with star shape and form into 1 inch strips on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 375° for 8-10 minutes. Yield 48-60 one inch straws.

title: lemon barbecue pork chops
directions: In a skillet, brown chops on both sides in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil.
Drain grease.
Mix the water and catsup and put on chops.
Sprinkle with red pepper flakes.
Put sliced lemons on top of chops.
Cover and simmer, about 35 to 45 minutes until done.

title: silver fish adobo
directions: Defrost silver fish, wash and drain very well.
Put in deep cooking pan.
Add tomato, onion, ginger root, cooking oil, soy sauce and Sinigang mix.
Turn over lightly with wooden spoon to mix ingredients.
Cook over moderate heat for about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and serve.
Best eaten over hot steamed rice.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan; set aside.
Cream butter and cream cheese; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed, until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour and salt, stirring until combined.
Stir in vanilla and remaining 1 cup pecans.
Pour batter in pan.
Bake at 325°for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Start cake in cold oven.

title: dressing for fruit salad
directions: Beat until sugar is thoroughly dissolved and mixture is syrupy.

title: flan
directions: Allow cheese to soften at room temperature, then beat until fluffy.
Add 1 egg at a time to cheese; beat well after each addition.
Combine evaporated milk and condensed milk with sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add to cheese mix.
Beat well.
Carmelize sugar; sprinkle with water in pan.
Place in shallow pan; pour cheese mixture on top of carmelized sugar.
Place pan in a pan of water.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Enjoy!
Cool and turn over into a serving dish.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spread croutons on bottom of cake pan.
Top with cooked sausage and then 3/4 cup cheese.
Mix eggs, soup, milk, onions and green peppers.
Pour over croutons, sausage and cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes. (Refrigerate overnight and cook next morning.)

title: "mom's" butter cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg thoroughly.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour and baking powder.
Chill dough.
Roll lightly on floured board.
Cut into shapes (use cookie cutters). Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until delicately browned in hot oven (425°).
Bake 5 to 7 minutes; watch, the cookies will burn easily.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the stuffing.
Place in a large Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until brown on top.
Press topping down with fork when half done.

title: berry-mandarin tossed salad
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients. Microwave, uncovered, on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Stir until sugar dissolves. Whisk in vegetable oil. Cover and refrigerate until serving.

title: hash brown scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°. Ham can be added.

title: "oh boy" waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Combine eggs, milk and shortening. Combine liquid and dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth just before baking.
This is a thin batter.
Bake in hot waffle iron.
Makes about 10 waffles.

title: spinach casserole(you'll never know it's spinach.)
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package.
Drain well, saving liquid.

Melt butter over low heat. Add flour, stirring until blended and smooth. Add onion and cook until soft (but not brown). Add liquid slowly, stirring constantly, to avoid lumps. Cook until smooth and thick.
Add seasoning and cheese which has been cut in small pieces. Stir until blended.
Combine with cooked spinach.
Put in casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter. Cook 30 minutes at 350°.
You can make the night before serving or it freezes well.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Coat pork chops with Shake 'n
Bake;
put
in
pan
and bake about 45 minutes at 350°.
Turn
pork
chops over and top with sliced onion and pour gravy or broth over top.
Cover and continue baking for 1 hour or until tender.

title: apple pie (deep dish)
directions: Combine ingredients, except butter and lemon juice, and let stand
while preparing pastry.
Line deep
pie
pan
with pastry; add filling, dot with butter and drop lemon juice over top of pie. Cover with top crust.
Bake for
35 to 45 minutes at 425°.

title: salsa cruda(fresh tomato sauce)
directions: To peel tomatoes, dip them in boiling water for 30 seconds. Plunge into cold water.
Slip skins off.
Chop tomatoes.
Combine chopped tomatoes with onion, olive or cooking oil, green chili peppers, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Cover; refrigerate several hours or overnight, stirring occasionally.
Serve as a relish. Makes about 3 cups.

title: tomato cakes
directions: Mash whole
tomatoes in bowl;
add eggs, crackers, salt and pepper to
taste,
and
sugar.
May
need more crackers to make mixture
just
stiff
enough to hold together like salmon cakes. Fry until
golden on each side.
A different dish with bacon or ham for breakfast or lunch.

title: eggs with crabmeat
directions: Beat the egg yolk with 1/2 cup milk.
Chop the ham and onions. Heat the oil in a saucepan and saute the ham and onions over a low heat until the onions are transparent.
Stir in the flour and the remaining 2 cups of milk.
Add the crabmeat and salt and pepper to taste.
Very slowly, pour in the egg yolk mixture and the sherry.
Beat the egg white until stiff and gently fold into the crabmeat mixture.
Pour the entire mixture into a well buttered dish and bake in a 350° oven for about an hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk until it thickens.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Layer in a large dish beginning with vanilla wafers, sliced bananas, pudding and repeat.
Refrigerate.

title: curried chicken cheese balls
directions: Ham and Swiss:
Thinly sliced ham and Swiss cheese slices, garnished with Dijon mustard.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken and slice into thin strips.
Trim green onions and slice thin.
Slice carrots thin.
Dice green pepper.
Saute chicken quickly in vegetable oil until it turns white.
Stir in green onions, pepper and carrots.
Saute 2 minutes.
Stir in soy sauce; cover and cook about 3 minutes until vegetables are crispy tender.
Blend cornstarch into chicken broth until smooth.
Stir into meat and vegetable mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly until sauce thickens and boils, about 3 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Place in bottom of deep dish pie pan. Pour salsa on top.
Place chopped red and green pepper on top of salsa and then shred cheese and put on top of peppers.
Serve with nachos

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel apples.
Slice in a glass pie plate.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon together.
Sprinkle over apple slices.
Mix the rest of the ingredients together; pour over apples.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Be sure macaroni has been rinsed with cold water and is completely cooled. Mix with remaining ingredients. Keep refrigerated. Will keep for several days.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs, milk and flour, then add vanilla and lemon.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Do not open oven while cooking.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add cake mix and flour. (You may need more flour to handle dough.)
Knead dough; let rise to double in bulk.
Knead and make into cinnamon rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: walnut spice kisses
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon, and nutmeg; set aside.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature).
Add salt at high speed of electric mixer for one minute.
Gradually add sugar mixture, 1 tablespoon at a time beating until stiff peak forms.
Fold in walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Pull biscuit layers apart (10 biscuits make 20 pieces or dumplings).
Stretch each layer of biscuit over your fingers, place an apple wedge on it.
Sprinkle with cinnamon; fold over and seal.
Place in pan.
Let water, sugar and margarine come to a boil.
Pour over dumplings and bake at 350° until golden and apples are tender.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain off fat.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low for 6 to 9 hours or on high for 3 hours.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion in 2 tablespoons oleo.
Drain Veg-All.
Mix Veg-All, Cheez Whiz and onion in baking dish.
Melt oleo.
Crumble crackers and toss in melted oleo to coat.
Sprinkle on top of Veg-All mixture.
Bake at 350° until mixture begins to bubble and brown.

title: party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in large shallow pan over low heat.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and seasoned salt.
Add ingredients and mix over low heat until all the pieces are coated. Heat in the oven for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes. Spread out on paper towels to cool.
Pour into bowl and serve.

title: sauteed chicken in cream sauce
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Melt margarine in large skillet; add chicken, vegetables and seasonings.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Add 2 tablespoons wine.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: bohemian coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients together as given.
Bake in tube pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: sea foam
directions: Beat egg whites and salt together until stiff.
Cook sugar, water or water & syrup mixture along with vinegar over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Then cook quickly until hard ball stage, 238 degrees.
Pour syrup mixture over eggs in a thin stream. Beat constantly until thick and creamy.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a square baking dish (cake pan), layer the lettuce, green onions, green pepper, celery, peas, bacon bits (save 2 tablespoons) and cheese (save 1/4 cup.)

title: apple taffy salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice, egg, sugar, vinegar and flour.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Cool.
Toss pineapple and apples together.
Add cooled custard and Cool Whip.
Add peanuts last. Sprinkle finely chopped peanuts on top, if desired.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in water until tender.
Drain.
Melt Velveeta and butter together.
Mix with carrots.
Pour into casserole dish. Sprinkle crumbled Ritz crackers or saltines over top.
Bake at 350° until bubbles.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Place all beans in a crock-pot; brown ground round and put into crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onion together; put into crock-pot.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Cook for 2 to 3 hours on low heat.

title: cherry macaroon cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, salt, egg and vanilla together.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts and cherries.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam or lightly oiled.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: butterscotch fingers
directions: Melt butter in pan.
After this, add rest of ingredients and put into a well-greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: cream fluff
directions: Arrange cake pieces in buttered 9-inch cake pan or large bowl.
Dissolve jello in boiling water; stir in strawberries. Whip cream and fold into jello mixture.
Pour over cake pieces and refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours or until set.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown and drain hamburger. Add rest of ingredients. Simmer for 1 hour, stirring often.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef in medium saucepan. Season with salt and pepper. Drain. Mix all remaining ingredients in with meat and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring often. Serve over fresh pasta.

title: bacardi rum cake
directions: Preheat
oven to 325°.	Grease and flour a 10-inch tube or 12-cup
Bundt
pan.
Sprinkle nuts over bottom of pan.
Mix all cake
ingredients together; pour batter over nuts in pan. Bake for 1	hour.
Set
on	rack
to cool.	Invert on serving plate. Prick
top;
drizzle
and
brush glaze evenly over top and sides.

title: christmas fruit bowl
directions: Do not peel apples.
Dice apples, cut oranges into small pieces and slice bananas.
Combine pineapple juice, juice of lemon and desired amount of sugar into saucepan.
Add cornstarch to thicken. Cook until clear.
Cool.
Add to fruit, mix well.
Continue to chill.
Serve in champagne glasses.
Top with cherries and sprig of mint or holly leaves.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Pour pineapple in casserole. Save juice. Mix sugar and flour. Sprinkle over pineapple. Pour juice over mixture. Sprinkle cheese over mixture. Mix crackers and butter. Spread over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugar, salad oil and eggs.
Sift and measure flour; sift with salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder and stir into creamed mixture, blending well.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured large loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 large loaves.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients except almonds.
Place mixture in buttered
x 12-inch casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight. Remove
one hour before baking.
Place almonds on top and bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Layer in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish half the hamburger, half noodles, half of both cheeses and 1 can sauce; repeat layers. Cover and bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana split sundae pie
directions: In 9-inch pie plate, melt oleo; add wafer crumbs until mixed well.
Press on bottom and up sides of pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: watermelon slices
directions: Line 1 1/2-quart bowl with plastic wrap.
Mix 1/2 of the whipped topping with food coloring in another large bowl until well blended.
Spread on bottom and up sides of prepared bowl. Freeze 30 minutes or until firm.

title: dora's favorite fruit salad
directions: Blend eggs, pineapple juice, sugar, flour and vinegar until smooth.
Cook over medium heat until sauce thickens and remove from
heat.
In large bowl, blend all fruits and nuts. Pour egg sauce over fruit and nut mixture and blend well.
Chill and serve. Serves 4.

title: donegal potatoes
directions: In a large (10 to 12-inch) frypan, heat olive oil.
In the heated oil, saute onion and green pepper until onion is transparent, but not brown.
Remove onion and pepper from pan and keep warm.

title: ora wubbels' kielbasa pie
directions: Thaw spinach and place in a large bowl.
Add eggs, kielbasa and cheese.
Mix thoroughly and distribute evenly in the two pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hawaiian beans
directions: Drain three bean salad, and then add all other ingredients mixing them in 10-inch Dutch oven. Heat for 30 minutes.

title: banana split pudding
directions: Line pan with graham cracker crumbs.
Next 1 layer of bananas sliced.
Mix 2 cans of Eagle Brand with 2/3 cup lemon juice then pour over bananas.
Next 1 layer of crushed pineapple drained. One layer of crushed nuts.
One layer of Cool Whip.
Top with maraschino cherries.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken and break into small pieces; put in pan.
Mix together soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Add Stove Top dressing (dry). Sprinkle about a teaspoon of the spices on top of dry stuffing. Pour chicken broth over entire mixture and bake about 45 minutes.

title: christmas filled cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs.
Beat well.
Put 3 cups oatmeal through grinder.
Combine this with other 3 cups.
Sift flour, soda and salt together; add this to the creamed mixture. Add all oatmeal and hot water to this.
Mix well.
Chill dough 30 minutes.

title: tortellini soup
directions: In saucepan over medium-high heat, cook garlic and margarine for 3 minutes.
Add broth and tortellini.
Heat to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Add spinach and tomatoes.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve topped with Parmesan cheese.

title: pineapple chiffon pie
directions: Bring the pineapple and sugar to a good, rolling boil.
Take from heat.
Add the lemon Jell-O and salt.
Let cool until jelled. Let milk (in can) chill while the Jell-O mixture is cooling. When Jell-O is beginning to set, whip the can of milk.
Fold into Jell-O mixture.

title: jack-o-lantern tea cakes(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
Stir the Bisquick baking mix, sugar, butter and milk into a soft dough.
Gently smooth the dough into a ball and place on a floured, cloth-covered board.
Knead 8 to 10 times.
Roll the dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cut this with a floured 2-inch cutter.
Form rounds into pumpkin shapes, using extra dough for the stems.
Bake these on an ungreased baking sheet for 6 minutes.
Let them cool and then frost with Orange Frosting. Decorate with licorice and candies to resemble jack-o-lanterns.

title: low-fat chocolate berry-crunch parfait
directions: In a medium-size bowl, combine the raspberries with 1 tablespoon of the sugar and set aside.
In another medium-size bowl, combine the yogurt, cocoa powder and remaining 1 tablespoon sugar, whisking until smooth and creamy.
Spoon 1/4 cup of the raspberries into 4 (8-ounce) parfait glasses, then sprinkle with 1/2 teaspoon of the wheat germ.
Make 3 more layers, ending with the yogurt.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before serving.
Garnish with mint sprigs and/or Lite Cool Whip

title: banana split crumb cake
directions: Mix together and press into pan for crust.
Reserve some for topping.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: dried beef log
directions: Chop with knife the dried beef and put on wax paper.
Mix in a bowl the cream cheese, margarine, onion salt, garlic and chopped green onions.
Mix all together and shape into long log.
Roll log in dried beef and then put in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Spread on Ritz crackers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Add all ingredients at once and stir until well blended.
Pour into baking loaf pan that has been Pam-sprayed.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: chinese meatballs
directions: Fry onions until light golden brown.
Beat eggs with milk or water.
Combine beef, onions, chili sauce, soy sauce, salt, pepper, chopped water chestnuts, eggs and crushed chow mein noodles.
Mix until well blended.
Fry balls in 1-inch of oil or broil in oven, turning once.
Make balls in shape of small walnut.

title: tuna mousse
directions: Heat soup without water.
Add gelatin until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Turn into a well-greased mold and refrigerate.

title: date cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs. Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Mix the dates, water, sugar and nuts together.
Cook until dates are soft. Cool and either mix in dough or use for filling.

title: easy 3 day coconut cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix and add dream whip.
Bake cake and let cool and split into 4 thin layers.

title: canning string beans
directions: Stem, cut and wash beans.
Blanch beans and pack in jars (real full).
Add salt and lemon juice.
Do not add water.
Cook in pressure cooker with 10 pounds pressure for 30 minutes.
When ready to use, a cheese sauce may be added or brown butter in a saucepan and add onion, bologna pieces or bacon.
Then add beans and simmer 5 minutes.

title: western hash
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add canned tomatoes, green pepper, onion, rice, salt, basil and pepper.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese and heat until melted.

title: chinese egg rolls
directions: Finely chop first 5 ingredients.
Drain bean sprouts.
Combine chopped ingredients, bean sprouts and the next 5 ingredients in a bowl.
Chill.
Prepare batter for egg rolls.
In a mixing bowl, sift together flour, cornstarch and salt.
Combine 2 beaten eggs and water; gradually blend into dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Reserve 1/2 cup batter for sealing egg rolls.
Pour about 2 tablespoons batter into crepe pan.

title: caesar salad
directions: In a jar with a lid, combine the oil, lemon juice, mustard and garlic; shake well.
In a salad bowl, combine the romaine lettuce, croutons, parmesan cheese and pepper.
Drizzle with dressing and toss to coat.

title: my apple pie
directions: Mix apples, sugar, cinnamon, season, flour, cornstarch and water.
Place apples in pie crust, placing slices of butter inside throughout.
Place top crust on top, cut vents.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to an hour.
Tastes great with a scoop of vanilla ice cream!

title: chicken-mushroom a la king
directions: Heat soup.
Stir in remaining ingredients; except chow mein noodles.
Heat until desired temperature.
Serve over chow mein noodles.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: pizza steak
directions: Take steaks, wash them, mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Dip steaks in milk and eggs.
Cover with Italian bread crumbs.
Brown steaks in iron skillet on medium heat until crisp.
Remove from skillet.
Place in baking dish and cover with sauce.
Place aluminum foil over baking dish.
Bake on 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Remove foil and cover with cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Place broccoli florets and grapes in bowl.
Add sunflower nut meats and onion.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour dressing over broccoli mixture.
Let set a couple of hours before serving.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients, then all the dry ones.
Last the chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: m&m cookies or macadamia nut cookies
directions: Blend shortening and both sugars in a large bowl.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in M&M's.
Roll in balls.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: mom's coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, milk and salt; cook to a boil. Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolk (beaten).
Return to hot mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, 2 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with small amount of water.
Add to hot mixture gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook until desired thickness. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and 1 cup coconut.
Pour into pastry shell and top with meringue.

title: aunt jan's egg foo yong and sauce
directions: Melt 6 tablespoons shortening in pan.
Add onions and cook 3 minutes.
Add meat and cook until done.
Remove from heat and add can of sprouts, eggs, 3 tablespoons water and salt.
Fry like a thin omelet.
Fry on one side, then turn like a pancake and brown other side.

title: nannie's chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Pour 1/4 cup of milk in a measuring cup and beat in egg yolks.
Clean measuring cup with remaining milk. Cook on medium heat until mixture thickens (full boil).
Add butter and cool a little.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.
Add meringue.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, powdered sugar and frozen orange juice together.
Add butter and pecans.
Form into balls and roll in coconut.
Refrigerate in a sealed container until ready to serve. Coconut may be tinted for various occasions.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: Bake 8 or 9 minutes at 375°.

title: dolores pecan pie
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and flour.
Cream until fluffy.
Add both syrups and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Fold in pecans and vanilla. Pour into shell.
Place in bottom of 350° (preheated) oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until puffed and golden brown.

title: cumin rice
directions: In heavy saucepan, brown rice in bacon drippings until golden. Add remaining ingredients,; stir well and heat until boiling. Cover tightly, reduce heat to simmer and cook until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender (about 20 to 30 minutes). Serves six.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Melt chocolate chips with water in double boiler.
Stir in egg yolks
and
salt.	Stir
egg
whites until stiff.	Add sugar to egg
whites.
Stir	egg
whites
into cool chocolate mixture. Break
cake
into
bite
size
chunks in 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Cover cake with sauce.
Cool for 6 hours.
Serve with ice cream.

title: aunt emma's spicy swiss steak
directions: Pound flour into meat using meat hammer or the edge of a heavy saucer.
Brown in oil in large skillet. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, salt and soda; blend well.
Stir in shortening; add sour cream, corn and eggs.
Mix well.
Spoon half of batter into greased heated 8 to
9-inch heavy skillet. Sprinkle with cheese and chilies; cover with remaining corn bread mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Bake at 350° on 2 cookie sheets.
Roll up like a jelly roll.

title: date nut bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in egg.
Add flour and milk, fold in nuts and dates.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars and roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: maxcine's chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add broth with it.
Pour in casserole.
Grated cheese may be added to top, if desired.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all together.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Saute onion and pepper until tender, then add to mixture.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix
the
first
4 ingredients together, then add flour slowly.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: french omelet
directions: Mix altogether, heat butter until hot.
Pour in mixture, when it begins to thicken around edges, reduce heat.
Lift edges as it cooks, with spatula or fork.
Increase heat to brown bottom. Loosen edges and fold in half.

title: layer salad
directions: Boil peas; set aside to cool.
Fry bacon, drain and crumble. Layer 9 x 12-inch glass pan with lettuce, onion, green pepper, peas and 12 ounces mayonnaise spread.
Salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, shredded Cheddar and crumbled bacon.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Chop the shrimp into small pieces.
Soften cream cheese and add the onions, salad dressing and lemon juice.
Mix.
Add the shrimp and mix well.
Use a fork to mix with.
Serve with Fritos as this gives the dip the best flavor.

title: spareribs, quick and easy
directions: Mix together sugar, celery seed and chili powder.
Roll ribs in this mixture and top with tomato soup in baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: bacon-bread roll-ups
directions: Remove crust from sandwich loaf.
Spread mushroom soup straight from can onto halved slices of bread.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Wrap up each slice with 1/3 strip of bacon; hold with toothpicks.
Bake at 225° for 2 hours.

title: caldito
directions: Brown meat, onion and flour.
Add potatoes and cover 3/4 way full of water in skillet.
Bring to boil, reduce heat to simmer for 20 to 25 minutes until potatoes are done.
Eat with tortillas. Serves 4.

title: baked ziti with homemade italian sauce
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pizza crackers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Shake in paper bag to soak up excess oil.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: squash supreme
directions: Cook squash and mash.
Add onion, carrot, soup, salt, pepper and margarine.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Cover with Pepperidge Farm seasoned crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You may use broccoli or cauliflower.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss gently to coat. Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: old fashion apple cake
directions: Mix well the apples, cider, honey, brown sugar, buttermilk, eggs and margarine.
Add the dry ingredients, mixing well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: potato hot dish
directions: Mix all, except olives and bacon.
Put in buttered dish and top with olives and bacon.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together pineapple juice, Tang and instant pudding mixes. Pour over other ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: apple squares
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; let stand 1 hour, stirring often. Add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour large cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Dust top with powdered sugar after baking.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, melted margarine, eggs, and bananas.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
