Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: First boil and debone chicken.
Mix together chicken, soups, sour cream and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Roll mixture into tortillas and place into casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: payday cake
directions: Mix 1/3 cup margarine, cake mix and egg.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes.
Melt 1/4 cup margarine, corn syrup marshmallows, peanut butter chips and vanilla.
Pour melted mixture over cake.
Sprinkle peanuts and Rice Krispies over melted mixture.

title: sausage jambalaya(rice cooker)
directions: Layer like recipe calls for.
After bell rings on rice cooker, add 1/2 cup green onions and parsley.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover and let steam at least 30 minutes.
(Use at least 8 cups rice cooker.)

title: chunk pickles
directions: Cut pickles an inch thick (half if necessary).
Pour boiling saltwater over them. Let stand overnight.
In the morning, rinse off in cold water.
Put pickles in a kettle with weak vinegar and heat thoroughly; drain off and put in another kettle with 1 pint vinegar, celery seed, sugar, turmeric and red pepper.
Boil this a few minutes and put in jars.
Put a slice of onion on top and a pinch of powdered alum.
(I put more onion in and cut them up in the kettle with the pickles.)

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat eggs until light and add mashed ripe bananas and lemon juice.
Blend with creamed mix.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and mix quickly into mixture.
Add nuts and bake in greased loaf pan in moderate oven (350°) about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Put broth, onions, salt and pepper, potatoes and instant potatoes in pan. Stir. Cook, uncovered, on high until fork-tender. Turn to low, then add butter and half and half and stir. Simmer, covered, 30 minutes. Put soup in bowl. Top with chopped green onions, shredded Cheddar cheese and crumbled bacon.

title: date and nut loaf
directions: Measure raisins and dates together.
In a saucepan, measure water and bring to a boil.
Add baking soda and the raisins and dates.
Drain liquid and keep aside.
Mix first six ingredients together in a bowl and mix with an electric mixer until mixed well. Mixture will be lumpy.
Add the liquid from the raisin mixture and mix again.
Finally add the raisins, dates and nuts.
Place in a loaf pan which has been greased and cook for one hour at a temperature of 375°.

title: onion soup gratinee
directions: Saute onions in butter in large saucepan.
Add broth, water and pepper.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Pour soup into six 8-ounce ovenproof bowls; top with toast.
Cover with Swiss and Parmesan cheese.
Place bowls on jelly roll pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peaches 'n cream delight
directions: Melt the margarine in medium size saucepan. Add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Heat while stirring to dissolve sugar.
Remove from heat. Stir in cereal and nuts. Press into bottom of ungreased 9-inch pie pan.
Spread softened ice cream in crust.
Freeze until firm.
Before serving, top with peach filling.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crab mist dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add crab meat, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and salt.
Blend thoroughly and chill.
Serve with crackers or crudites.

title: my chili
directions: Cook hamburger and drain grease.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Cook onion, if fresh, with meat.
Add flour to meat.
Mix well. Then add water and stir.
Add cut tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, beans, onion (if not fresh), chili, garlic salt, more pepper and salt if desired.
Cook over low or medium heat, careful not to burn bottom.
Stir occasionally.
Enjoy with tortillas and grated cheese.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Cut together with 2 knives until crumbly. Take out 1/2 cup crumbs and set aside.

title: marinade for chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Marinade chicken for 2 to 3 hours.
Pierce occasionally.
Chicken should be kept in refrigerator while marinading.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole, uncovered.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add soda and baking powder, then 1 cup flour and 2 eggs.
Add remaining flour and eggs alternately, beating well after each addition.
Last, add sour cream and beat well.
Bake in oven.

title: pecan-pineapple pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and syrup, then add eggs, then pecans and then pineapple.
Pour in crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: blender cheesecake
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend 2 minutes until smooth. Pour into a greased 9-inch glass pie plate. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to one hour until set.

title: boiled okra
directions: Boil cleaned and sliced okra until tender in salted water. Drain.
Add butter and let boil for 1 minute.
Put in serving dish.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: yankee cheese roll
directions: Grind all together and knead until well mixed. Divide into 3 rolls and roll in paprika. Refrigerate. Take out and serve with crackers for uninvited guests.

title: deli hot dogs
directions: Mix and pour on mini hot dogs.
Simmer 1/2 hour or until thoroughly heated.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Slice Twinkies lengthwise and put in an 8 x 8 dish.
Mix pudding according to package directions and pour over Twinkies. Place pineapple over pudding.
Slice a layer of bananas over pineapple,
add a layer of Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts. Chill and enjoy.

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients
in heavy pan over medium heat until soft ball stage, using candy thermometer.
Add butter and powdered sugar.
Stir until it gets real thick.
Add red food coloring.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Let it harden, then break into pieces.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and add 1 cup pecans. Mix well. Refrigerate until firm and shape into ball. Roll in remaining nuts before serving. Garnish as desired. Serve with assortment of crackers. Yield: 3 cups.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and sour cream.
Sprinkle dry Jell-O into mixture and stir until creamy.
Add drained oranges and pineapple. Mix thoroughly.
Place in dish and chill.

title: hot dogs and scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes, onion and enough water to cover in a large saucepan; cook until tender.
Meanwhile, melt butter in another pan; add flour and stir until smooth.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add milk and cheese, stirring until cheese melts and sauce is thickened.
Add hot dogs and heat through.
Drain potatoes and onion.
Place in baking dish.
Add sauce and mix to distribute hot dogs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Makes about 8 servings.

title: cream cheese-pecan pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, 1 egg and 1 teaspoon flavoring until creamy.
Spread in pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over this.
Then beat until well blended the 3 eggs, 1/4 cup sugar, corn syrup and 1 teaspoon flavoring.
Pour this over the pecans.
Bake at 375° until center is firm, about 45 minutes or a little longer.

title: mexican cornbread(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray an 8 or 9-inch skillet with cooking spray and heat in oven.
Add ingredients to cornmeal in order listed.
Add jalapeno peppers to taste.
Stir ingredients until well mixed.
Pour into hot skillet and bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
In saucepan, place water, margarine and cocoa; bring to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients.
Mix well; set aside.
Mix together butter, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Add to chocolate batter.
Pour on greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; bake at 400°.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add lemon juice and chili powder.
Stir well.
Add catsup, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve on buns.
Serves 5.

title: linda's country meat loaf
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together to make 2 loaf size pans or 4 mini loaves.
After mixing ingredients, add to mixture 4 ounces dressing and 1/2 of can of tomato paste.
Arrange loaves in pan. Mix remaining dressing and tomato paste.
Pour over top of loaves. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar; set aside.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water and add syrup.
Chill until almost set.
Add cranberry mixture and remaining ingredients to gelatin.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Chill.

title: oyster crackers(snack food good for diabetics)
directions: Put crackers in plastic bowl with cover.
Heat oil warm.
Pour over crackers; add dill pepper and Ranch dressing.
Shake real good; then shake real good. Shake every so often.
Make 24 hours before serving.

title: raisin-cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll dough on a lightly floured surface into a 14 x 8-inch rectangle.
Brush surface with 2 tablespoons melted butter. Combine sugar and next 4 ingredients; sprinkle over dough, leaving a 1/2-inch border on all sides.
Starting with long side, roll up jellyroll fashion.
Pinch seams to seal (do not seal ends).
Cut into 12 slices; place in a lightly greased 9-inch pan.
Brush with remaining butter; cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and let rise in warm place (85°) for 50 minutes or until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine powdered sugar and lemon juice; drizzle over warm rolls.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: cold fresh peach pie
directions: Mix together cornstarch, salt, sugar and water.
Cook until thick; remove from heat and add dry Jell-O.
Cool.
Fold in diced peaches.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Sprinkle on remaining ingredients.
Roll.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: salmon patties
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter.
Mix with other ingredients. Form patties.
Let stand a few hours in fridge.
Dip in egg, bread and fry.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Peel and slice zucchini 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Grease baking dish and arrange zucchini in a layer.
Put in sliced onion and sliced tomato.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Add layer of Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cold taco pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in baking pan to make a crust.
Bake according to directions on package.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and taco seasoning together.
Spread mixture over cooked and cooled crust.
Spread chopped tomato, green pepper and olives over top of mixture.
Sprinkle entire pizza with shredded cheese and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: diet sloppy joes
directions: Saute ground beef, onion, celery and garlic; drain well.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon hamburger mixture over both pieces of each bun.
Serves 6. Has 269 calories, 5 fat grams; food exchanges equal 3 meat, 1 bread, 1 fat.

title: peaches and cream tart
directions: Combine pecans, flour and butter; press into the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 9 in. tart pan with removable bottom. Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely.
Whip cream until soft peaks form; set aside. Add extracts and orange peel; mix well.
Mix in the whipped cream on low speed.
Spoon into crust.
Chill for 2-4 hours.
Just before serving, arrange peaches and raspberries over filling.
In the microwave or on the stovetop, melt preserves and honey; mix well.
Carefully spoon or brush over fruit.
Cut into wedges and serve.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Brown the margarine and onion together.
Add all remaining ingredients (except corn flakes) in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add the browned onion with butter.

title: hot cranberry cider
directions: In saucepan, bring ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Remove spices.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spread cherries in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread cake mix (powder) over the top. Sprinkle sugar over the top of cake powder.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over top and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 325° until light brown on top and bubbly.

title: totable peach cobbler
directions: Peel and pit peaches; slice into 2-quart casserole.
Add sugar, lemon juice and cornstarch to peaches.
Mix gently. Sprinkle with topping (recipe below).
Bake in 350° oven until center is bubbly and topping is browned.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except eggs in a large bowl. Whip the eggs until fluffy; fold into other mixture and pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzel crumbs with melted butter.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add Cool Whip; spread over pretzel mixture and refrigerate.
Blend strawberries with gelatin mixture that has been dissolved in hot water.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Spread over cheese mixture.
Return to refrigerator and chill until firm.

title: company sausage gravy(low-fat)
directions: Crumble sausage into large saucepan; cook over medium-low heat until brown.
Add onion; cook and stir until transparent.
Stir flour into cooked sausage mixture until golden brown.
Stir in milk; cook about 6 minutes or until mixture bubbles.
Add seasoning; cook, stirring, until thickened.
To serve, spoon over biscuit halves.

title: lexington style dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot. Bring to a boil, then turn down to low heat and simmer until sugar melts. Let sit for several hours before serving over barbecue.

title: microwave chili
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, crumble ground beef; stir in onions and garlic.
Heat 6 to 7 minutes on High, stirring once; drain. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat covered for 6 to 7 minutes on High.
Continue cooking on Medium (power level 5) for an additional 35 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Gradually add rice flour.
Next add flour.
Grease 2 round (9-inch) tins and place in dough.
Prick all over with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool a few minutes and cut into triangles.
Cool on wire rack.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine apple, celery and raisins in a medium bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and lemon juice, stirring well to blend.
Add to fruit mixture and toss lightly to coat well. Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Yields 5 servings.
Serving Size:
1 cup. Exchanges:
1 fruit, 1 fat.

title: roasted eggplant and pepper salad
directions: Roast eggplant and peppers until done.
Put in paper bag. Remove skins, seeds and membranes from peppers.
Peel skin from eggplant.
Cut eggplant and peppers into narrow strips.
Combine with remaining ingredients except sardines.
Gently toss in sardines and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve on diagonal slices of crusty Italian bread. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: snails in mushroom caps
directions: Mix parsley, scallions, garlic and butter well.
Add salt and pepper to taste and add a pinch of nutmeg.
Remove stems from mushrooms and fill with butter mixture.
Place a snail in each mushroom cap and top with more butter mixture.
Place in casserole (one layer).
Bake at 400° about 10 minutes.
Serve as first course or appetizers.
Makes 24.

title: mama's refrigerator yeast rolls
directions: Mix sugar, salt and oil in large bowl.
Add scalded milk and then cool mixture.
Add 2 well beaten eggs.
In a separate bowl, dissolve 2 packages of yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add to mixture. Beat in 3 cups of flour to make a soft batter.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Beat down; add 3 to 4 cups flour.
Do not make dough too stiff.
Rub Wesson oil lightly over dough. Cover and let rise in refrigerator overnight.

title: cranberry holiday salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add orange rind, cranberry sauce, pineapple and celery.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart dish and chill until firm (3 to 4 hours).
Makes 12 servings.

title: baked yams
directions: Place yams in baking pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Remove yams from oven and cut in half.
Remove skin, add orange rind, allspice and salt. Mash with electric mixer until smooth.

title: three chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugars, butter and evaporated milk in large pan. Stir until melted and mixture boils.
Cover and boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat; add marshmallows and stir until dissolved. Add chocolate; stir until melted and then add vanilla and nuts to mixture.
Pour into 10 x 15-inch pan.
Cool; chill.

title: granny's coconut cream pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch or flour and salt. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook at medium heat until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir small amount hot mix into egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture.
Cook another 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla, then coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes until brown.

title: aunt kay's corn casserole
directions: Mix and put in 2-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Heat 1/2 cup sugar in heavy skillet; stir constantly, until sugar is melted and golden brown.
Remove from heat; stir in boiling water slowly.
Cook over low heat; stir constantly until sugar lumps are dissolved.
Add enough water to syrup, if necessary, to measure 1/2 cup.
Cool.

title: pull-apart onion rolls
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix butter, onion, bouillon, parsley and onion powder in saucepan.
Heat until butter is melted and bouillon is dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Pour about half of mixture into 9 x 1 1/2-inch round layer pan.
Spread mixture evenly.

title: alice's chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter, Crisco and sugar. Add 5 egg yolks and mix well. Add the cocoa. Add alternately the flour, baking powder and milk, mixing well after each addition.
Add the vanilla.
Fold stiff egg whites into mixture last of all.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or longer.
(I check mine at 1 hour.)
Frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: cheesy chicken macaroni
directions: Make macaroni and cheese as instructed on the box.
While stirring in cream of chicken soup, reduce heat.
Cover and let sit for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Season as desired, then serve.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: Cream together the first 5 ingredients.
Add chocolate chips, form into ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill for 2 hours. Serve with graham crackers or chocolate graham crackers.

title: mushroom-spinach pasta
directions: With an electric mixer beat cottage cheese and cream cheese until nearly smooth.
In a saucepan, cook onion in butter or margarine until tender but not brown.
Add mushrooms, wine, thyme, salt and pepper.
Stir in cheese mixture, evaporated milk and drained spinach.
Heat through, but don't let it boil or it will separate.
Place hot spaghetti on large platter and top with sauce; toss gently.
Serves 4 as a main course.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans or one large Bundt pan.
Sift flour and combine all ingredients.
Mix well by hand.
Pour batter into prepared pans and bake for 1 hour or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: "hello dolly" cookies
directions: Melt oleo or butter in the bottom of pan (flat cake pan).
Add in the order listed.
(These should be added layer by layer.) Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes. May need to shield pie crust to prevent overbrowning.

title: italian beef
directions: Roast beef to medium rare or medium.
Slice thinly; refrigerate.
Add ingredients to drippings in pan.
(Hint for rosemary:
Staple into tea bag.)
Strain rosemary after 10 to 20 minutes simmering.
Cool.
Remove fat.
Add cold beef to heated mixture.
Serve on submarine buns, hoagie buns, potato rolls or kaiser rolls.
Great for crowds.

title: calico bean bake
directions: Bake all together at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: squash bake
directions: Cook squash until tender and drain. Add pimento, sour cream, soup, margarine and 1/2 box of Stove Top dressing. Add 2 tablespoons seasoning from dressing box. Mash squash and these ingredients. Put into shallow baking dish, adding remainder of Stove Top dressing to top of squash. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil, debone and cut up chicken.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Melt margarine and pour over chicken.
Place eggs on top.
Mix flour and milk with wire whisk.
Pour over chicken. Mix chicken broth and soup.
Bring to boil.
Pour over mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Roll chops in flour.
Fry until brown; drain.
Mix other ingredients and pour over chops.
Cook, uncovered, for 45 minutes, or until tender.
Baste often.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Beat 5 minutes. Add chips.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes in a well-greased Bundt pan.
Cool 15 minutes before turning out.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Dough will be a little sticky.
With floured hands, roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes until cookies look dry and tops are creakled.
Remove from oven and immediately press a candy kiss in center of each.
Cool on cookie sheets for 2 mins.

title: italian pea soup
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil until translucent.
Add celery and saute.
Add pea juice, tomatoes and spices; simmer 10 minutes. Add peas.
Serve with cooked pasta shells.

title: graham cracker fruit cake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Chop
nuts.
Add fruit and then milk and coconut.
This makes a
thick batter.
Use a knife to mix dough and spread in well-greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: steak americana
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces. Roll into flour and place in skillet (iron skillet is best). Brown on both sides. Drain off grease. Sprinkle with garlic powder.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter in frypan or Dutch oven.
Add onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook until tender.
Add tomato soup.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve over rice.

title: sugar-free cookies
directions: Combine the flour, baking powder,
salt and cinnamon. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add a little milk at a time.
Bring to boil.
Add butter.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Set aside.
Cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
Mix with other ingredients.
Pour dressing over and let set for at least 3 hours before serving.

title: baked cornbread
directions: Sift together meal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Mix together beaten egg, milk and fat.
Add, all at once, to the dry ingredients.
Stir just enough to moisten and blend all ingredients.
Pour batter into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
9 servings.

title: southwestern chicken
directions: Simmer sauce for 10 minutes.
Pour over 2 1/2 pound chicken and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: no fail fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in a large glass mixing bowl. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on Roast (70%) for 10 minutes. Stir and continue cooking on Roast (70%) for 5 to 6 minutes or until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Fold in Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla. Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
When firm, cut into squares. Yields 72 fudge squares.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13 pan.
You will probably have enough for another smaller pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You will have to adjust baking time. It will take a little less time for the smaller one.
Top with bread crumbs or durkee's french fried onions.
Dot with butter and put back in oven for 5 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave-safe container in the microwave at Full power for 3 minutes or on top of a double boiler over simmering, not boiling, water.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and add next 3 when Jell-O begins to set.
Then combine remaining ingredients and cook until thick. Cool and spread on Jell-O mixture.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese and chopped nuts.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: hawaiian spareribs(makes 6 servings)
directions: Cut ribs in 2 inch pieces; brown in hot shortening.
Combine garlic, ginger, soy sauce, vinegar and sugar and pour over ribs. Add hot water.
Simmer until meat is tender, about 45 minutes. Remove meat and thicken liquid in pan with cornstarch.
Reheat ribs in gravy and serve with rice.

title: turnip and onion casserole
directions: Arrange alternate layers of turnips and onions in a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper. Pour bouillon over the vegetables and dot with butter. Bake, covered, at 400° for 1 hour. Garnish with bacon or parsley before serving. Serves 6.

title: tuna 'n' celery sticks
directions: In large bowl, mix together cream cheese, yogurt and basil until smooth.
Add tuna, carrot, Cheddar cheese and onion.
Mix well.
Spread mixture into celery stalks; cut into fourths.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except jello.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Let cool. Pour over sliced berries in pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Add crushed pineapple to beaten eggs.
Add sugar and mix well. Sift flour with baking soda and add to mixture.
Add chopped pecans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: crab imperial
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter and stir in flour.
Add milk, salt and pepper; simmer over medium-low heat until thickened. Cool.
Mix with crab.
Add mayonnaise, Worcestershire and lemon juice.
Mix well and spoon into casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until top browns and casserole is hot.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 400°, partially baking crust for 10 minutes.
Cool; reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Stir in taco seasoning mix.
In a small mixing bowl, combine refried beans and 1/2 cup taco sauce.
For deep dish crust, layer one-half of the seasoned meat mixture in bottom of pie crust and top with one-half of refried beans.
Repeat layers.
For regular crust, place one-half of the seasoned meat mixture in bottom of crust and each with one-half of refried beans.
Sprinkle cheese on top; bake 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; cool 10 minutes.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes and remaining taco seasoning.
Makes six servings; 25 minutes to prepare and 35 minutes baking time.
Cool time:
10 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix beef, pork, bread crumbs, milk, egg, onion, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place meatballs on ungreased 10 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake uncovered in preheated 350° oven for about 20 minutes.
Remove meatballs; keep warm.
Place 3 tablespoons pan drippings in saucepan; stir in flour.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in water, half and half and beef base or bouillon.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour gravy over meatballs.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and chill.

title: crock-pot round steak
directions: Mix soups and water.
Cut round steak into 4 to 6 servings. Alternate soup mixture with meat layers.
Cook in crock-pot all day on medium.
Serve with noodles.

title: granny's extra special strawberry jam
directions: Mix berries and sugar.
Combine lemon juice and pectin in a bowl.
Add to berry mixture.
Stir for 3 minutes or until most of the sugar crystals are dissolved.
Pour into jars and cover with lids.
Let set at room temperature for 24 hours.
Put in freezer or refrigerate for use within 3 weeks.
Makes 5 medium jars of jam.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix all at room temperature and beat.
Store in jars or freeze.
Spread on thin slices of French bread and broil until cheese melts.

title: pineapple paradise pie
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, flour and coconut.
Press into the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Crumble.
Press 2 cups of crumbs into 9-inch pie pan.
Cool.
Reserve remaining crumbs to sprinkle on top of pie.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Mix all of above.
Chill for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange lettuce in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In layers, add other vegetables.
Do not toss!
Spread mayonnaise evenly over layer of peas.
Sprinkle with sugar and Cheddar cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Sprinkle bacon over salad before serving.
Cut into squares.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.
This may be made the night before serving.

title: fail-proof egg and cheese souffle
directions: Cut crust off bread and tear remainder into pieces to line the bottom of a small cake pan.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings together and pour over the bread.
Keep in the refrigerator overnight.
Put on cheese just before baking.
Bake at 350°
for 40 to 60 minutes, depending on depth of pan.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes (whole) in plenty of boiling salted water until just tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Drain; let stand a few minutes until cool enough to handle, then peel.
Cut into 1/2 inch thick slices.
Place in a salad bowl.
In skillet, fry bacon until crisp; remove, crumble and add to potatoes.
To fat in skillet, add onions and cook until transparent.
Next, add vinegar, salt, pepper, sugar, bouillon cubes and water.
Bring to a boil, while stirring and dissolving bouillon cubes.
Pour with salad oil over potatoes; toss carefully.
Sprinkle with parsley.
It's best to prepare 45 minutes before serving time.

title: apple oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add vanilla and apples; mix well.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and spices; add to cream mixture.
Mix well.
By hand, stir in raisins, nuts and oatmeal.
Drop by tablespoonfuls, 2 inches apart, on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.
Cook on wire rack.
Store between sheets of waxed paper.
Cookies will stick together.

title: gingered zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini into 1/4-inch thick julienne strips.
Heat a wok or skillet and add cooking oil.
Add zucchini and toss gently for 1 minute.
Add all remaining ingredients and stir-fry for another few seconds, or until the sauce is hot.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked gouda in pastry
directions: Thaw one sheet pastry according to directions; reserve second sheet in freezer for other uses.
Cut pastry sheet in half and roll each half on a lightly floured surface to a 9-inch square. Sprinkle 1/4 cup pecans in center of each pastry square.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a large skillet cook onion, green pepper and garlic in oil until tender but not brown.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, rice, sugar, chili powder, pepper, hot pepper sauce and 1 cup water. Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender and most liquid is absorbed.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: all-american hot sundae cake
directions: Combine brown sugar, cocoa and water; mix well. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place marshmallows evenly on top. Make cake batter according to package directions. Pour into pan. Top with nuts. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: avocado and crabmeat ring
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1 1/2 cups of water in top of double boiler.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Place over hot water and stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate approximately 30 minutes until syrupy. Separate crabmeat pieces.
Cut avocado in half.
Press chunked and peeled avocado through sieve until measures 1 cup.
Toss crabmeat, avocado, sour cream, mayonnaise, onion, celery, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Mix with gelatin and pour into 6-cup ring mold. Refrigerate until firm.

title: breaded venison
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Dip venison steaks into beaten egg, then dry mixture, then repeat.
Fry in oil until done or you can bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water in large bowl and cool.
Blend white sugar, brown sugar and oleo into oatmeal.
Beat in eggs. Stir in flour, baking soda, salt, cocoa and 1 cup chocolate chips. Put it in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with another cup of chocolate chips and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: punch
directions: For peach color punch, use orange Kool-Aid and orange sherbet. Mix and chill before serving.

title: grace griffin's cream puffs
directions: Add water and butter and bring to a boil. Add plain flour and add pinch of salt.
Beat until forms a ball.
(Have fire on low.) Take off and add the eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each.
Drop by spoonfuls (teaspoon) on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 250° for 15 minutes.
Do not open door until this time.
Cool.
Slit and add filling.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: granny vaughn coconut pound cake
directions: For rich cake, add 2 sticks butter.
Cream together Crisco and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk alternately. Add vanilla and coconut.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mom hettricks' barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to a boil in a saucepan.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Make sauce mix tomato sauce, onions, garlic and oregano together.
Add salt and pepper; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour.

title: chicken or tuna balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Blend in shortening and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Roll out on a waxed paper coated with flour.
Cut and place in a greased pan.
Bake about 15 minutes at 425°.

title: south sea sauce with crackers
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Pour on block of cream cheese. Serve with crackers.
Makes enough for 2 packages cream cheese.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x 13-inch pan with diced chicken.
Mix together chicken soup and sour cream and spread on top of chicken. Cover with 3 cups of crushed crackers.
Drizzle melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Cream peanut butter and shortening well.
Add sugars and vanilla; continue beating until fluffy.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in flour mixture and mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in flour.
Make a crisscross pattern.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: cabbage soup
directions: In large pot, cook celery, onion and cabbage in water until tender.
Add bouillon, salt, pepper, beef and tomato sauce.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in brown sugar and ketchup.
Simmer 10 minutes longer.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: dilly beans
directions: Parboil beans 15 minutes.
Place in hot jars and add 1 clove garlic and 1 teaspoon of dill seed to each jar.
Combine water, vinegar and salt and heat; cover beans with hot vinegar mixture. Seal jars.
Makes approximately 6 pints.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, flavoring and rest of ingredients.
Use 1/2 teaspoon batter; mash down with fork or thumb.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 80+ cookies.

title: english tea scones
directions: Mix flour and salt in basin.
Rub in shortening.
Mix in sugar and fruit.
Stir in egg and milk, sufficient to make a soft dough.

title: chili con quesa
directions: Put all ingredients into large bowl.
Set microwave oven to High.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes or until well melted.
Stir every three minutes so cheese does not burn on bottom.
Serve hot with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: cabbage patch soup
directions: Combine and cook slow for 2 hours.
Thin with chicken broth if too thick.

title: scallops linguine
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in mushroom stems and scallops for a minute or two.
Sprinkle in flour; stir until it disappears.
Gradually add half and half or milk; blend until saucy.
Stir in seasonings and mushroom caps; simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve over linguine pasta.

title: crock pot christmas punch
directions: In a crockpot, combine juices, red-hot candies and cinnamon stick. Cook on low for 2-5 hours. Remove cinnamon stick(s) before serving. Yields 2 quarts.

title: three bean dish
directions: Mix all together and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix together pineapple, cranberries, oranges and sugar.
Let stand while jello mixture is cooling.
After cool, mix all together and add 1 cup nutmeats.
Chill.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Add Jell-O to boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add sugar. Add the can of cranberries to hot Jell-O and stir (chop up) until dissolved.
Add crushed pineapple with juice.
When cool, add celery and nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fried squash
directions: Wash squash and cut up.
Boil until tender.
Drain water.
Add grease and onion and cook until tender.
Put in skillet and fry a little.
Add egg, salt and pepper to taste.
Stir real good.

title: caramel poppycock
directions: Pop corn as directed.
In large saucepan combine brown sugar, butter, syrup and salt.
Heat to boiling and cook for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Stir hot syrup into popped corn and peanuts.
Spread on baking sheet.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Melt Velveeta and butter together.
Sift sugar and cocoa together.
Mix all together with vanilla and nuts.
Mix with a spoon until smooth.
Spoon into pan.
Cool and cut into squares. Yields 5 pounds.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix together eggs, margarine, onion, cottage cheese, salt, broccoli and corn muffin mix.
Pour into large greased baking pan and bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375°.
Test with silver knife after 45 minutes.

title: whipped cream fruit salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate; add cherries to top.

title: stuffed dates
directions: Mix
cream cheese and sugar.
Stuff cheese mixture into dates. Top with cherry half.
Store in refrigerator.

title: nosebag lunch(method:  fireless)
directions: Girls can prepare their Nosebag Lunch at home or at the campsite before venturing away for an extended period of time. Leave the juice boxes and soda cans at home!
Your fruit can serve as a thirst quencher.
(Leaders may wish to have a jug of fresh water on hand, especially in warm weather.)

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and add milk and water.
Stir in chopped onion.
Add more milk as may be necessary to form workable dough.
Mold pieces of dough into pones about 5-inches long, 3-inches wide, 3/4-inch thick.
Fry in deep hot fat or oil until brown.

title: raspberry divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and cook to hard ball stage. Combine beaten egg whites and gelatin; beat until mixture forms stiff peaks.
Pour hot syrup slowly into egg whites, beating until candy loses gloss and holds shape.
Fold in coconut and nuts (optional).
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Top with rows of chopped nuts and coconut.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Cook vinegar, sugar, butter and eggs until thick. Cool. Add remaining ingredients. Mix all together and chill day before.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Slice potato as if for French frying into foil (large enough to wrap potato).
Place butter or margarine on top of pattie. Sprinkle garlic salt and pepper to taste.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.
Serves 1.

title: praline pie
directions: Combine
butter,
brown
sugar
and
pecans in skillet; cook over low
heat until sugar dissolves.
Pour in pie shell. Combine sugar
and
cornstarch
in
a boiler; slowly add milk. Cook over low
heat until thickened.
Add vanilla;
pour over pecan mixture. Let
cool.
Whip cream, adding powdered sugar, as desired. Spread on top of cool pie.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Immediately add strawberries.
Stir until strawberries are melted.
Add pineapple and the small marshmallows.
Marshmallows will come to the top. After Jell-O is set and cold, top with whipped or sour cream.

title: orange coffee cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix at low speed.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hot 3 bean casserole(diabetic)
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet at medium heat until hot. Add onion, celery and garlic. Cook and stir for 5 minutes or until onion is translucent. Add remaining ingredients except green beans. Bring to a boil and reduce heat to
low. Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes. Add green beans. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Garnish with oregano. Makes 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: peanut butter chocolate kisses
directions: Combine brown sugar, peanut butter and butter in mixing bowl. Beat until thoroughly blended.
Add egg and vanilla, blend well. Add flour, blend well.
Cover and refrigerate about 1 hour. Preheat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Bake 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Press chocolate kisses into center of each cookie.
Return to oven and bake 3 minutes.
Watch carefully to avoid burning.
Transfer to wire racks to cool.
Cool completely before storing.
Makes about 40 cookies.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: strawberry cream roll cake
directions: Beat eggs until light and lemon colored.
Gradually add sugar and beat well.
Mix in water and vanilla.
Sift together cake flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold into egg-sugar mixture.
Line a greased jelly-roll pan with waxed paper.
Lightly grease the paper.
Pour batter onto waxed paper and spread evenly.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Lightly sift 10x sugar onto a tea towel.
Invert cake on waxed paper onto towel.
Remove paper and trim off any dry edges.
Roll cake up with towel, starting on long side.
Cool.
When cake is cool, unroll and spread the following mixture over it and reroll (don't try to flatten it).

title: extra easy pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll 1/2 the dough between 2 pieces of lightly floured wax paper.
Loosen top wax paper from dough; flip and loosen other wax paper.
Remove top wax paper and flip onto greased pie tin.
Cook with pie filling at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes enough for lower and upper crust or 2 lower crusts.

title: hash
directions: Cook onion slowly in fat for about 5 minutes.
Add potatoes, meat, salt, pepper and broth.
Continue cooking until potatoes are done.
If necessary, add extra liquid to keep mixture from burning.
Stir occasionally.

title: wild rice dressing
directions: Mix rice according to directions.
Brown sausage meat in skillet and drain.
Cook celery, onions and mushrooms with sausage until done.
Then add to cooked rice plus can of mushroom soup and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick mix sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix egg yolks, water, baking powder, vanilla, flour and 1 cup sugar in small bowl.
Combine in large bowl the egg whites, salt and cream of tartar.
Beat with mixer at high speed until soft peaks begin to form.
Beat 1/2 cup sugar into egg whites, 1 teaspoon at a time.
Do not underbeat.
Beat the small bowl ingredients all at once.
Fold small bowl ingredients into stiffly beaten egg white mixture.
Do not beat!
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Invert pan immediately.
Cool in pan at least 1 hour.
Frost top and sides with your own frosting.

title: green chile chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion in a spoonful of butter until translucent; add green chilies, soup and chicken.
Cook over low heat until bubbly. In large casserole dish, layer noodles, soup mixture and cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is bubbling.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Make 4 loaves, or pat in pan.
Bake for about 20 to 25 minutes at 450°.
Meanwhile, mix tomato sauce, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over loaves.
Cook another 10 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix everything except marshmallows by hand just enough to blend.
Do not over mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If desired cover with miniature marshmallows while still hot.

title: beef jerky
directions: Mix all together; pour over meat.
Refrigerate overnight. Stir once or twice.

title: crab casserole
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, add flour and stir until smooth. Sprinkle lemon juice over crab meat.
Add remaining ingredients to sauce; mix well and pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with buttered crumbs and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields approximately 6 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat with mixer.

title: baked chicken souffle
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients; season to taste.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 3 slices diced bread (toasted) on bottom of pan.
Put chicken mixture over, then cover with 3 more slices of bread.
Mix the beaten eggs with the milk; pour over top.
Place in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: sugar-free strawberry pie
directions: Mix vanilla pudding with 2 cups water in bowl and microwave for 6 minutes. Stop halfway and stir with whisk.

title: loretta's pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil together.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well. Sift together all dry ingredients; add dry ingredients alternately with water.
Pour into two well greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tests done.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pans to cool.
Makes 2 loaves.
Freezes well.
Applesauce may be substituted for the pumpkin.

title: microwave polenta
directions: Put in dish altogether.
Mix well.
Put in microwave for 5 minutes, then take out and mix.
Put in 5 minutes more.
Take out and mix well.
Put in 3 minutes more.
Take out and mix, let stand.

title: california chicken salad
directions: Skin chicken.
Cook until tender in salt water.
Shred chicken when cool.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, Pet milk and oleo to boil and boil rapidly for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and blend in peanut butter and 1 pint of marshmallow cream.
Put in a greased pan until cool, then cut in small pieces and let sit until firm.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Mix together the Baker's cocoa, milk, salt, Swan's Down cake flour and sugar.
Cook until it begins to thicken.
Add egg yolks. Continue cooking at least 2 minutes or until thick.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Beat with the mixer until creamy.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and use enough mayonnaise to suit your taste or to coat all vegetables.
Bell pepper is optional but adds color if you have red or yellow on hand.

title: grilled bacon wrap-ups
directions: Wrap 1 or 2 strips of bacon around each piece of chicken. Secure with toothpicks.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Grill over hot coals about 10 minutes on each side or until tender.

title: creamy broccoli mold
directions: Soften gelatin in 3/4 cup cold water.
In medium saucepan, bring 1/2 cup water to boil.
Add broccoli, bouillon cubes and onion.
Cover and bring to a full boil over high heat.
Reduce heat, simmer 5 minutes or until tender.
Add gelatin, stir until well dissolved.
Remove and let cool.

title: beef picante casserole
directions: In large shallow bowl, mix water and picante sauce.
Soak tortillas for 5 minutes and drain.
Cook beef and onion; drain. Stir salt, pepper, cumin, chili powder, garlic powder and picante into meat mixture; simmer 5 minutes.

title: peach pie - baked pie shell
directions: Place all ingredients in pan and cook on stove top until thick and clear.
Cool.
Place in pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add the applesauce and raisins.
Add the flour, soda, spices, salt and nuts.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes in an 8 x 12-inch loaf pan.

title: cheese strata
directions: Place 6 slices of bread in a buttered pan.
Layer the cheese, then ham and place the remaining 6 slices of bread on the top. Combine the remaining ingredients and pour evenly over the bread. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 55 minutes.
About 15 minutes before done, spread shredded cheese over the top.

title: chocolate velvet pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake pie crust 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, in heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate with sweetened condensed milk; remove from heat.
Stir in eggs.
Add water and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into hot pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 300°.
Bake 20 minutes longer or until center is set.
Cool.
Chill thoroughly.
Top with whipped cream. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: quick beef stew
directions: Heat stew and sour cream on stove.
Pour into baking dish. Prepare biscuits but do not cook. Drop biscuits on top of stew mixture. Bake at 350° until biscuits brown.

title: tomato meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook onion in butter until soft; combine with meat.
Add salt, pepper, parsley 1/2 can tomato soup, eggs and bread crumbs.
Shape meat into a loaf about 9 x 5 x 2-inches.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Combine remaining soup with the water; pour over meat loaf during last 15 minutes of cooking. Serves 8.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put pie on cookie sheet to catch any drippings.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sparerib sauerkraut dinner
directions: Layer spareribs, sauerkraut and carrots in large cooker. Season with salt. Measure reserved sauerkraut liquid and add water to make 1 cup. Pour into cooker and bring to boil. Reduce heat to simmer for 2 hours. Add potatoes and simmer for 1 hour more.

title: jean's cheese bread
directions: Spread on thick-cut French bread.
Wrap loaf in foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesecake tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, vanilla and eggs together for filling.
Place bake cups in muffin tins.
Put a vanilla wafer in each bake cup and fill 1/2 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Allow to cool.
When cooled, top with pie filling.

title: biscotti (christmas gifts)houston, texas
directions: Combine in a large bowl.
Package in an airtight container. Attach the following recipe:

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in cold water.
Boil sugar, jello and boiling water. Then add to Knox gelatine.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When set, cut into squares and store in plastic container.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Alternate shrimp and
Bermuda onion rings in a container. Combine remaining
ingredients
and
mix
well.
Pour over shrimp and onion rings and marinate overnight. Drain to serve. Serves 8 as a salad	served	on
lettuce
or
to
20 as an appetizer.

title: no-fat mustard dill sauce
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly in a small bowl.
Serve on vegetables or fish.
Store in a covered container in the refrigerator.

title: whipped mince pie
directions: Combine pudding and milk; whip 1 minute.
Add water and sour cream; beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Stir in mincemeat and pour into baked pie shell; chill.

title: christmas coconut cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar and beat 10 to 15 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk and oil, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.

title: corned beef puff sandwich
directions: Layer bread and sprinkle corned beef and cheese on top.
Add remainder bread.
Pour liquid over and let sit for 30 minutes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Prepare rice by boiling in 3 cups boiling water with salt. In a frying pan put oil; heat very hot.
Beat eggs and put in hot pan, stirring all the time.
Add vegetables (onion, mushrooms and pimentos).
Add soy sauce and soy brown gravy sauce, stirring and adding rice in mixture until all brown.
Add Accent.
Let simmer on low heat.

title: jumbo molasses cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt, ginger, and cloves.
Blend in baking soda into molasses; set aside.
Cream butter gradually and add sugar and
beat till light and fluffy.
Blend in molasses mixture.
Add flour mixture alternately with water.
Blend
thoroughly after each addition.
Stir in cereal.
Use 1/4 c dough for each cookie. Drop onto greased baking sheet about 3 inches apart.
Use a glass with flat bottom dipped in butter and sugar after pressing each cookie 3 to 4 inches in diameter.
Bake 375° for 15 minutes. Makes 20 large cookies.

title: crab casserole
directions: Toss together lightly.
Put in casserole and cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Very good!

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Slit each chop horizontally so that a small pocket is formed. Dice the bread and mix with the cream, salt, pepper and herbs. Mix thoroughly and use to fill the pocket in each chop.
Secure with wooden toothpicks.
Brush the chops with oil and sprinkle with paprika, then broil or barbecue for 10 to 15 minutes on each side.
Remove the toothpicks and serve the chops on a bed of braised cabbage or sauerkraut.
Serves 4.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread and cool completely.
Combine all ingredients and enjoy.

title: cranberry squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Stir in orange juice, shortening and egg.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in cranberries and nuts. Turn into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with topping.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Prepare 3 cups instant soup per instructions on packet.
In baking dish, pour preserves and Thousand Island dressing.
Pour hot onion soup over mixture and stir.
When combined thoroughly, place chicken breasts in baking dish, spooning liquid over them evenly.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Check chicken for doneness. Serve with yellow rice and crescent rolls.

title: bill's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes. Then add remaining ingredients.

title: egg casserole
directions: Coat a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard in bowl. Stir in bread, cheese and sausage.
Pour into prepared dish. Chill, covered, for 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cut into serving portions to serve.

title: date nut bread
directions: Grease loaf pan and line bottom with wax paper.
Mix dates and water.
Let stand 2 hours.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and date mixture.
Sift soda, salt and flour.

title: impossible garden pie
directions: Sprinkle chopped vegetables into a pie pan.
Top with cheese. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth and pour over vegetables and cheese in pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.

title: almond butter crunch
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan. Add sugar, corn syrup and water. Cook and stir (between medium to high temperature setting), stirring occasionally to hard-crack stage (300°). Quickly stir in coarsely sliced nuts and spread on ungreased 12 1/2 x 16-inch flexible cookie sheet. Cool thoroughly (several hours). Melt

1 bar of chocolate in double boiler. Spread in sections on brittle, spreading ground nuts on each section as you go. Refrigerate this batch (on sheet) to chill for an hour. Then remove brittle and turn out on waxed paper and ice 2nd side with chocolate and almonds. Refrigerate to chill (second side). Set out at room temperature for an hour before breaking up.

title: rigatoni with vodka sauce
directions: Melt butter over medium heat in large nonstick skillet until foam and bubbles appear.
Saute Prosciutto for approximately 5 minutes.
Sauce will begin to thicken.
Add cheese (1/2 cup or more to taste).
Pour sauce over pasta in a large bowl and toss to coat.
Garnish with fresh parsley bunches.

title: nana mcnulty's cookies
directions: Mix the brown sugar and the shortening. Add the eggs and the vanilla.
Sift the flour, soda and salt. Add the dry ingredients to the shortening mixture.
Mix in the chopped walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fudge(carnation 5 minute)
directions: Combine Carnation, sugar and salt in saucepan over medium heat. Bring to boil and cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. (Start timing when mixture starts to bubble around edges of pan.) Remove from
heat.
Add chocolate, marshmallows and vanilla.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute (or until marshmallows are completely melted and blended).
Pour into 8-inch square buttered pan. Garnish with nuts, if desired.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: ham brunch puffit
directions: Mix bread crumbs, cheese, beaten egg yolks, milk, 1 tablespoon butter and seasonings.
Saute onion in remaining butter.
Add to first mixture with ham and parsley and mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Turn into buttered shallow baking dish. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until set.
Serves 6.

title: stewed paprika chicken
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons shortening in large kettle, but do not brown chicken.
Put sliced onions on top and paprika, salt and pepper. Cook about 1 hour.
Add soup and vegetables.
Add cream just before serving.
May be thickened (with flour and water); serve with dumplings or hot rice.

title: chicken chas
directions: Cook chicken and chop into bite size pieces.
Mix mayo, soup and cheese over low heat until all is melted, stirring constantly. Combine remaining ingredients, except wine.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour, stirring every 10 minutes.
Cook noodles; pour sauce on top, then squeeze lemon juice on top.
Open wine.
Oh, it's soo . . . good!
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Rub 3 to 4 pounds roast with brown sugar.
Place in crock-pot with 1/2 cup water.
Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.
Drain liquid, saving 1 cup.
Shred meat and add remainder of ingredients to meat with 1 cup of meat juice mentioned above.
Simmer and serve.

title: banana split cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package for a two layer cake. Prepare fillings; divide Cool Whip in half.
Fold berries into half and pineapple into other half.
To assemble:
Use a serrated knife to split cake layers in half horizontally.
Place bottom of one layer on a serving plate.
Top with the berry-cream mixture, spreading to the edge.
Place another split layer on top.
Spread with half of the warm fudge topping.
Sprinkle with half of the nuts.
Top with another cake layer.
Repeat process with pineapple cream mixture.
Top with remaining split cake layer.
Spread remaining warm fudge topping on top of cake, letting some drip down the sides.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Serve immediately or refrigerate.
If desired, garnish with strawberries or bananas.

title: ham rolls
directions: Slice dinner rolls in half.
On bottom half of rolls, add ham and cheese.
Put the top of the bread on top of the cheese.
Mix together the next 5 ingredients.
Slowly pour over dinner rolls. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
May garnish with sesame seeds. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion.
Mix soup and tomatoes together.
In casserole dish, put beans on bottom.
Meat and onions next.
Corn chips (crush chip first).
Grate cheese on top, then pour on soup and tomato mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange slice candy cake with frosting
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Dissolve soda in milk and add to creamed mixture.
Place flour in a large bowl.
Add dates, orange slices, nuts and coconut.
Add to creamed mixture.
This makes a very stiff dough (mix with hands).
Bake in three greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients like pie crust.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° until golden brown; cool.
Next blend together:
8 ounces cream cheese, 1 cup powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Next, mix 2 packages instant chocolate pudding with 3 cups milk until firm.
Layer cream cheese, then top with pudding and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli slightly less than package directions.
Mix broccoli, egg, mayonnaise, onion, soup and cheese in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Mix stuffing and melted butter; sprinkle over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy vegetable stew
directions: Shape meat into 1-inch balls.
Place into water.
Add cubed potatoes.
Cook 35 minutes over low heat.
Add vegetable soup and cook 10 minutes more.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Melt margarine and pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine 1 egg and cake mix; spread over melted margarine.
Combine 2 eggs, cream cheese and box of 10x sugar; spread over cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: louisiana cream pralines
directions: Mix sugar,
salt, milk and butter in a 2 quart saucepan; cook and
stir
over
low
heat
until sugar is dissolved.
Add pecans and
cook
over
medium
heat to soft ball stage (234°), stirring constantly.
Remove
from heat and let cook 5 minutes. Stir rapidly
until
mixture
begins to thicken and coat pecans lightly.
Drop
rapidly
from
a teaspoon onto aluminum foil to form patties.
If candy becomes too stiff at the last to handle easily, stir in a few drops of hot water.
Let stand until cool and set.
Yields 4 dozen patties.

title: borscht dr.
directions: Heat beef, pork, water, broth, salt and pepper for 1 1/2 hours.
Debone pork.
Put beef, pork, onion, garlic, potatoes and cabbage in soup.
Tie dill seed and pickling spice in cheesecloth; add to soup.
Simmer about 2 hours.
Stir in vinegar; remove spice ball.
Serve sour cream on top of soup.

title: lemon pepper marinade
directions: Combined all ingredients mixing well. Good for marinating shish kabobs!

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Melt margarine; add sugar and milk.
Bring to a full boil on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes on medium heat.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips, vanilla, Marshmallow Creme and nuts.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9 dish.

title: never fail coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine yogurt, mayonnaise, cream cheese and seasonings.
Mix well; stir in Cheddar cheese and crab.
Cover and chill 2 hours; sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with crackers, breadsticks or vegetables.
Makes approximately 20 servings.

title: microwave apples with strawberry sauce
directions: Place strawberries in blender container or food processor. Blend until smooth.
Cut off 1/4-inch from top and bottom of apples.
Cut each apple in half crosswise, forming 2 thick slices.

title: lemon ice box pie
directions: Beat milk and sugar together until mixture becomes thick. Add lemon juice and beat until thick.
Pour into pie shell and chill.
Yield:
6-8 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Soak broccoli in cold water overnight.

title: waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients in one bowl.
Separate eggs, putting egg whites in small bowl and egg yolks in dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Heat butter in saucepan over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour; cook until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except chicken.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Brush on chicken.
Grill chicken.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Gradually add flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder, vanilla and cocoa.
Mix well.
Mixture will be real thick!
Add zucchini.
(If your zucchini is very wet, drain and press out excess liquid or your bread will be too wet.)
Add almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for a regular bread pan or for 45 minutes for the mini loaves.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: grandma staehle's butterklose chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken slowly for a tender and tasty chicken, but if using a plump fryer, add 3 to 4 bouillon cubes for added flavor. Lay bread out until dry, pulling apart in small pieces, not crumbs.
Bread should be fresh, not stale.
Melt butter, pour on bread and mix.
Add allspice and mix.
Add eggs and mix.
Knead lightly; press into shape, forming a ball about 3/4 inch in diameter, against palm of hand.
Remove chicken from broth.
Drop butterklose into soup at rolling boil; allow butterklose to rise. Continue cooking for approximately 1/2 to 3/4 hour, testing klose intermittently until done.

title: golden rhubarb
directions: Cut the orange slices into small pieces.
Combine all the ingredients in a large pan.
let stand until the sugar dissolves. Then bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir until it thickens about 10 minutes.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Flour and fry breasts in small amount of oil until brown; set aside.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Mix chicken soup with one soup can of water. Spoon rice into a 10 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay fillet of breast on rice.
Add about 1/2 of soup on this layer, then put broccoli on breast fillets.
Add rest of soup and top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: watermelon rind preserves
directions: Dissolve the lime in 2 gallons cold water.
Cut rind into small pieces of uniform shape and size.
Soak overnight in lime water.
Drain and rinse through 2 changes of cold water and soak in clear water for 3 hours.
Add the ginger to 1 gallon water, then add rind and boil 20 minutes.
Add sugar and sliced lemon to 3 quarts fresh water.
Bring to boiling, add rind, and, if desired, add cinnamon, allspice and cloves to taste.
Cook until it is clear and tender.
Pack in clean, hot jars and seal immediately.

title: baked pizza dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and Italian seasoning until well blended. Spread in the bottom of a 9 inch pie plate.
Top with a layer of cheese (1 cup), a layer of pizza sauce and another layer of cheese (1 cup).
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes until thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: banana split muffins
directions: Combine biscuit mix and the 1/4 cup sugar.
Combine egg yolks, milk and shortening.
Add all at once to the dry ingredients, stirring just to moisten.
Put 1 1/2 tablespoons batter in the bottom of a greased muffin tin.
Cut banana into 12 cubes.
Place a banana cube, a cherry half and a walnut half atop the batter. Cover with 1 tablespoon more batter.

title: chocolate peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch baking pan in the oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over margarine and pour condensed milk evenly over the crumbs.
Top with chips and press down firmly.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool, then cut into bars.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 1/2-inch thick strips.
Coat with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Brown strips in 1/4 cup hot shortening. Drain tomatoes, adding liquid, water, onion and beef flavored gravy base to meat.
Simmer 1 1/4 hours until meat is tender.
Cut peppers into strips and to meat; simmer covered 5 minutes.
Add drained tomatoes, cut up to meat and cook 5 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: simple salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese and dry Jell-O (any flavor or color to complement the fruit you use or the season of the year). Add drained fruit (i.e. 1 small can crushed pineapple, jar of cherries, fruit cocktail, Mandarin oranges, etc.).
Coconut and chopped nuts can be added, if desired.

title: whole buttermilk biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine all dry ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Cut 6 tablespoons of butter into small pieces and add to flour mixture, cut in butter with a pastry blender or use 2 knives until mixture resembles fine meal.
Melt remaining 4 tablespoons butter and set aside.
Make a well in the flour mixture; pour in buttermilk and gradually work flour into buttermilk, using fork. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface.
Roll or pat evenly to 1/2 inch thickness, using a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter or rim of a glass, cut out 12 biscuits.
Brush both sides with melted butter and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool on baking sheets at least 5 minutes before splitting.
Use to make sandwiches or serve with main dish.

title: party pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Melt cheese and add enough ketchup to give an orange tinge.
Add cheese and sprinkle oregano over sausage.
Put spoon of sausage on party rye bread.
Add a spoonful of pizza sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Brown lightly at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: armenian rice
directions: Brown
vermicelli in margarine.
Add rice, then add hot chicken
broth, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until broth is absorbed, about 30 minutes.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix and pour over crackers.
Let stand 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: raised meatballs
directions: Soak bread in 1/2 cup milk.
Then add beaten eggs and mix. Add ground beef, salt and pepper, baking powder and onions; mix lightly but well.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts and brown in a small amount of fat.
Place into a greased baking dish.
Mix together soups and remaining milk.
Pour over meatballs and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: black russian pie
directions: Mix well and press into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 7 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool completely.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Mix all ingredients but the beef together in a medium saucepan and simmer for about 5 minutes, stirring as needed.
Cut roast in 2 or 3 pieces for easier turning.
Place meat in a single layer in a roasting pan and pour barbecue sauce over it.
Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, turning beef about every 1/2 hour.
During the last half hour, remove cover and turn more frequently.
Sauce will thicken and meat brown.
(Meat should be tender enough to tear apart easily.)
Remove from oven and cool enough to handle.
Shred meat (using two forks), removing bits of excess fat and bone, if any.
Pour off excess fat from sauce and mix sauce with shredded beef.
Serve hot in rolls.
Makes about 1 quart or enough for about 12 sandwiches.

title: norma's broccoli salad
directions: Toss with dressing. Can put red or green pepper on top. Can also add cauliflower.

title: scalloped potatoes(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Cook onion in butter until transparent but not brown.
Add flour, seasoned salt and pepper and blend.
Add milk and cook and stir until smooth and thickened.
Combine potatoes and sauce in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with buttered bread cubes and bake in a 375° oven about 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Cook chopped onion and celery in butter over low heat until tender.
Crumble the corn bread and loaf of bread in pan.
Add eggs, sage and salt.
Add onion and celery.
Add turkey broth. Mix lightly with fork until moist.
Pour into greased baking dish. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: anise cookie
directions: Beat the egg yolks and the two whole eggs together with sugar until foamy.
Blend in flour, salt and anise.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in 375° oven about 15 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream together all the above ingredients.
Cut up apples, oranges, grapes or any fruit in season and dip.

title: easy "fried chicken"(lo-fat)
directions: In a large bowl, combine oil, parsley, garlic and pepper.
Add chicken and toss to thoroughly coat each piece. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour, turning occasionally.
Heat oven to 350°.
In a large pie plate, combine bread crumbs and cheese. Remove chicken from marinade; completely coat each piece with bread crumb mixture, shaking off any excess.
Arrange in one layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake 1 hour or until cooked through, turning occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: rhubarb surprise pie
directions: Sift together 1 cup flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter.
Add egg and milk; mix.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate. Arrange rhubarb in pie shell.
Sprinkle with gelatin.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle on top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until rhubarb is tender.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown pork chops in a little bit of shortening. Arrange chops in a 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Lightly toss bread cubes, onion, butter, 1/3 cup water and poultry seasoning. Spoon over pork chops and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, blend soup and 1/3 cup water.
Pour over chops and bake 15 minutes more or until chops are tender.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Tear bread into small pieces.
Place in medium bowl.
Add milk and soak for 5 minutes.
Add ground round, onions, salt, egg, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon allspice.
Mix ingredients well with hands, then shape into balls.
Heat large skillet over medium heat; add meatballs and brown 5 minutes.
Remove to bowl.
Add broth to skillet; stir to combine brown particles and broth; heat through. Add remaining 1/4 teaspoon allspice, yogurt and sour cream.
Mix well.
Put meatballs back into skillet and heat on low for 5 minutes.
Do not boil.
Makes 38 to 40 meatballs.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: honey graham special
directions: Make chocolate pudding.
Whip the cream; add sugar and vanilla.
Layer graham crackers and pudding until about 6 layers high.
Frost the top and sides with whipped cream.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken.
Debone and cup up.
Cook carrots.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Add chicken, carrots, green peas to chicken broth.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Mix well.
Add cooked noodles.
Add salt, pepper and thyme to taste.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and garlic.
Drain.
Cool.
Stir in Mozzarella cheese, bread crumbs, egg, parsley, salt and pepper. Cook shells and drain.
Stuff shells with meat mixture.
Spoon 1/4 of the sauce in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Place shells on top, pour rest of sauce over shells.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: amish broccoli cheese soup
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan/Dutch oven.
Add onion and garlic or garlic powder and cook until tender.
Add broccoli and mix well.
Sprinkle with flour and cook, stirring frequently, several minutes.
Blend in chicken broth and bring to a simmer. Break linguine into short lengths and add.
Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes on very low heat until noodles are tender, stirring frequently.
Stir in milk and pepper.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Add cheese.
Turn off heat.
Let stand a few minutes and stir well before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: baked squash
directions: Slice squash; boil in salted water until done.
Drain and mash.
Saute onion, cream and crackers in butter.
Add to cooked squash and eggs; pour into greased casserole.
Top with dots of butter and a few bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour, or until firm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken breasts in 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over chicken; bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes. Place rice, vegetables and 1/2 can onions around and under chicken.
Combine bouillon and Italian seasoning; pour over chicken and vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, at 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions, bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Let stand 5minutes before serving.

title: pignolata(honey balls)
directions: Place flour in bowl; make well in center and crack eggs into flour.
Mix well working dough with hands until smooth.
Roll dough out to about 1/8-inch.
Cut the dough into long strips.
Cut the strips into 1-inch diagonal pieces.
Fry pieces of dough in vegetable oil.
Pieces should be placed one at a time so as not to stick to each other.
After all dough has been fried, it is time to cook them in honey.
Heat (low-medium) honey in saucepan until it starts to bubble.
Place fried dough into the honey and stir, coating all pieces (about 5 minutes).
Spoon into paper cupcake wrappers and let cool.
May garnish with colored sprinkles.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, brown sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Using a medium size bowl, beat melted butter into the sweet potatoes.
Add the dry ingredients, stirring in a little at a time alternately with the buttermilk.
Mix just enough to moisten dough to form into a ball.
Turn out on a lightly floured board.
Pat top side with flour as well, since it is a rather sticky batter.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness with a floured rolling pin.
Cut with a floured biscuit cutter.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Combine baking mix, milk, garlic powder, parsley and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat 30 seconds. Drop dough by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Brush with butter before removing from cookie sheet.

title: funny pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar and cocoa; add hot water and vanilla.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Cream 1 1/2 cups sugar and shortening in mixing bowl.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour into pie crusts.
Pour cocoa mixture in pie crusts. As pie bakes mixture goes to bottom.
Bake at 350°
for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken with olives
directions: Skin chicken.
