In a large skillet cook chicken in hot oil over medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until chicken is lightly browned, turning to brown evenly.
Remove chicken; set aside

title: p.p.l.p.  casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Brown hamburg in frying pan.
Mix 1 can water with 1 can tomato soup; drain noodles and layer on bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Drain browned hamburg and put over noodles.
Drain green beans; put over hamburg.
Lastly, cover with French fried onion rings.
Pour tomato soup over all.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove casserole from oven; add slices of cheese.
Bake for another 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Heat cheese and butter until soft enough to combine.
Add vanilla.
Combine cocoa and powdered sugar.
Add liquid mixture to the dry mixture.
Stir and knead until thoroughly mixed.
Spread in large buttered pan and allow to cool and become firm.
Cut. Yields 6 pounds; recipe may be halved.

title: butter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup warm water.
Mix together light butter and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add yeast mixture, plus 1/2 cup warm water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and sifted bread flour.
Mix all ingredients well.
Let sit in greased, covered bowl in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out like biscuits and cut.
Let rise at room temperature about 2 1/2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: joy juice
directions: Mix all juices together (except Sprite) and put in a large plastic ice cream container(s).
Freeze.
Several hours before serving, take out the containers and let them thaw some.
Crush and add Sprite.
Serve as a "slush."

title: cheesy macaroni bake
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spray a 6 cup shallow baking dish with nonstick spray.
Cut the Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella into 1/4-inch cubes.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Lightly salt and pepper chicken.
Brown slowly in butter using heavy skillet.
Remove breast and arrange skin side up on baking dish.
Add soup to skillet drippings and slowly stir in Sauterne. When smooth, add remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Pour sauce over chicken; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with white rice (4 to 6 servings).

title: kasutera(japanese honey cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, honey and sugar until very thick.
Add flour, beating well.
Pour into a greased oblong 9 x 12-inch baking pan and bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until cake tester inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan.
Serve cut into strips and dusted with confectioners sugar.
Serves 6.

title: southwestern beans
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together oil, vinegar, chili powder, salt, black powder and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients and gently toss to mix well. Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: easy cheesy chicken bake
directions: Combine soups and tomatoes.
Add chicken.
Put the crushed corn chips in the bottom of a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Pour chicken and soup mixture over chips.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted (about 30 to 40 minutes).
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: orange dessert
directions: Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool completely.

title: christmas punch
directions: Blend cranberry juice, sugar, fruit juices and almond extract to combine.
Refrigerate covered until serving time.
Just before serving, stir in 7-Up and sherbet.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream margarine or butter, shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and fold in small amounts at a time.
Blend in lemon juice, lemon rind and coconut. Bake in greased and floured 10 inch tube pan at 350 degrees about 45 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except sugar-cinnamon.
Mix with spoon as dough will be very stiff.
Grease two loaf pans; sprinkle part cinnamon-sugar mixture in bottom of pan and add dough equally to pans.
Sprinkle remaining sugar-cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool; wrap in foil.
Store 2 to 3 days before using. Freezes very well.

title: cheese spread
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Add more mayonnaise if needed.

title: broiled coconut icing
directions: Combine butter, sugar and milk in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil on "high".
Remove from stove; add coconut.
Pour over a warm cake.
Spread evenly.
Place cake on rack on 4th from bottom. Turn control to "broil".
Broil slowly until a golden brown, about 2 or 3 minutes.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together; the batter will be very thick. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch square pan.

title: apple snaps(sugar-free)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Mix in applesauce and cinnamon. Pour into dessert dishes. Chill.

title: mild bear chili
directions: Brown meat with onions and green peppers.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer on low heat for 1/2 hour.
Serves 4 to 6. Preparation Time:
1 hour.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Combine ingredients in large salad bowl and toss with Poppy Seed Dressing.

title: eggs day ahead
directions: Scramble eggs with milk and 1/2 of butter.
Saute mushrooms in remaining butter.

Mix soup and sherry, heat in small pan.	Put eggs in 9 x 13 baker, cover with meat, mushrooms and soup mixture. Sprinkle with cheese, cover with foil and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 250 for 50 minutes uncovered.
Serves 10-12.

title: beef jerky
directions: Trim off fat.
Semi-freeze meat and slice with the grain, making strips approximately 2 inches long and 1/2 inch thick. Place meat in shallow baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over meat.
Marinate overnight.

title: baked macaroni and cheese*
directions: Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Melt butter.
Add flour and when smooth add milk and cook until thickened.
Add grated cheese and seasonings and mix with macaroni.
Pour into greased baking dish; dot top with butter (buttered crumbs or cheese, if desired) and bake.
Temperature:
Time:
20 to 30 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Stir eggs and sugar together.
In separate bowl, mix flour, cinnamon, soda, salt, oil and vanilla.
Add to egg and sugar mixture.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Using rolling pin, crush the cereal to measure about 1/4 cup. Combine with the 2 tablespoons flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar in a small bowl.
Add margarine, mixing until crumbly. Divide chopped apples between greased 6 ounce custard cups.
Sprinkle with the 1 teaspoon flour.
Sprinkle cereal mixture evenly over top. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown. Serve with half and half or ice cream.
Makes 2 servings.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix together; pour 1/2 of the batter into greased Bundt pan. Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon brown sugar on top of batter.
Pour remaining batter into pan and top with 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/2 teaspoon brown sugar.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Be sure to preheat oven.

title: rotel chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken breasts; remove chicken from broth.
Debone and chop.
Cook spaghetti with chicken broth until tender; drain. Saute pepper, onion and celery in butter.
Cube cheese in bowl; add Ro-Tel and stir.
Place in microwave oven and heat just until cheese mixture is melted and can be well blended.
Mix chopped chicken, spaghetti, sauteed vegetables and cheese mixture and place in large casserole dish.
Bake in oven just until cheese is melted and mixture is hot.
Do not overcook or brown to prevent dryness.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla and beat thoroughly.
Add milk, blending well.
Stir in flour and mix all well.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
You may add nuts, if desired.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: In a medium size casserole dish, pour in pineapple chunks with 1/2 juice drained.
Mix sugar and cornstarch together and pour over pineapple.
Place grated cheese over sugar; top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Place pats of butter on crackers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until bubbling.

title: german chocolate pies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
If desired, pies may be topped with Cool Whip or whipping cream.

title: chocolate pudding fudge(made with chocolate pudding)
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients except peanuts.
When this comes to a boil, lower heat and boil for 5 minutes, then add peanuts and beat.
Spoon out on aluminum foil or wax paper.
Put in refrigerator until set.
Yields 18 pieces.

title: candy bar fudge
directions: *Any flavor candy bar may be used.

title: jalapeno black-eyed pea dip
directions: Place chilies, jalapenos, 1 tablespoon jalapeno juice, onion and garlic cloves in blender.
Puree.
Place this mixture into a large saucepan.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Mix all together and fry in oil.
Serve with tartar sauce, catsup and lettuce.

title: angel whip
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Reserve 1/3 of the mixture.
Add 1 box of the dry jello into it, blending with a whisk.
Alternate layers in the cake pan, 1/3 white, 1/3 jello, 1/3 white.
Bake as directed.
Cool completely.
Mix 1 cup of hot water with one box of jello.
Chill and allow to almost set.
Blend into the Cool Whip using it to frost the cake.
Refrigerate.

title: pickle wraps
directions: Trim edges off bread; spread cream cheese on one side of bread.
Roll up with pickle.
Wrap with plastic wrap.
Chill until firm.
Slice in thin slices.
Serve on crackers.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; save juice.
Cook sugar, juice, flour, egg and vinegar until thickened.
Cool thoroughly.
Combine pineapple, marshmallows, peanuts and apples.
Combine Cool Whip with cooked mixture and coat apple mixture.
Chill.

title: chicken & dumplings
directions: Stew a large, fat fryer or hen until tender.
For dumplings, dip out 2 cups broth and cool until lukewarm, add beaten egg and salt to taste.
Beat in enough flour until just stiff enough to roll out.
Cut in strips and drop into boiling broth.
If not rich enough, add 1 can cream of chicken soup.

title: quick and easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Mix all ingredients together. Heat until begins to boil. Serve with corn bread or crackers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together in medium mixing bowl; place in the freezer for 30 minutes.
Shape into ball and roll in almond slices.
Place in the refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers or your favorite party toast.

title: porketa
directions: Debone meat and remove outside fat.
Fill with a mixture of the next 7 ingredients.
Roll roast jelly-roll fashion and tie with a string.
Rub outside of roast with mixture of last three ingredients.
Roast in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes per pound or to an internal temperature of 170°.
Allow roast to stand for 15 minutes for easier carving.
Slice and serve on hard rolls.

title: rice oriental
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients
together in frypan.
In 2 1/2 to 3-quart covered casserole, dissolve hot water and soup mix.
Add rice, pimento and mushrooms and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add almonds if desired.
Serve with soy sauce at table.

title: health bread
directions: Sift flours with baking soda and salt. Mix liquid ingredients in separate bowl. Pour into dry ingredients. Fold in nuts and raisins. Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 1 loaf.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in ovenproof dish.
Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine until course.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: fish stew
directions: Place in casserole.
Add cream of celery or cream of mushroom soup.
If thawed, bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
If frozen, bake at 500° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: classic macaroni salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 6 ingredients until smooth. Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover and chill. Makes 5 cups.

title: buddig pinwheels
directions: Blend cream cheese, onion, horseradish and Worcestershire sauce until of spreading consistency.
Separate Buddig meat slices.
Lay out five slices, slightly overlapping on an 18-inch piece of aluminum foil.
Lay out two more rows to form a rectangle of Buddig meat.
Spread with cheese mixture.
Roll up as jelly roll, using foil to bring up meat at beginning of roll.
Use fingers to roll until complete.
Chill.
Just before serving, slice into 1-inch slices.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix softened margarine with the condensed milk; work in sugar. Add coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Place in refrigerator 20 to 30 minutes, then shape into small balls.
Or press onto cookie sheets and chill.
Then cut into small squares or rectangles.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Cut off tops of peppers; remove seed and membranes.
Precook pepper cups in boiling salted water about 5 minutes.
Drain. Sprinkle inside cups with salt.
Cook beef and onion until meat is lightly browned.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes, water, rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Stuff peppers. Stand upright in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all items until creamy.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake until the pies are brown.

title: hot sauce meatballs
directions: Mix meatball ingredients and roll into small balls.
Bring ketchup to a boil.
Add meatballs. Simmer, covered, 8 to 12 minutes.

title: wet burritos
directions: Fry hamburger and onions; drain.
Add taco seasoning and water; simmer 10 minutes.
Add enchilada sauce and soup; simmer 10 minutes more.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, spoon mixture into tortillas. Roll and insert toothpick to hold in place.
Reserve some mixture for top of rolled tortillas.
Top with cheese.
Place in warm oven or microwave until cheese melts and warmed through.
Serves 6. May top with sour cream, lettuce, tomato, etc.

title: oriental stuffed trout
directions: Stir-fry the vegetables in a wok (or large skillet).
Add eggs and soy sauce.
Cook until eggs begin to coagulate.
Stuff the trout with this mixture and wrap each fish with 2 bacon strips. Bake in a large baking dish at 500°, until skin is crisp (about 20 minutes).

title: sour cream velvet frosting
directions: Melt chips and butter over hot (not boiling) water.
Remove from hot water and blend in sour cream, vanilla and salt. Gradually beat in enough sugar to make a frosting of correct spreading consistency.
Will cover a 9 x 13-inch cake.

title: seven layered salad
directions: Run hot water over peas and drain.
Fry bacon crisp and cut into small pieces.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook the rhubarb in water.
Stir in sugar and Jell-O while hot. Remove from heat.
Add applesauce and pineapple. Pour in mold and let set overnight.

title: spaghetti pie* * * * * *
directions: Chicken will fry more crispy if a little baking powder is added to flour or dip to roll in and brown quicker if a little paprika is added.

title: meat ball
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and roll into ball.
Take the cream cheese and spread over ball sides.
Roll in chives or nuts (optional).
Spread on crackers and enjoy.

title: sweet-n-sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice; set aside.
Bone chicken breasts and cut meat into slivers; saute in butter until no longer pink.
Add bouillon and carrots; cover and cook until carrots are tender.
Combine reserved pineapple juice, brown sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and soy sauce; add to chicken and carrots and cook until mixture thickens.
Just before serving, add pineapple, onion, green pepper and water chestnuts.
Cook just until heated. Serve over hot rice.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Line bottom of Pyrex dish with bacon.
Pour box of rice on top of bacon.
Place the chicken breasts on top of rice.
Mix can of golden mushroom soup with 3/4 cup of water.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle herbs and seasoning mix on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: orange-ginger marinated swordfish steaks
directions: Arrange fish in a large shallow dish.
Combine barbecue sauce and next 6 ingredients; pour over fish.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 24 hours, turning occasionally.
Remove fish from marinade, discarding marinade.
Place fish in grill baskets that have been coated with cooking spray.
Cook, covered with grill
lid, over medium coals (300° to 350°), 7 to 10 minutes on each side. Garnish, if desired, and serve immediately.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine and beat for 2 minutes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Sift flour, measure and resift 3 times, the last time sifting with the sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add shortening and 1/2 cup of the two milks combined.
Beat with electric mixer for 2 minutes on low speed. Scrape batter from the sides.
Add remaining 1/4 cup combined milks, egg whites and vanilla.
Beat for 2 minutes more.
Turn into 2 (8-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes before turning out.
When cool, spread with icing and sprinkle coconut over the top.

title: ham on the grill
directions: Take your favorite boneless ham; score top of the ham with a knife.
Add a few whole cloves to the ham.
Make a paste of brown sugar and mustard and spread over the ham.
Heat up your coals and bank in grill.
Place ham on grid and cover grill for 9 minutes per pound.
Cool for 5 to 10 minutes and slice to desired thickness.

title: chocolate-cheese cups
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in container of an electric blender; blend on high until smooth.
Pour into large bowl; set aside.

title: almond pound cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add flour, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Turn oven off and let stay for 15 minutes.

title: peach cobbler supreme
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Set aside until syrup forms.
Bring peach mixture to a boil; reduce heat to low and cook 10 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat; add flavoring and butter.
Stir until butter melts.

title: beef and pepper rice skillet
directions: Brown beef in oil in a 10-inch skillet.
Stir in onion, rice, beef broth, water and soy sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and cook over low heat until liquid is absorbed, about 25 minutes.
Stir in green pepper.
Heat through.

title: champagne turkey
directions: Mix together salt, black pepper and celery salt and rub inside and out of turkey.
Loosen skin from
breast
and	rub with soft butter.
Roast for 30 minutes at 425°.
Mix together onions, thyme, consomme, parsley and flour.
Pour over turkey. Reduce oven to 325°.
Roast for 1 hour.
Pour
champagne
over turkey.	Baste every 30 minutes until done, about 2 1/2 hours.

title: spiced hot tea
directions: Combine all and heat to serving temperature.

title: fruit salad
directions: Prepare sauce first; dissolve cornstarch in water and set aside.
Combine pineapple juice, butter, lemon juice and sugar in saucepan, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat until it comes to a slow boil.
Add cornstarch and cook until mix coats a spoon.
Cool completely in refrigerator.
Mix with mayonnaise.

title: almond chicken(casserole or crepe filling)
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove skin and bones and cut into chunks.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Good as cold chicken salad or baked in casserole dish (350° for 20 to 25 minutes) as hot chicken dish.
Or place heaping teaspoons in each crepe and roll.
Place crepes on baking pan and bake in 350° oven 10 to 12 minutes until hot and golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: sausage balls
directions: Grate the cheese.
Mix ingredients together.
Mixture will be dry until thoroughly mixed.
Shape into balls the size of small walnuts.
Bake on cookie sheet 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain on paper towels if necessary.

title: sweet and sour chicken wings
directions: Remove wing tips. Separate wings at joint.
Place in large rectangular casserole dish. Mix ketchup, tomato sauce, seasonings and sugars.
Pour over wings.
Bake uncovered for 2 hours at 350°.

title: microwave salsa and cream cheese dip
directions: In blender, whirl 1/4 cup granulated sugar at a time at highest speed for a full 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, stopping your blender periodically to push the powdered sugar off the container walls. If you're using a food processor, whirl 1/2 to 1 cup of sugar at a time until powdered.

title: french vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl at medium-high speed of an electric mixer for 1 minute.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add sweetened condensed milk, pudding mix and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in 1 quart of milk.
Pour mixture into freezer can of a 5-quart hand crank or electric freezer.
Add remaining milk.
Freeze mixture. Let ripen at least 1 hour.
Yields about 4 quarts.

title: veal parmigiana with spinach noodles
directions: In large bowl, combine cracker crumbs, 3/4 ounce Parmesan cheese and the pepper, mixing well.
Dip one veal cutlet into egg, then dredge in cracker mixture, coating tall sides.
Transfer to plate.
Repeat with remaining cutlets, coating evenly.
In 12-inch nonstick skillet, combine 2 teaspoons margarine and the oil and heat over medium-high heat until margarine is bubbly and hot.
Add veal and cook, turning once, until lightly browned, 1 to 2 minutes on each side.
Remove to plate and set aside.

title: stove top ground meat casserole
directions: Mix all into frying pan.
Cook until onion, celery and pepper are crisp.
Season to taste.
Stir in macaroni and cheese.
Add just enough to keep moist.

title: mushroom frittata
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions, green pepper, zucchini and garlic in oil until crisp-tender.
Beat eggs
with cream, salt and pepper; add mushroom mixture, bread cubes, cream cheese and Cheddar.
Stir thoroughly, but lightly, so cream cheese cubes are intact.
Pour into well-greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set in center and brown.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: rock fish - grilled
directions: Clean fish, leaving scales and cut into fillets.
Leave bone in.
Bring to a boil the lemon juice, water, red pepper, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and butter; set aside.
Grill fish on charcoal until flaky on scale side first.
Turn; brown meat side and turn back to scale other side.
When 1/2 done, brush all of sauce on.
Serve hot.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed.
Pour into 9 x 16-inch ungreased pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for one hour.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: The vegetables will be placed in layers in flat Pyrex dish, 9 x 12-inch.

title: apple roll
directions: Divide dough into 3 equal parts and roll each part to 1/8 inch thick on floured board. Spread applesauce on each part. Dot with oleo and sprinkle with sugar. Then roll each part like a jelly roll and lay length-wise in baking dish.
Pour half and half milk over rolls. Dot with oleo and sprinkle with remaining sugar. Bake at 350° until brown; about 45 minutes.

title: crunchy almond bark
directions: Melt almond bark; add remaining ingredients and stir well. Spread on cookie sheet and cut into squares when firm.

title: punch
directions: Boil sugar with water about 5 minutes.
Dissolve 2 packages jello in this syrup.
Add pineapple juice, lemon juice and almond flavoring.
Mix all together thoroughly.
Place in refrigerator. About 1 hour before serving, mix one part mixture to one part water.
Chill.
When put in punch bowl, add one part ginger ale or 7-Up.
Serves 75.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil.
Add clear jell mixture and bring to a boil again.
You might have to add more or less clear jell until it's nice and thick.
Put in jars and seal.

title: rocky-road cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put flour, sugar, cocoa, salt and pecans into ungreased 8-inch square baking pan.
Stir with fork until blended.
Add oil and eggs; stir to mix well.
With rubber spatula, scrape any ingredients clinging to sides, corners and bottom of pan into batter.
Bake 15 minutes or until top feels firm.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and return to oven.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until marshmallows have softened.
Cool in pan on rack; cut into bars.

title: three cheese dip
directions: Combine cheeses; let come to room temperature.
Beat with mixture until smooth and creamy.
Add remaining ingredients, beat until fluffy.
Chill.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix with a fork until all dry ingredients are taken up into a crumbly mixture.
Pour into potato mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick apple strudel
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening and add milk to make a soft dough.
Toss onto floured board and knead gently.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and brush with melted butter or margarine.
Cover with chopped apples and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll as for jelly roll and shape into large crescent on greased baking sheet.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
While still warm, frost with confectioners sugar frosting and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Yields 12 (1-inch) slices.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream together butter and sugar; blend in milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, chopped cherries and chopped pecans.
Form dough into two 8-inch rolls.
Roll in flaked coconut to coat outside.
Wrap in waxed paper or clear plastic wrap. Chill thoroughly.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until edges are golden, about 12 minutes.
Makes about 60 cookies.

title: spam and tater casserole
directions: Layer bottom of dish with sliced potatoes, then 1 layer of sliced onions, 1 more layer of potatoes.
Heat 2 cans soup; add 1/4 can water.
Pour over potatoes.
Slice Spam and lay over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon cake mix
directions: To lemon cake mix, add drained pineapple and instant pudding. Fold together with a wooden spoon.
Add apples and nuts (if desired).
Bake at 350° in a round pudding pan or pound cake pan until brown, soft and delicious.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and nuts. Chill.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake until set, but not brown (10 to 12 minutes) at 400°.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans well.
Put salad mixture in a low flat dish so the liquid will
get
into
the
beans.
This salad is best made the day
before serving and will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: bubble bread
directions: Mix melted margarine and brown sugar and spread in bottom of Bundt pan.
Melt 1 stick margarine.
Combine sugar and cinnamon and place in separate bowl.
Tear thawed bread dough in pieces to form balls.
Dip into margarine and then into sugar.
Layer in pan in uneven rows.
Let rise for 2 hours.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Trim asparagus and green beans.
Cut peppers into strips.
Pare carrots and sweet potato and cut into bite size pieces.
Drizzle with olive oil, salt and pepper.
Bake in large roasting pan, turning occasionally about 30 minutes.

title: cherry crumb
directions: Blend topping ingredients together until crumbly.
Put cherry pie filling in a buttered baking dish.
Top with the crumb topping.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Add sugar and lightly beaten eggs to milk.
Beat until smooth. Bake until set firm.
Egg whites may be left out and used in meringue.

title: spinach artichoke dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly brown. Serve with tortilla chips or crackers. Makes 2 cups.

title: oatmeal raisin spice cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat Crisco and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Combine flour, spices, soda and salt. Mix well.
Stir in oats and mix well.
Drop by tablespoons on baking sheet and bake 12 to 13 minutes or until brown.

title: lemon-garlic green beans
directions: Cook beans in 1-inch water for 8 minutes over medium heat covered.
Cut zest from lemon rind and cut into 1/8-inch strips. Squeeze lemon juice and set juice and rind aside.
Saute oil and garlic in pan for 1 minute.
Add beans and coat with oil/garlic mixture.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake in preheated oven at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
It will be moist inside when done.
Bake in a large Pyrex dish.
Makes 15 large squares.

title: sour cream nut cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg whites.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake in layers at 350° until done.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: Grind the pecans in a food processor. Combine ground pecans, graham cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and melted margarine in a bowl and blend well.
Press the mixture onto the bottom and sides of a greased 9-inch spring-form pan. Chill in the freezer while preparing the filling.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix taco seasoning with 1 cup water and simmer until most of water is evaporated. Mix beans in beef. Spread mixture into large pan.
Spread sour cream on top beef mixture.
Put lettuce on top of sour cream, tomatoes, green onions and cheese.
Serve with corn chips.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: In saucepan, heat milk, Velveeta and margarine until melted. Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread partially thawed potatoes in dish.
Pour milk, Velveeta and margarine mixture over potatoes. Cover and set overnight in refrigerator.
Do not stir.
Before baking, sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Add and stir in cornflakes.
Put by teaspoonful on waxed paper.

title: beef stew
directions: In a 4-quart pot, melt 1 tablespoon butter over medium heat with no lid.
Place beef cubes in and braise meat until all juices are cooked out (takes about 10 to 15 minutes).
Let beef cubes cook until bottom of pan has brown crusty bits (this helps make the gravy).
Add 2 cups water (or until meat is covered with water).
Add chopped onions. Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except Jiffy mix; then add Jiffy. Bake at 350° for about 60 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: In 4-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot butter, cook onions and sugar for 10 minutes. Stir in flour until well blended with onions and pan juices.
Add water, wine and undiluted beef broth and heat to boiling.

Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Cut 4 (1-inch thick) slices of bread from loaf. Save remaining bread to eat with soup. Toast the bread slices in a 325° oven until lightly browned, about 10 minutes.
Ladle soup into 4 (12 ounce) oven-safe bowls and place 1 slice toasted bread on surface of soup in each bowl.
Fold Swiss cheese slices and fit onto toasted bread slices in soup.
Place soup bowls on jelly-roll pan for easier handling.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes or just until cheese is melted.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage in water 15 minutes.
Mix soup and milk together. Layer cabbage and stuffing in 3 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour soup over it.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: speedy caramel frosting
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Blend in brown sugar and salt. Cook over low heat 2 minutes, stirring.
Add milk; continue stirring until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and blend in confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Thin with water if too thick or add more sugar if too thin.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and mince or chop finely; mix all ingredients together and cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken in peanut sauce(this is a microwave recipe)
directions: Remove any fat from chicken.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Combine onion, garlic and butter in covered microwave-safe casserole dish; microwave on High for 3 minutes. Stir in peanut butter, stock, honey, mustard, curry powder, cardamom and Tabasco.
Add chicken pieces.
Stir well.
Microwave on High 6 minutes.
Stir; microwave on High another 6 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: m. y. f. pound cake
directions: With electric mixer, cream margarine well.
Add powdered sugar and beat well.
Next, add eggs, one at a time, and beat well again.
Finally, add flour, vanilla and flavoring, mixing well. Line bottom of tube pan with wax paper, well-greased.
Bake at 325° until done, about 1 hour for a large cake, or divide batter and make 2 loaf cakes.

title: peach delight
directions: Melt butter, add sugar and peaches.
Heat.
Mix flour and milk.
Pour over peach mixture and bake 1 hour at 350° in 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Serve warm with Cool Whip.

title: zesty mozzarella chicken
directions: In bowl, combine egg whites and milk.
In other bowl, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and spices.
Dip each breast in egg white mixture, then in crumbs.
Melt butter in skillet.
Brown chicken on both sides until no longer pink and juices run clear.

title: buried treasure muffins
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Put
paper muffin cups inside muffin pans.
Mix
together
the	flour,	quick
oats, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Dig a hole in the middle.
In another bowl, break
the egg and mix it with milk and oil.
Add liquid mixture to	dry
mixture and stir.	Fill muffin cup half way; then	put teaspoon
of
blueberries
in the middle and then a teaspoon
more of butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 18 to 20 muffins.

title: cheese dollars
directions: Mix well.
Roll out and form into small balls.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: herb seasoned chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix; drizzle with butter.
Pour orange juice over chicken; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve over rice with Sweet Orange Sauce.

title: fran's homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Put Olive Oil and Butter in Skillet
and heat.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix with Miracle Whip to taste. Garnish with olives and pickle.

title: skillet noodles and peas
directions: Heat oil and margarine.
Add cooked noodles to oil.
Add onions.
Brown noodles then add broth and milk.
Add frozen peas. Cook 15 minutes.

title: chewy fudge squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir the first 3 ingredients until well blended.
Mixture will be stiff.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in pan.
May have to use your hands to press mixture into pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: meggy leves (cherry soup)
directions: Bring to boil the cherries, water and spices.
Add sugar to taste according to the sweetness of the cherries.
(I start with 1/2 cup of sugar and add an additional 1/2 cup if cherries are unpitted or tart.)
Boil cherries for 20 minutes or until tender. When done, blend flour and milk; add to cherry mixture while boiling, just long enough to mix.
Serve cold.

title: banana split cake
directions: Cut up 1 quart or more of apple slices and put into casserole dish. Sprinkle a little lemon juice over them. Mix the following ingredients and sprinkle over top of apples.

title: pork sausage brunch
directions: Place bread, sausage and cheese in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with eggs, milk, onion, soup,
mushrooms and pepper.
Place covered pan in refrigerator overnight.
Bake one hour at 350°; uncover and brown top.

title: pasta verde
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil.
Add damp spinach, cover.
When spinach wilts, but is still green, puree with other ingredients. Toss with your favorite pasta.
Garnish with cheese and nuts.

title: pineapple supreme
directions: Melt margarine in a baking dish.
Sprinkle in pretzels; then add 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Cream the cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar.
Drain pineapple mixture into Dream Whip and pour over pretzels. Refrigerate.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Spread filling in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over filling.
Drizzle melted margarine over the cake mix. Sprinkle on nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix and bake in greased loaf pan (1 - 9 x 5 loaf or 2 small loaves).
Bake at 300 to 325 degrees until brown.

title: mississippi dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix together well.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cream of broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in 6 cups water for 20 minutes.
Stir to break vegetables into smaller pieces.
Add cream of chicken soup and Velveeta cheese.
Simmer and serve.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter together.
Add sugars and cream.
Beat egg and blend into creamed ingredients.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Chill dough well.
Form into balls; flatten with fork dipped in flour.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375° on lightly greased cookie sheet.

title: buckeyes
directions: Cream together margarine, powdered sugar, graham cracker crumbs and peanut butter.
Will be stiff.
Roll in 1-inch balls. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate.
Use toothpick.
Place on wax paper on cookie sheet.
Cool and transfer to tight container.
Refrigerate. (Will keep for weeks.)

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix other 3 ingredients until crumbly.
Spread over peaches.
Bake at 300° until golden brown.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a pan.
Add stuffing mix.
Set aside a few tablespoons of this mixture.
In a separate bowl, mix the soup and sour cream.
In an 8x8 inch pan, put a layer of the stuffing mix, then a layer of the soup mixture, then a layer of sliced zucchini and carrots.
Repeat layers, ending with the soup mixture. Sprinkle the reserved stuffing (or use bread crumbs) on top. Cover and bake at 350° for at least 45 minutes.

title: russian salad dressing
directions: Beat sugar in vinegar until dissolved.
Add catsup, salt and paprika.
Beat well; slowly add oil.
Beat in onion.
Refrigerate. Place mixture in blender and blend until smooth and mixed well.

title: lemon or orange icing
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Add the butter, lemon juice and grated rinds. Beat yolks and add half of mixture to yolks.
Pour back in saucepan and boil 1 minute.

title: lea's corn bread
directions: Heat cast-iron skillet in oven until hot with oil.
Sprinkle small amount corn meal in pan before pouring batter into pan.
Mix ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: jumbo shells
directions: Cook shells as directed, drain and dry in single layer. Combine cheeses, eggs, salt and parsley.
Fill shells with 1 or 2 tablespoons of mixture.
Spread a thin layer of sauce in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place a single layer of shells in dish and cover with part of the sauce.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve with remaining sauce.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; chill until slightly thickened.
Add other ingredients.
Fold in mayonnaise last.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: marshmallow creme
directions: Cook
white sugar, water and light corn syrup to 240 medium-hard ball.
While
this
is
cooking,
place
warm
Karo and egg whites in a mixing bowl.
Beat
slowly until well mixed, then beat hard until light and fluffy.
Pour
the
first mixture into this in a thin stream.
When all is
mixed, beat hard for 3 minutes.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Store in jars.
Cover after it is cold.

title: wonderful blueberry muffins
directions: Cream well the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Mix as though making a cake batter and gently fold in 1 pint fresh blueberries. Fill muffin tins (lined with foil liners).
Sprinkle with granulated sugar before baking.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes. Yields 16 to 18 large muffins.

title: tommy's cracker dessert
directions: Combine crackers and butter.
Press 3/4 of the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve remaining mixture for top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In large saucepan, blend butter and flour.
Add mushroom soup.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in broccoli.
Place in 1 quart casserole baking dish.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Top with cheeses.
Sprinkle on crushed crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cloves, nutmeg and cinnamon together.
Set aside.
Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in pumpkin and blend well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pans.
Cover with foil if you desire a very moist cake.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Use 8-inch glass or porcelain pie plate.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(Makes its own crust.)

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: After chicken is boiled and set aside in the chicken broth, cook 1 can of biscuits, torn off into small pieces, for 10 minutes.
Mix together 1 large tablespoon of cornstarch with 1 cup milk.
Add to broth to thicken.
Double thickener is not enough. Add chicken.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: fried peach pies
directions: Place flour and salt into a large bowl.
Cut butter into flour until it looks like corn meal.
Pour water in and blend with a fork.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Cook dried fruit according to directions on bag.
Roll dough out on a floured surface, small pieces at a time.
Roll to size of a saucer.
Place fruit on 1/2 of rolled-out dough.
Close other part of dough over fruit.
Mash edges together with a fork.
Heat oil in a medium skillet (iron one preferred).
Oil should sizzle when you drop a drop of water in (about 200°).
Fry 2 pies at a time.
Drain on rack.
Sprinkle on powdered sugar.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, crabmeat, onion, milk, horseradish and seasonings.
Mix until well blended.
Spoon into 9-inch pie plate or ovenproof dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with toasted almonds.
Serve as a dip or spread with crackers, chips or raw vegetables.

title: spiced peaches with nutty dumplings
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, 2 tablespoons sugar and pecans; stir well.
Stir in milk and butter flavoring.
Set aside.

title: pineapple-cheery delight
directions: Mix pineapple, Thank You brand cherries and Borden's Eagle Brand milk.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Top with crushed walnuts.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: tyler's broken cookies
directions: Combine the flour, walnuts and sugar.
Cut in the butter until mixture is crumbly.
Quickly stir in the vanilla and chocolate, being careful not to cream mixture.
Press mixture into a 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Cool.
Break into pieces and serve.
Good served with vanilla ice cream.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Peel and devein the shrimp.
Set the shrimp aside.
Put the heads and shells in a pot. Cover with water and boil for 30 to 45 minutes.
Strain liquid and add water to make 6 quarts shrimp stock.

title: sweet corn
directions: Cut corn off cob and scrape cob.
Do not blanche.
Place in heavy pan.
Add oleo and sugar.
Cover with milk.
After it begins to boil, cook for 5 minutes at medium heat.
Stir constantly. Completely cool and place in containers and freeze.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix and bake cake according to directions.
While still slightly warm, poke holes in cake with straw.
Pour over the can of pineapple, juice included.
Mix vanilla pudding using 1 1/2 cups of milk instead of 2 cups.
Fold Cool Whip into pudding Spread over pineapple.
Sprinkle shredded coconut on top. Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Yummy and light.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour all at once and mix by hand.
Pat onto cookie sheet, about 13 x 9-inch. Prick all over with fork.
Bake at 300° for about 45 minutes. Should be a light brown.
Cut into fingers while hot.
Sprinkle liberally with sugar.
Cool and store in an airtight tin.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients well.
Add pineapple with juice and walnuts.
Bake in tube pan sprayed with Baker's Joy.
Bake 1 hour; let stand 15 minutes.
Turn upside down on plate.
Let cool and frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: meringue for pies
directions: Beat egg whites with mixer. Add all other ingredients one at a time. Beat until stiff.

title: champagne sauce
directions: Open cans of broth and scoop hardened fat off top; discard. Simmer broth in saucepan (don't boil).
In another saucepan, heat butter until it gently bubbles, then stir in flour until mixture bubbles.
Add hot broth; stir until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat.
In small pan, heat heavy cream until warm (not hot). Add cream to broth mixture; stir to blend, then stir in champagne.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: *If self-rising flour is used, omit salt, soda and baking powder.

title: magnolia pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Beat in cream cheese and sugar.
Add rind and juice of one lemon.
Pour into two graham cracker crumb crust pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Combine rest of sugar and juice of other lemon with sour cream.
Refrigerate.
Remove pies and cool slightly.
Spread sour cream topping and return to oven for 5 minutes.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sour cream banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg and sour cream; mix thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients, alternately with mashed bananas and lemon juice mixture.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 375°. Yields one 1-pound loaf.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Blend flour, sugar and oleo.
Melt Crisco, cocoa and water and add to blended ingredients.
Add eggs, cinnamon, vanilla, soda and buttermilk.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate layer bars
directions: Combine crumbs and butter in small bowl.
Press into bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Layer peanuts, morsels and coconut over crumb mixture.
Drizzle sweetened condensed milk evenly over top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until coconut is brown.
Cool completely on wire rack.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand 5 to 10 minutes. Before stirring, add 2 cups flour and all other ingredients.
With mixer, blend low for 2 minutes.
Blend in the other 2 cups flour by hand.
Cover; let stand until doubled in bulk, 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir batter down; place in greased muffin tins.
Let rise again, double in size.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: pretzel torte
directions: Crush pretzels to resemble coarse nuts.
I use my blender - chop button.
Melt margarine in pan; mix with sugar and crushed pretzels.
Press mixture in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Save part for topping.
Beat the cream cheese with powdered sugar until fluffy. Fold Cool Whip into cream cheese.
Spread 1/2 of cream cheese mixture on pretzels.
Add 1 can pie filling, then rest of cheese mixture.
Top with remaining crushed pretzels.
Refrigerate overnight.
Delicious.

title: strawberry lover's pie
directions: In a saucepan, melt 2 ounces chocolate and butter over low heat, stirring constantly.
Spread or brush over the bottom and up the sides of pastry shell.
Chill.

title: sour cream pecans
directions: Combine sour cream and sugar.
Cook over medium-low heat to almost hard boil at 242°.
Turn off flame or heat.
Add vanilla, butter and soda.
Beat for 1 or 2 minutes.
Add pecans, stirring to coat.
Turn onto lightly buttered baking sheet.
Cool and separate pecan halves.
Makes 4 cups.

title: finger sandwiches
directions: Crumble bacon as fine as possible.
Mix with cheese.
Spread onto bread (cut after spread is applied).
Garnish with halved Tommy Toe Tomatoes.
Serves 40 to 50.

title: spanish macaroni
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in margarine in skillet until tender.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Cook, stirring, until ground beef is brown and crumbly.
Add soup, cheese and macaroni; mix well.
Place in a baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: crab and shrimp salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce leaf. Serves 4.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and
store in airtight container. To prepare tea, place
heaping teaspoonfuls of the mix in a cup or mug and add boiling water.

title: banana shake
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender until ice is melted.
This has 65 calories per serving.

title: soap bubbles
directions: Mix in advance because it works better after stored awhile.

title: old-fashioned chocolate icing
directions: Bring sugar, butter, milk, cocoa and syrup to a boil (slow). Cook 5 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Cool.
Or, add to sheet cake while cake and icing are hot.

title: crazy crust apple pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar, water, egg and shortening.
Mix well at lowest speed on mixer.
Mix for 2 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into pie pan.
Add filling.
Add lemon juice and cinnamon in center of pie filling.
Don't stir.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Mix the buttermilk, eggs and butter.
Mix dry ingredients with wet ingredients.
Add raisins. Butter a 10-inch (No. 8) frying pan or casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chinese cookies
directions: Heat oil in large skillet or pot until it is hot.
Drop several won ton wrappers in oil at a time; cook until they are golden brown, about 1 minute.
Remove from oil and drain on paper towels.
After draining, sprinkle wrappers with powdered sugar. Serve.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Glaze with the following powdered sugar icing as soon as you remove the cake from the oven.

title: "a a" cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture.
Add chocolate syrup.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage sumi salad
directions: In a large bowl, crush noodles; add slaw mix, onions and sesame seed.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese into cubes; melt and add Ro-Tel.
Brown and drain ground beef or sausage.
Add to cheese and Ro-Tel.
Serve warm as a dip with tortilla chips, crackers or corn chips.

title: play-goop
directions: Put Borax in 1 1/3 cups water.
Put the glue in a separate bowl and mix it with the 1/2 cup water.
Pour Borax mix in and continue stirring until firm.
Add little bits of Borax to make more firm.
Add food coloring and store in airtight container.

title: butter pie
directions: Cream the sugar, flour and butter until it is in small lumps. Add milk and vanilla.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell and bake until it gets crusty on top and kind of brown.

title: weight watchers pimento cheese
directions: Combine all ingredients and and mix well.
Add liquid from jar of pimentos and mix to desired consistency.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine bread crumbs, egg, onions and salt.
Add ground beef, mixing lightly.
Gradually add about half of the tomato sauce just to hold the mixture together.
Mix together lightly, but well. Shape into a loaf in a baking dish.
Pour the rest of the tomato sauce on top of your loaf.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until meat loaf is browned.

title: favorite pancakes
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Combine eggs, milk and salad oil; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: chicken stuffed shells
directions: Brown chicken breasts.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to microwave instructions on the container. Cut chicken into small pieces and mix with Stove Top stuffing and mayonnaise.
Boil the shells. Stuff the jumbo shells with this mixture.
Lay in baking pan in a single layer.
Combine soup and chicken broth and pour over shells. Top with shredded Parmesan cheese, Cheddar cheese or another cheese of your choice.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake 30 to 45 minutes until bubbly at 350°.

title: trash pie
directions: Mix together; pour in graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: oh henry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine oats, sugar, shortening and syrup using a pastry blender.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Spread over baked mixture.
Cool slightly and cut into bars.

title: macaroni and cheese pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box.
When you add the milk, cheese and oleo, add the beaten egg, too.
Press into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Add beef and sausage. Pour the pizza sauce on top of meat.
Then sprinkle on the cheese and return to the oven until cheese is melted.

title: frozen potato casserole
directions: Place frozen potatoes in baking dish or pan. Bake 10 minutes at 400°. Brown hamburger.
Add broccoli, mushrooms and 1/2 can onion rings.
Mix together celery soup, milk and cheese. Add to hamburger. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Just before serving, top with rest of onion rings.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Add all other ingredients except tortillas and picante sauce.
Mix together well. Refrigerate cream cheese mixture for approximately 1 hour, then spread tortillas with cream cheese mixture almost to all outer edges.
Roll tortillas jellyroll style and lay on tray with open edge down.
Refrigerate filled tortillas overnight (for easy slicing).

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll dough and press against bottom and sides of a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan to form crust.
Pinch perforations to seal.
Bake in 375° oven for 13 minutes; cool.
Beat together cream cheese, salad dressing and seasoning; spread over crust.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Cut into rectangles.
Makes 25 servings.

title: broccoli cheese noodle soup
directions: Cut broccoli into bite-sized pieces.
Saute onion in oil and set aside.
Add bouillon to boiling water.
Add noodles.
Cook until almost done.
Add broccoli and cook until done.
Add onion, cheese, milk and seasonings.
Cover and let simmer.

title: pineapple pork
directions: Brown pork in small amount of oil in a large frying pan.
Add water to reserved pineapple juice to make 1 3/4 cups.
Add pepper to pork after about 5 to 10 minutes.
Saute about 5 minutes.
Add juice, salt and pepper to taste and simmer, covered, until pork is tender.

title: aunt mary's sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend in dry ingredients; mix well.
Cover and chill 1 hour or overnight.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll out and cut.
Takes 6 to 8 minutes cooking time.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Wash and scrape carrots and slice into 1-inch pieces. Parboil in enough water to cover carrots. When tender, drain and puree carrots in blender. Combine butter, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour and carrots. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. When done, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown beef in oil until all moisture is absorbed.
Add 3 cups water and bouillon.
While these are cooking, mix cornstarch, water and soy sauce in small bowl and add to skillet mixture. Boil that until clear.
Add celery; cook about 10 minutes or until tender; add pepper and onion; cook for 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: easy rhubarb jam
directions: Cook rhubarb, sugar and water together until tender.
Stir often.
Add raspberry Jell-O.
Stir well.
Then add blueberry pie filling.
Cool.
Keep in refrigerator or freeze.

title: german chocolate caramel cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Melt together caramels, oleo and milk.
Pour 1/2 cake mix into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and pour caramel mixture over baked 1/2 of cake.
Add the rest of the cake batter.
Spread chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake 40 minutes longer.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Cream butter and add sugar. Add eggs (1 at a time), beat.
Add flour, then chocolate and nuts. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Bake in 9 x 9-inch pan (will need 2).

title: candy cookies
directions: Bring sugar, butter, milk and cocoa to a boil.
Boil 1 full minute, then stir in oats until thick.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
If using peanut butter, add with oats.

title: ranch stew supreme
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef. Drain. Add all ingredients in a very large pot. Simmer until most of the day from morning. Serve with garlic, rice, and hot sauce.

title: aunt sheila's no bake birthday cookies
directions: Boil together the first 3 ingredients for 1 minute.
Stir and add the peanut butter, cocoa and vanilla. Stir and add the oats. Stir and drop by teaspoon onto wax paper or greased cookie sheet.

title: pecan dainties
directions: Preheat oven to 325°, after chilling dough.
Combine butter and sugar until light.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Chill, roll into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press pecan half in center and flatten cookie.
Bake for 20 minutes, roll in sugar while warm.
Cool on rack.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: date nut loaf
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder over dates and nuts.
Mix well.
Beat eggs and vanilla and mix well with dry ingredients. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Melt butter and brown onions and garlic.
Add tomatoes and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add diced chicken, soup, cheese and olives.
Add cooked spaghetti and small can peas.
Cook until cheese has melted completely.

title: mexican chicken salad
directions: Stir together.
Serve cold on lettuce-lined plates or bowls.

title: pierogi
directions: Beat eggs, water and salt until well mixed.
Into a large bowl sift the flour.
Add the eggs and water and mix well.
Knead until firm and now let the dough rest in a covered bowl for 10 minutes. Divide the dough in half and roll thin.
Cut circles with a large glass or biscuit cutter.
Now place a small spoonful of filling onto each circle.
Fold over and pinch edges together very firmly. Be sure to do this so that the filling won't come out.
Drop pierogi into a large pot of boiling water to which you add a teaspoon of salt.
Cook gently for 3 to 5 minutes.
Lift out very carefully with a perforated spoon.
Never crowd or heap the pierogi.
The uncooked will stick together.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Combine butter, sugar, egg yolks, and milk.
Cook until thick. Add vanilla.
Cool.
Add pecans and coconut.
Spread on cake.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Mix cream cheese (softened) with Zesty Italian dressing.
Add enough tomato juice for color and spreading.
I use on Town House crackers and celery.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine and refrigerate first four ingredients.
Next day, whip the cream; add sugar and vanilla.
Combine everything; garnish with red cherries if desired.

title: macaroni and cheese(stovetop)
directions: Cook macaroni in hot salt water; drain and add condensed milk and oleo. Bring to boil. Turn off heat and add the desired amount of Velveeta cheese. If too thick, add a little milk.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix into crumbs the flour, oatmeal, brown sugar and butter. Press half the crumbs into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover crumbs with rhubarb.
Add a layer of strawberries if desired. Combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until clear in color. Then pour over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate mousse(france)
directions: Beat yolks and sugar until pale.
Melt chocolate, water and butter together, then add to yolks.
Beat whites with salt until stiff and fold into the chocolate.
Spoon into dishes.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Optional:
Can put avocado dip on it.

title: fudge
directions: Melt chocolate over double boiler.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla, salt and milk. Stir.
(Add nuts.)
Pour into pan.
Chill.

title: wild rice
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add onion, oregano and rice. Brown slightly.
Add liquid and mushrooms and pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: boiled corn and salt meat
directions: Cut salt meat into chunks.
Boil until tender, about 1 hour. Drop corn in with salt meat and boil until corn is tender.
Serve chunks of meat with corn.
Rub meat on corn and eat both.
Meat is not necessary to use.
Butter or salt; good with sliced tomatoes.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, salt to taste and drain grease.
Add sour cream and soup.
Layer in dish:
tortilla shells, meat mixture, tortillas shells, meat mixture and tortilla shells, then add Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Heat the milk hot. Add to the Grape-Nuts, then sugar and egg. Bake in slow oven 30 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail jello(salad)
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over fruit cocktail and let stand overnight.
Next morning, add the remaining ingredients. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: poppy cock
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt in heavy saucepan; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring 5 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour mixture over corn and nuts; quickly stir until well coated.
Pour mixture into 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Bake at 250° until dry, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 20 minutes. Remove from oven; spread apart if necessary.
Store airtight. Makes 5 1/2 quarts.

title: chili
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook 6 hours in slow cooker or crock-pot on low to medium setting.
(Good served over nacho chips and sprinkled with cheese.)

title: togetherness
directions: Coming together is business.

title: tomato pie
directions: Fill cooled pie shell with alternating layers of
tomatoes and onions sprinkled with salt, pepper, basil and chives. Combine mayo and cheese and spread over tomatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix 2/3 cup flour with blueberries; let stand for 1 hour. Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Sift remaining 2 cups flour with salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk.
Add floured blueberries.
Pour into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well, being sugar sugar is dissolved and Marshmallow Creme is well blended (may be put in the blender, small amounts at a time).
Pour in ice cream freezer can and finish filling with whole milk to line indicated on can.
Freeze until firm.
Let ripen 1 hour.

title: best pesto
directions: Blend well like paste.
Add almonds and pulse a few times.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat the shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir together dry ingredients; gradually add to shortening mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in mincemeat.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto greased baking sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Garnish as desired.
Makes about 6 1/2 dozen.

title: jan hagel cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together with egg yolk.
Press flat onto greased cookie sheet. Spread with egg white, slightly beaten. Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar with a little cinnamon added over egg white. Top with sliced almonds.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until nicely browned. Cut into squares while warm.
Cookies should be thin and crisp.

title: orange slice bars
directions: Beat eggs; add water and salt.
Add brown sugar and beat again. Mix 1 cup flour with candy; be sure to coat cut sides with flour. Add to egg-sugar mixture along with all remaining ingredients. Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°. Cut into bars while warm.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in microwave on High, until butter is melted, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in marshmallow and peanut butter until smooth.
Put in vanilla and mix.
Pour in buttered pan.
Cool, then cut into squares.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Put broccoli in a small cooking utensil half full of water. Cook until tender.
Do the same with the rice.
Strain both, one at a time and add to bowl (ovenproof).
Mix almost whole jar of Cheez Whiz and about 3/4 can of soup into the bowl.
Add salt, pepper and onion.
Bake about 10 or 15 minutes.
Do not let sides of bowl burn.
Then add enough grated cheese on top to cover it. Broil 5 minutes.

title: wild west chili
directions: Cook ground
beef with onion until brown.
Pour off the liquid.
Add the garlic salt, broth, soup, beans, chili powder and vinegar.
Season
with salt and pepper to suit your taste. Simmer for approximately an hour.

title: chicken in spanish sauce
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large skillet.
Brown chicken on both sides; remove from pan.
Saute onion and garlic in fat left in pan for 3 minutes or until tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Return chicken to pan.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into a ball.
Refrigerate. The tuna ball will freeze well.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble bread in a large bowl.
Melt butter and lightly saute onion and celery.
Add to crumb mixture.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
If dressing seems too dry, add more broth.
Bake in shallow pans at 400° for 15 to 25 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Place half of the ice cream on graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle 1/3 of the brickle over this layer.
Spread remaining ice cream over top.
Sprinkle 1/3 of the brickle over this layer.

title: zucchini salad
directions: Combine lettuce with celery.
Add tomato, zucchini, apple and egg.
Add dressing to taste (Creamy Cucumber or Creamy Italian goes well with this).

title: zucchini cranberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Divide batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: company eggs
directions: Bake biscuits according to package directions.
Split and arrange brown side down in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Brown sausage. Sprinkle partially drained sausage over biscuits.
Beat eggs and cream.
Pour over sausage.
Sprinkle on all cheese.
Beat mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over cheese layer.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook and shred potatoes; cool.
Put potatoes, eggs, onions and celery in a large bowl.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Mix well.
Let set overnight.
It is important that potatoes are shredded, such as shoestring, rather than just cubed.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Cream together butter and powdered sugar.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until cold or can even be put in the freezer. Form to desired size balls and dip them into your favorite chocolate sauce.

title: raspberry cooler
directions: Dissolve drink powders and sugar in water.
Add fruit juices and pineapple; chill through.
Serve in frosted glasses.
(Twirl 1/2 inch of rim in lemon juice, then in granulated sugar.)
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: seafood dip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cream cheese, seafood, onion, horseradish, garlic salt, pepper and hot sauce in a bowl. Mix well.
Spoon into 2-quart buttered baking dish.
Saute pecans in butter in skillet.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake for 25 minutes. Serve warm with crackers.
Yields 16 servings.

title: baked bean stew
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in oil in large saucepan until tender, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add chicken and cook over medium heat until browned, 3 to 4 minutes.
Add beans, tomatoes and herbs to saucepan; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered 8 to 10 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
(This recipe can be used by diabetics.)

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: In a bowl, beat until fluffy.

title: brownies
directions: Put flour with salt.
Cream butter; gradually blend in sugar and add beaten eggs.
Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Add vanilla and stir in melted chocolate.
Add flour mixture alternately in 2 ounce 3 portions, stirring well after each addition. Add nuts with last few stirs.
Spread into 8-inch square cake pan which has been buttered.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove pan from cake rack.
Cut in pieces while warm.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into patties.
Fry or broil as hamburg.
Great on the grill.

title: ida's banana bread
directions: Mix in order.
Mix again.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stir-fried noodles
directions: Cook the noodles as directed on package.
One-third pound dried noodles equals one pound cooked noodles.
Add cornstarch, cooking wine and 1/2 teaspoon of soy sauce to the meat and marinate for 20 minutes.
Tear the spinach into 2-inch pieces.

title: pecan cookie balls
directions: Blend butter with salt and vanilla.
Add sugar gradually; cream well.
Sift in flour.
Add chopped nuts.
Shape dough into little balls slightly larger than a marble.
Place on greased cookie sheet; bake for about 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove from pan and quickly but carefully, roll the hot cookies in sifted powdered sugar.
This forms a frosting-like coating over the cookies.
Cool, then roll again in powdered sugar.
Store in an airtight container.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix instant pie filling with 1 cup fruit juice or 1 can fruit pie filling.
Coat bananas first.
Add rest of drained fruit and refrigerate.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise. Remove yolks. Mash yolks well. Add remaining ingredients to mashed yolks and mix well. Spoon mixture back into egg whites. Sprinkle tops with paprika. Place on serving tray. Garnish with stuffed green olives in center of plate.

title: lo-cal country style cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients well; pour into nonstick square pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cut into 6 servings.

title: pork chops n' brown rice
directions: Brown pork chops on each side.
Place rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Place pork chops on top of rice.
Pour both soups over rice and pork chops.
Add mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry coffee cake(lo-fat)
directions: Blend liquid ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients.
Fold 2 mixtures together and fold in blueberries last.

title: winter salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add juice and water.
When partially set, add the remaining ingredients.
Mold.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, shortening and butter.
Save 1 cup of crumbs.
Stir boiling water with baking soda.
Add molasses.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Place in greased and floured loaf pans (2). Top with 1 cup of crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sauerkraut and tomatoes casserole
directions: Drain sauerkraut well.
Put tomatoes through a strainer. Melt the bacon or other fat.
Add onion and stir until golden brown. Add the strained tomatoes and brown sugar.
Add the drained sauerkraut.
Place the mixture in a covered casserole and bake for 1 hour.
Uncover the last 20 minutes of cooking.
Garnish the top with crumbled crisp bacon.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Make a paste with cornstarch and water.
Add and cook until thick.
Store with lid loose in cool, dry place.
Keeps for 2 months or more.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Layer each ingredient in oblong pan (pineapple, filling, cake mix and margarine, sliced and placed over mix, then pecans).
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lasagna bread
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add tomato paste and seasonings and simmer 5 minutes.
Roll out one can of rolls (8) and place on cookie sheet.
Spread a mixture of cottage cheese, egg and Parmesan cheese over rolls, a layer of meat, then Mozzarella cheese slices.
Top with other can of rolls (rolled out and sealed).
Brush with egg and milk.	Sprinkle with sesame seeds (optional).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Preheat	crust
approximately 15 minutes.
Combine sugar, flour and nutmeg in a
bowl.
Beat in eggs (medium speed) until smooth.
Beat
in buttermilk, butter and vanilla
to blend.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle
top
with pecans and coconut.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until filling is just set. Cool.
Serve at room temperature or chill.

title: spicy sausage and red cabbage
directions: Cook sausage in saucepan, breaking it up as it cooks.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: special salsa verde
directions: Mix together and spoon over warm beans.
Serve immediately or let cool.
This is perfect with grilled fish.

title: sole shrimp roll
directions: Put most of the crushed crackers on bottom of buttered baking dish.
Layer out fillet strips.
Place small shrimp on fillets. Roll fillets and hold with toothpicks.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Dilute soup with small amount of milk.
Pour over fillets.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: dried beef
directions: Brown onion in skillet.
Add dried beef, soup and peas.
Cook a few minutes until peas are done.
(May need to add some water, if necessary.)
Serve in French pastry shells.
Serves 4.

title: caramel custard cups
directions: Set oven at 350° and let warm.
Press 1 tablespoon brown sugar lightly into each of four custard cups.
Mix ingredients in a 1-quart bowl and pour carefully over brown sugar.
Set cups in pan with 1-inch of water.
Bake 50 minutes.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, oil and celery seed in a small pan; bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage, onion and bell pepper.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling over the bottom of an oblong-type greased baking dish, approximately 6 x 11-inches, then spread a can of crushed undrained pineapple over cherry pie filling.
Pour on dry cake mix and scatter nuts over top.
Melt butter and pour over cake mix.
Be sure to cover all mix and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: stars and stripes dessert
directions: This dessert will have the design of the American Flag.
Cut pound cake in pieces 1 1/2 inches thick and line the bottom of an 8 x 12-inch baking dish with enough to cover bottom.
Top with 1 cup each of strawberry slices and blueberries, then with thawed Cool Whip.
Design "Stars and Stripes" - 1/3 cup of blueberries in left corner in rows to symbolize stars and place strawberries in rows, symbolizing "stripes".
A good and pretty dessert for July 4th or other "Flag" holiday.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serves 15.

title: fresh peach snack
directions: Form cream cheese into a log.
Roll in brown sugar until coated.

title: egg in a hole
directions: Cut center out of bread with cookie cutter or glass.
Butter both sides of bread using 1/2 tablespoon butter.
Melt remaining butter in skillet over medium heat.
Brown one side of bread in skillet; turn bread over.
Break egg in small bowl.
Carefully slip it into the hole in the bread slice in the skillet. Sprinkle salt and pepper on egg. Brown egg on both sides and remove from skillet.

title: burger bean bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes.

title: luncheon delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add cream cheese and whip with beater.
Let cool.
Whip the cream.
Add Jell-O mixture to the whipped cream.
Fold in the remaining ingredients. Put in mold and refrigerate.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook elbow macaroni according to the instructions on the box. Melt margarine or butter on the stove.
Remove it from the heat and add flour, mustard, garlic, salt and milk.
Return to the stove with very low heat and stir gently.

title: lebanese rice
directions: Brown the meat in the Crisco; add salt, pepper and cinnamon. Add about 3 cups water; cook until liquid is reduced to 2 cups. Add rice; cook until it boils.
Simmer.
Roast pine nuts, nuts and almonds in Crisco until golden brown.
Set aside.
Serve the rice in an oval flat dish; cover the whole with the roasted nuts. Makes a nice accompaniment to baked chicken or lamb.

title: sweet potato-pineapple rings
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, brown sugar, butter, orange juice, pumpkin pie spice, orange peel, pecans and raisins, mixing well. Drain pineapple slices and place in baking dish.
Mound 1/3 cup of sweet potato mixture on top of each pineapple slice.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, then top with marshmallows and bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cottage fried potatoes
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine.
(If necessary, add additional margarine during cooking.)
Layer potatoes into skillet. Sprinkle with garlic powder, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Cook, covered, over medium heat for 8 minutes.
Add onion rings.
Cook, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes more or until potatoes are tender and browned, turning frequently.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grandma's ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into one big loaf or two small.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart dish.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to coat potatoes.
Cover tightly with Saran Wrap.
Cook at 100% for 10 to 15 minutes shaking dish once to distribute potatoes.
Remove from oven.
Uncover and serve hot.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Take frozen dough, wrap and tie it in a Kroger plastic bag. Let it sit at warm room temperature for 8 hours until dough rises. Once it has risen, open bag and pinch off about a cookie size piece. wrap 5 to 6 pepperoni into dough and tuck and place on baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until lightly browned. Let sit for 1 minute in the pan so the pepperoni juice crusts on the bottom of roll.
Put them into a Tupperware container to keep fresh and warm.
Serve warm.
Serves 12 rolls.

title: party ham salad
directions: Process bologna and cheese in food processor to finely chop pieces.
Add relish to taste and mayonnaise to desired consistency.

title: red devils food cake
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Gradually add 1 c. sugar, creaming together until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla.
