Combine 1/3 c. cold water and cocoa, beat into creamed mixture.
Add flour alternately with 1 c. cold water, beating well after each addition. Beat egg whites till soft peaks form.
Gradually add 3/4 c. sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold meringue into batter. Combine soda and 1/3 c cold water.
Stir to dissolve soda.
Stir into batter.
Mix well.
Bake in 2 paper lined 9 x 1 1/2 inch round pans in moderate oven. 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Mix the crushed corn flakes and melted margarine together and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: squaw corn
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add other ingredients and simmer.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and syrup.
Add eggs, butter, vanilla and nuts. Mix well and pour into uncooked 9-inch pastry-lined pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 400°.
Lower temperature to 300° and cool for 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix the spaghetti, butter, Parmesan cheese and eggs; put in bottom of pie pan.
Spread cottage cheese over top.
Pour spaghetti sauce over cottage cheese.
Sprinkle top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt maggie's dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients to taste.

title: texas pie
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients in order given.
Ladle the melted oleo over the top and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: bundt bread
directions: Melt margarine in 250° oven in Bundt pan.
Place biscuits on side in pan and bake at 250° or 275° until done.

title: apple nut squares
directions: Cream the margarine and add salt, sugar and beaten egg. Continue beating until light and creamy.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Mix well.
Turn into greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut into squares.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute broccoli and onion in oleo. Cook rice. Put broccoli and rice in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: egg custard(club member: laine shoemake)
directions: Beat eggs on low; add salt and sugar. Continue beating.
Pour hot milk over egg mixture; add vanilla. Put into unbaked pie crust. Sprinkle top with nutmeg. Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes. Really good.

title: overnight refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Add oil, sugar, eggs and 4 cups flour and salt.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in rest of flour.
Will be a soft dough.
Put in greased large bowl with lid.
Store in refrigerator and use as needed.
Will keep several days.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: farmhouse barbecue muffins
directions: In skillet, brown ground meat.
In small bowl, mix ketchup, brown sugar and vinegar, stir until smooth.
Add meat and mix well.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits, flatten into 5 inch circles.
Press each into bottom and sides of a greased muffin cup.
Divide meat mixture among muffin cups.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 5 minutes before removing from tin and serve.

title: mom's corn casserole
directions: Saute onions and peppers in margarine.
Add corn and beaten eggs.
Pour in casserole dish and top with dry cornbread mix. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 20 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach on paper towels.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into hollowed out bread loaf (sourdough or French).
Use bread chunks and vegetables for dipping.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Use 13 x 9-inch baking dish with cover.
Pour rice in the dish, covering the bottom.
Add the soups, but save some of onion soup mix to cover chicken.
Add milk and stir until evenly distributed. It is okay to have soup lumps.
Put chicken pieces on the top. Sprinkle with remaining onion soup mix.
Cover and bake at 275° for 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oyster crackers
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the vegetable oil, garlic powder, dill and dressing mix.
Add the oyster crackers and mix until crackers are well coated.
Store in covered container.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: avocado salad
directions: Mix avocados, onions and tomatoes.
Pour Italian dressing over all just before serving.
Very good with any Mexican dish or beans of any kind.

title: grandma's apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine 1/2 cup butter, flour, brown sugar and cinnamon for topping. In a 7 x 7-inch pan, spread apples and dot with 1/4
cup butter and lemon. Crumble topping generously over apples. bake for 30 minutes. Touch with knife to test apples for softness. Serve piping hot with vanilla ice-cream.

title: chocolate peanut butter cake
directions: Scald milk and margarine; set aside.
In a large bowl mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt; beat well, then add flour, baking powder and milk and margarine mixture.
Mix well.
Grease cookie sheet. Pour batter into cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven.
Spread peanut butter over cake.
Cool.
Melt milk chocolate, spread over peanut butter and refrigerate until chocolate is hard.

title: soy chicken
directions: In a deep pan, melt the sugar in the soy sauce. Heat a frying pan and add oil, ginger and garlic. Fry the whole chicken until lightly browned. Place chicken in the pan with sugar and soy sauce, cover and cook slowly until tender.
Turn from time to time to get an even brown. About 1 hour.

title: grape wine
directions: Stomp grapes real hard.
Add warm water.
Let stand in cool, dark place to sour, 4 or 5 days.
Strain through.
Add 2 1/2 pounds sugar to each gallon of juice.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti; drain.
Return to pan 1/2 jar sauce, Ricotta and some Parmesan cheese.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle a little Parmesan cheese on ziti.
Spread remaining sauce over top. Place Mozzarella over sauce.
Bake at 375° until cheese bubbles.

title: aunt pee wee's sweet potato pones
directions: Cut up enough sweet potatoes to measure 1 gallon and 1 quart. Shake potatoes down a little when measuring.
Cook potatoes until tender.
Drain.
Add butter to cooked potatoes while hot so butter will melt.
Beat well with mixer.
Combine sugars, spices and flour in another bowl.
Let potatoes cool, then gradually add flour mixture to potatoes, alternating with Pet milk.
Mix well. Pour into 4 to 5 greased iron skillets.
Melt some margarine and pour on top; then sprinkle with sugar.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350° to 400°.

title: broccoli casserole(a la pat mechun, presbyterian pastor)
directions: Spread cooked broccoli in a 1 1/2-quart oblong pan.
Make white sauce of butter, flour, bouillon and milk.
Pour over broccoli. Heat water and butter until melted.
Pour over stuffing mix and toss to coat.
Add nuts and combine thoroughly.
Spread stuffing mix over broccoli and sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Rinse large saucepan with cold water; do not dry.
Pour in milk; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir in rice; return to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally until rice is tender, about 55 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook chicken breast and cut up. Put onion in large bowl and add soups, broth and chilies.

title: cool and creamy fruit cup
directions: Put the colander in the mixing bowl. Empty the orange sections and pineapple tidbits into the colander letting the juices run into the bowl. Throw away the juices.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together for 2 minutes.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: homemade american style noodles
directions: Beat the yolks and egg until they are light.
Beat in the salt and 3 tablespoons of cold water.
Using your hands, work the flour into the mixture to make a stiff dough.
Cut into three equal parts.
Cover with plastic wrap and let rest a few minutes.

title: honey mustard mayonnaise
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Makes 1 cup.

title: banana spice cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add shortening, buttermilk and bananas.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat 1 minute.
Pour batter in 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
If desired, frost with cream cheese icing when cool.

title: lime salad
directions: Stir together boiling water and jello until dissolved.
Mix cream cheese and pineapple together.
To jello mixture, add marshmallow and cheese mixture.
Let set until almost set.
Then beat with mixer.
Add whipped cream and pecans.
Pour into mold until set.

title: cheese cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie pan, then cool in refrigerator for about 3 hours.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix kool-aid and chill.
About 20 minutes before serving add chilled ginger ale and sherbet.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Separate dough into 8 triangles. Place in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points towards the center. Press over bottom and top sides to form a crust and seal portion. Mix eggs and milk, salt, pepper and pour onto crust. Spoon cooked sausage over top. Sprinkle with potatoes and top with cheese. Bake at 375 for 30 minutes.

title: tutti bread
directions: Put cheese slices in between each slice of bread.
Mix next 4 ingredients and drizzle over bread.
Put crumbled bacon in between slices of bread, also.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: ham puffs
directions: Blend cream cheese, egg yolk, onion juice, baking powder, horseradish, hot sauce and salt.
Spread deviled ham on each bread square; top with layer of cream cheese mixture.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hamburger diane
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, garlic, onion and mushrooms.
Cook over medium heat for 2 minutes.
Push to side of skillet and place 4 hamburger patties in skillet.
Cook until done.
Serve mushrooms-onion mixture over patties.

title: toasted salted coconut
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Pierce at least 1 eye of coconut with an ice pick or nail and hammer.
Drain liquid.
Bake coconut about 15 minutes, or until shell cracks.
Remove from oven.
When cool enough to handle, rap nut with a hammer to break open.
Pull meat away from shell; discard shell.
Working over a baking sheet and using a vegetable peeler, shave meat into long, thin strips. Separate shavings evenly over baking sheet.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, tossing occasionally, until shavings are a light golden brown (shavings will not cook evenly;
some will brown, some will only have brown tips).
Remove from oven and pour onto a large sheet of wax paper.
Sprinkle hot coconut with salt.
Cool completely before storing in an airtight container. Yield:
About 8 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in dish.
Melt margarine and add to corn flakes.
Put on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix Stove Top dressing according to directions on package. Mix instant gravy mix as package indicates.
Mix onion with ground beef.
Place in 3-quart casserole dish.
Add Stove Top dressing and cover with gravy mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
tags: Stove Top dressing mix for beef

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat all ingredients together and put in a 2-quart casserole.

title: strawberry-nut salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Fold in strawberries.
Mix pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Add to Jell-O.
Pour half of the mixture into a 12 x 8-inch or 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm. Spread with sour cream. Gently pour remaining over and chill.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in margarine.
Add flour and mix.
Add water and seasoning.
Cook slowly 10 minutes or so.
Add sour cream and serve over noodles or rice.

title: 1, 2, 3 step peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake until golden brown.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry with paper towels. Place chicken in a bowl and cover with buttermilk. Refrigerate overnight. In a bowl, combine flour and seasonings. Dredge each piece of chicken in flour mixture; repeat. In a skillet, heat 1 to 2-inches of oil. Fry chicken until tender and golden brown.

title: apple dumpling
directions: Peel, core and quarter however many apples you want to do. Wrap 1/4 apple in one crescent roll. Work with hands until entire piece of apple is covered. Place in casserole dish. Bring to a boil the orange juice, butter, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg. After the butter has melted, stir well and pour into casserole dish with apples. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Can serve with dollop of vanilla ice cream.

title: cheese ball #2
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into ball.
Chill.
Serve with any kind of crackers.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: cranberry orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, salt, fresh cranberries, pecans, apricots, dried cranberries, and orange zest in a bowl. Set aside. In another bowl, mix the canola oil, applesauce, and soy/rice milk and vinegar. Fold the dry ingredients into the liquid ingredients and combine gently.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Mix with soup and sour cream. Crumble desired amount of Ritz crackers on top.
Sprinkle poppy seeds over Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: beef log
directions: Chop dried beef very fine.
(Food processor works great). Save about 1/4 cup.
Mix all ingredients together; chill.
Roll into log or ball.
Roll in 1/4 cup chopped beef that was saved.

title: chicken parmesan pie
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 25 minutes, then cut up in bite-size pieces.
Spread cottage cheese in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top of cottage cheese.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine and mix ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Place the eggs in pan and cover with lukewarm water.
Heat rapidly to boiling point, then boil about 8 minutes.
Remove the pan from heat, cool eggs in cold running water.
Peel the eggs carefully and cut eggs in half lengthwise; remove the yolks.
Place egg yolks and other ingredients in bowl.
Mix with fork until well blended.
Spoon some of the egg yolk mixture back into each white half.
Sprinkle the top lightly with paprika.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pistachio dream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, yogurt, egg whites and vanilla (beat at low speed for a minute).
Gradually beat in soda.
Pour into a 9 x 13 pan sprayed with non-stick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: gazpacho garden salad
directions: In 1-pint jar with tight fitting lid, combine oil, ReaLemon, garlic, salt and pepper.
Shake well.
In narrow 1-quart glass container, layer 1/2 each of the green pepper, tomatoes, cucumber and onion.
Repeat layering with remaining vegetables.
Pour dressing over salad.
Chill 4 hours to blend flavors.
Makes 8 servings.

title: green tomato casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Layer green tomato slices, cheese and crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Continue layers, ending with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until tomatoes are tender. Tomatoes may be parboiled first if baking time is to be short.

title: heavenly hash salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl and chill overnight.
Makes 5 (1 cup) servings.

title: corned beef cracker spread
directions: Mix all ingredients until well mixed.
Let sit for several hours or overnight.
Serve with a variety of crackers.
Keep well for several days.

title: chicken moo goo gai pan
directions: Cut poultry into 1-inch cubes.
Combine with soy sauce, oil and ginger; mix well.
Spray nonstick electric frypan or large skillet with cooking spray.
Add poultry in single layer.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until lightly browned.
Stir in onion and mushrooms.
Mix well.
Stir in 3/4 cup broth.
Add mixed vegetables.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Mix remaining broth with cornstarch until smooth; stir into skillet.
Cook and stir until sauce is thick.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings, approximately 190 calories each.

title: opal basil vinegar
directions: Opal basil will make a wonderful herb vinegar, imparting both its flavor and color to the vinegar.
Start with a dry, clean bottle.
Pack several sprigs of opal basil to make 2 cups.
Place into bottle.
Fill basil-packed bottle to within one inch of top of bottle with a quality white wine or cider vinegar.
Let stand in dark place about three weeks.

title: red beans and rice(low-fat)
directions: Place water and rice in saucepan; bring to boil.
Cover and reduce to low heat for about 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; return to boil.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 10 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla and butter.
Mix in bread crumbs.
Put in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Add raisins and butter.

title: pineapple banana nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs.
Add the four dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add oil last.
Pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Toothpick should come out clean, not sticky! Keep in refrigerator or freezes well.

title: hot mexican brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix per package.
Drain peppers and add to mix.
Bake per package.
Serve with a lot of milk.

title: butter cookies
directions: Work first 5 ingredients together to form smooth paste; add carob chips.
Roll a spoonful of dough between the palms of hands. Flatten with bottom of glass or cookie press.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 25 minutes at 325°, until golden brown.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburger with the onions, salt, chili powder and cumin powder.
Add tomato sauce, paste and soup; cook slowly for about 2 hours.
Sauce is enough for several hot dogs.

title: easy corned beef and potatoes
directions: Peel
potatoes	and
onions.
Cut them into cubes.
Put into a frying
pan and cover with water.	Cook on medium-high until potatoes are tender.
Add the can of corned beef and mix it in with
potatoes.
Cook
on low heat until corned beef is heated. Pepper
and
salt
as necessary.
The corned beef has salt in it already.

title: cheesy mushroom puffs
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl combine cream cheese, mushrooms, pimiento, onion and hot pepper sauce.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits; press or roll each to a 4-inch circle.
Spread each with a heaping teaspoon mushroom mixture; roll up and seal edges.
Cut into 6 pieces.
Roll in croutons.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 18 minutes until brown. Serve warm.
Makes 60.

title: twenty four hour dill pickles
directions: In a gallon jar, place sliced cucumbers, dill and garlic. Bring to a boil water, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Pour hot solution over cucumbers.
Let stand until cool.
Put on lid and refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine hamburger meat, onions, green peppers, mushrooms, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Place into pan (loaf or square).
Bake 400° until done.
Drain grease.
Mix tomato soup; heat until boiling.
Pour over meat loaf.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Mix 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon and roll each biscuit in the mixture and place them on edge in a greased Bundt pan.
Combine last four ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes, then flip over onto a plate.

title: old fashioned stack cake
directions: Stir together buttermilk, soda and baking powder.
Set aside.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix together.
Batter will be stiff.
Grease and flour pans. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Use Delicious or Stayman apples. Makes 2 to 3 loaves.

title: pineapple whipped cream mold
directions: Chill beater and bowl before whipping cream.
Helps to whip faster.
Dissolve jello in hot water and let cool.
Mash soft cheese and add pineapple with juice.

title: russian tea
directions: Simmer water, sugar, cinnamon sticks and whole cloves for 15 minutes.
Take 1/2 cup mixture and tea bag; bring to boil.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Strain or remove spices.
Add mixture. Add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix cream, vinegar and sugar.
Heat; cool.
Beat eggs and pour into mixture and heat until it gets thick.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer nuts and raisins on bottom. Break 1 thawed loaf into pieces evenly over raisins and nuts. Melt margarine, sugar, milk and pudding in pan.
Pour over bread. Sprinkle on cinnamon.
Break second loaf and fill in all spaces covering nuts and raisins.
Cover with towel and let raise 2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Invert immediately to cool.
(Put waxed paper under rack to catch syrup.)

title: broccoli soup
directions: Chop the onion into 1 cup of water; let boil.
Add the broccoli; cook until tender.
Add soups and Velveeta; cook until cheese is melted.

title: popcorn gone nuts
directions: Combine popcorn and nuts in large bowl.
Set aside.
Combine butter, sugar and syrup in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cook, stirring constantly to 300° on candy thermometer.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sprinkle soda over raisins.
Pour hot water over them.
Stir in sugar.
Break egg yolks in measuring cup; add to measuring cup with eggs enough mayonnaise to equal 3/4 cup.
Combine eggs, mayonnaise and sugar.
Stir in flour.
Save 1/2 cup flour and roll nuts in flour.
Add nuts to batter.
Bake in 3 layers at 325° until done.
Frost with 7-Minute Frosting or favorite frosting.

title: mac-n-cheese for crockpot
directions: In crockpot combine all ingredients and cook on low 3 1/2 hours.
Stir every 1/2 hour.
(I double this to fill my crockpot.)

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, pumpkin, shortening and orange peel.
Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in raisins and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet; cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes.
Add sugar and continue beating.
Add rest of ingredients, mix well.
Grease and flour 11x16 pan.
Pour cake in pan and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sheral's corn muffins
directions: Follow directions on box of Jiffy mix.
When thoroughly mixed, add sour cream.
Pour into muffin papers and bake as directed.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and boil for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Mix well and drop by spoonful on waxed paper and let cool.

title: rich pastry
directions: Combine flour and salt in bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender or fork until pieces are size of peas.
Mix egg, water and vinegar in cup and gradually stir in flour mixture until evenly moistened.
Form into ball, handling as little as possible.
Roll out as directed in recipe.
Makes two 10-inch crusts.
Everyone will rave about your flaky pie crust.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and stir until sauce dissolves.
Add pineapple and nuts.
May be served with sour cream on top.

title: apple glazed baked ham
directions: Mix first four ingredients and cook in a saucepan over low heat until melted and well blended, stirring constantly.
Baste ham with jelly mixture.
Cover and return ham to oven and bake at 350 degrees for one additional hour.
Serve immediately.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cloves, ginger, cinnamon, baking soda and salt in a bowl.
Beat eggs in another bowl.
Add oil, milk and pulp.
Mix together.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into prepared loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: salisbury steak deluxe
directions: In bowl, combine soup, mustard, Worcestershire and horseradish.
Blend well and set aside.
In another bowl, lightly beat egg; add bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup of soup mixture.
Add beef and mix well.
Shape into six patties.

title: corn dish
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese; mix well.
Pour into dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes longer.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve sugar and jello in boiling water.
Add sour cream, drained mandarin oranges, and drained pineapple.
Pour into 2 quart dish.
Chill before serving.

title: essence of emeril
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Store in tight container and season as you wish.
Try on chicken, steak, burgers, pizza, cottage cheese, eggs, almost anything.

title: italian zucchini
directions: Saute onion, zucchini and spices in olive oil, until zucchini is crisp-tender.
Add tomatoes.
Cook on medium until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with Parmesan before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and pour into an oblong baking dish.
Mix the flour, margarine and milk.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: hearty egg scramble
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion and green pepper in butter until crisp-tender.
Add potatoes and ham; cook and stir for 5 minutes.
In a bowl, beat eggs, water and pepper; pour over ham mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until eggs are set.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix
the first four ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
(A Bundt cake pan can be used.) Add
lemon	juice to confectioners sugar.
Pour slowly over warm cake.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients together on medium speed.
Will be thick.
Store in a tightly covered jar in the refrigerator.

title: beef rouladen
directions: In skillet cook bacon until crisp; remove and crumble.
Cut meat into 6 pieces (6 x 4-inch); pound.
Spread each with 1 teaspoon mustard.
Place 2 pieces of pickle and 4 pieces of carrot across the narrow end; sprinkle with 2 teaspoons onion.
Starting at narrow end, roll up.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Brown roll-ups in drippings; pour off fat.
Stir in soup, celery, parsnips and parsley.
Cook over low heat 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Thin with water if desired.
Serve with mashed potatoes.
Garnish with bacon.
This is nice for a company or Sunday dinner.
Serves 6.

title: turkey or chicken pie
directions: In saucepan, over heat, add 1/4 cup water and stuffing.
Mash stuffing into water until the consistency of mashed potatoes.
Add gravy and mix again.
Add turkey or chicken and as much frozen vegetables as you like and mix.
Pour into pie shell; top with another pie shell and seal.
Cut two slices in middle of crust with a sharp knife.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.
Serve with cranberry sauce.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak crumbs in milk 10 minutes.
Cook onion in 1/2 of margarine until yellow.
Add to meat with seasonings and egg.
Add bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Form into small balls.
Cook in margarine until brown.
Sprinkle with flour, coating well.
Add milk or cream.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: white nut loaf
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together into bowl. Add egg and milk and mix only until dry ingredients are moistened. Stir in nuts.
Grease loaf pan and dust with flour.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Mix and set aside.

title: sausage balls
directions: Put everything in a bowl.
Pour in milk, all at once.
Stir until mixture leaves sides of bowl.
Knead 12 times on lightly floured surface.
Form into balls.
Place on baking sheet 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake 15 minutes or until browned.
Bake at 425°.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef with onion. Add salt, vinegar and brown sugar. Add ketchup and beans. Simmer 15 minutes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: munchins goodies
directions: Melt oleo and mix with graham cracker crumbs; spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chocolate bits, nuts and coconut; drizzle milk over all and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into bars.

title: dippety doo dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and warm over double boiler or in microwave.
Mix well.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg.
Add milk alternately with dry ingredients.
Add lemon rind and nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chuck roast
directions: Flour meat and brown on all sides in cooking oil.
Add onion to oil and brown.
Mix catsup, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce and pour over meat.
Add enough water to meat and mixture to come to top of meat.
Cook until tender 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together and pour into pie crust. Chill before serving.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add butter, hot applesauce and spices. Then add fruits and nuts.
Add soda and flour; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fruity salad
directions: Skin melon and cantaloupe.
Cut in half and scoop out insides. Chop melon and cantaloupe and place in a large bowl.
Pull grapes off stem and add to bowl; toss gently.
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons of preserves and toss until well mixed.
Serve in wine glasses topped with whipped cream.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients in a slow cooker and simmer all day.
Serve.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: In an oblong pan, layer the following ingredients:
spinach (torn), hard-boiled eggs (chopped), bacon (crumbled), salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon sugar sprinkled, lettuce (torn), peas, onion (chopped) and salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon sugar, sprinkled.
Top with sour cream and mayonnaise mixed together.
Chill overnight.

title: butterscotch dessert surprise
directions: Put in 9 x 13-inch pan; bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: rye bread and dip
directions: Mix together one day before serving.
Hollow out middle of bread to make a bowl for the dip.
Place small pieces of bread around bread bowl and add dip just before you eat.

title: salmon pie
directions: Put bottom crust in a deep 9-inch pie plate.
Pick over salmon and mix all ingredients together.
Put in plate.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 to 60 minutes, until crust is brown.

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: In saucepan mix sugar and starch.
Gradually stir in orange juice until smooth.
Stir constantly, bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice and grated rind.
Cool completely.
Fold in fruit.
Turn into cookie crust; chill 4 hours.

title: country style venison steak
directions: Combine flour, Season-All, pepper, m.s.g. and nutmeg.
Pound this seasoned flour into both sides of steak.
Brown on both sides.
Brown both sides of steak in hot oil in a heavy skillet. Add onions, carrots and beef flavor base, which has been dissolved in water.
If you like to cook with wine, replace about one half of the water with wine.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Serves four.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup, onion and eggs together.
Place broccoli in baking dish; pour mixture over broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs, nuts and Cheddar cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Melt butter.
Mix butter into bread mix.
Set aside.
(Combine squash, onion, soup and sour cream.) Mix together.
Add half of butter and bread mixture.
Blend.
Add remaining mixture on top.
Bake in oven 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tailgate beans
directions: Brown bacon and ground beef; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: instant spice tea mix
directions: Mix ingredients together well and store in jar or airtight container.
Makes 1/2 quart of powder.

title: stuffed giant shells
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Drain excess fat.
Cool.
Stir in cheese, crumbs, parsley and egg.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook shells in boiling water until almost tender, about 15 minutes.
Drain.
Use meat mixture to stuff shells.
Spoon 1/4 of the sauce over the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan. Place shells on top of sauce, side by side in a single layer.
Mix wine with remaining sauce and pour over shells.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve sprinkled with additional grated cheese.

title: shrimp cream cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1-quart microproof casserole.
Cook on High (maximum) power 3 1/2 to 4 minutes or until warm.
Stir. Serve with crackers or chips. Cooking time:
2 minutes.

title: corn casserole i
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Cook at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: eclair
directions: Lay crackers in bottom of baking dish (whole).
Mix pudding and evaporated milk.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour over crackers. Apply another layer of crackers on top of pudding.
Chill.
Spread frosting over top layer of crackers.

title: pink pasta sauce
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil and when brown discard clove.

Then saute onion in oil; add tomatoes, bay leaf, salt, bouillon cube, sugar and butter, let simmer for 30 minutes uncovered. Remove bay leaf; add cream and basil.	Simmer an additional 10 to 15 minutes to blend flavors.
Serve over penne pasta or rigatoni.
If you prefer meat, fry a chicken breast in a little olive oil until browned; and then cover with sauce and serve. Delicious!

title: great barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and store in the refrigerator. Great on chicken, beef or pork!

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown onions and pepper in margarine. Add all remaining ingredients, except cheese; mix well. Pour into a greased casserole dish; top with cheese. Place in 375° oven until cheese is melted.

title: lorna doone dessert
directions: Mix crushed cookies and oleo and press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix pudding, milk and ice cream and spread on top of crumbs. Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding mixture.
Sprinkle crushed Heath bars on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: albert's shrimp dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and chill.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in olive oil, adding water as needed to keep from sticking.
Combine the Ricotta, tofu (if used), Parmesan, spinach, egg whites, black pepper, parsley and sauteed onion and garlic, mixing well. Cook the lasagna according to package directions.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat whipped margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar; beat well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flour with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Fold in egg whites last.
Bake in 3 cake pans at 325° oven.
Let cool and frost.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sharon's brownies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: purple cow for two
directions: Stir or place in blender.

title: salad dressing chocolate cake
directions: Stir ingredients all together in bowl until smooth.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.

title: italian smoked sausage bean soup
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven over medium heat, brown sausage and onions in oil for 5 minutes.
Add the tomatoes with the juice, water, pasta and broth and bring to a boil.
Add the beans.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until the pasta is tender, about 15 minutes.
Just before serving, sprinkle with grated cheese.
Serves 6.

title: snow-day vegetable soup
directions: Plan on 2 hours cooking time, including time to return to proper simmer after adding ingredients.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Mix sugar and Karo in large saucepan; bring to low boil. Remove from stove and add peanut butter; stir until blended.
Add Rice Krispies; mix well.
In double boiler, melt butterscotch chips and chocolate chips until creamy.
Firmly pat Rice Krispies mixture into ungreased 9 x 13 -inch pan.
Pour the melted chip mix on top.
Let the icing firm up before cutting.
Children love this dessert.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Peel, core and thinly slice apples.
Combine all other ingredients and mix with apples.
Place in pie crust.
Top with topping.

title: hot chip dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Cut cheese into chunks and add to browned beef. Pour tomatoes and green chilies into cheese and beef mixture. Add Worcestershire sauce and chili powder to mixture. Cook until all the cheese has melted. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: polish sausage and cabbage
directions: Slice sausage, potatoes, cabbage and onions into medium size chunks and combine in a large saucepan.
Stir in chicken broth, then add water until the meat and vegetables are covered with liquid.
Add salt and pepper and let simmer for 45 minutes or until potatoes are cooked.
Correct seasoning and serve.

title: chicken breast orange
directions: Brush chicken with melted butter, then dust lightly with flour, salt and pepper.
Place skin side up in baking pan.
Add 1/2 cup hot water. Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Remove cover and bake 1 hour longer or until chicken is very tender.
Place 1 slice of orange on each breast and serve at once with Orange Sauce.

title: round steak with gravy
directions: Fry steak.
Fry onions.
Put onions on top of steak and simmer for 10 to 20 minutes.
Put on hot plate and eat.

title: mississippi caviar
directions: Drain peas; add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Store in refrigerator at least 3 days.
After the first day, remove garlic. Serve with wide corn chips.

title: toll house chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until well blended.
Add melted butter.
Stir in chocolate morsels and walnuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Toss hot spaghetti with oil or butter.
Combine eggs and 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese. Stir into spaghetti.
Pour spaghetti mixture in pie plate.
Form into a crust.

title: pea casserole
directions: Drain peas and put in baking dish.
Mix with soup and cheese. Sprinkle potato chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.

title: pecan roll
directions: Crush vanilla wafers.
Mix with condensed milk and nuts. Shape in roll and put in refrigerator and chill. Cut in slices and serve.
Rich and good!

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Combine meat, onion and seasonings in fry pan.
Stir until brown.
Cut vegetables in inch slices and cook 6 minutes.
Mix with soup and meat; top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in water well covered for about 30 minutes or until done.
Add chicken cubes while boiling.
Cut up tortillas and drop into chicken and broth while boiling.
Cover with lid; turn down on low and let it cook for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve.
